Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.75,0:01:01.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}Days of you and me
Dialogue: 2,0:01:12.09,0:01:17.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,So {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} opens with Joel, discussing the ending events of the first game.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.58,0:01:20.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,The cameras focused on the thread board of the guitar,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.34,0:01:23.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,which has a very distinctive symbol on it, which will be important later.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.91,0:01:27.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,I want you to take a mental picture of this scene
Dialogue: 2,0:01:27.25,0:01:30.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it's going to come back all the way at the end of the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.60,0:01:33.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,During this conversation between Joel and Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.81,0:01:38.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel explains his decision to save Ellie over humanity.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:38.37,0:01:43.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now even this point was one of controversy when the game first launched.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.86,0:01:45.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see, at the end of the first game,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.42,0:01:50.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,there was a serious question as to whether or not the Fireflies would be able to develop a vaccine at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.91,0:01:55.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was one of the reasons that a lot of people thought that Joel's actions were highly justified.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:55.32,0:01:58.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,Not just in that he was saving Ellie, his "daughter character",
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.89,0:02:02.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,but rather that he didn't want to sacrifice Ellie's life
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.78,0:02:07.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,for the sake of a cause which likely wouldn't find success any ways.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.14,0:02:11.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, the Fireflies in the first game are pretty damn incompetent.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.52,0:02:14.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,They hire somebody from outside their ranks to transport,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.67,0:02:19.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,who is likely the most important human being who has ever lived in the form of Ellie
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.29,0:02:24.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,all the way across the country in order to hopefully develop a vaccine.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.21,0:02:28.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when you get there and you explore the hospital at the end of the first game,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:28.38,0:02:31.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,you find out that a lot of the doctors involved in this procedure
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.76,0:02:34.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,are unsure as to whether or not it's even possible.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:34.68,0:02:39.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, literally, every single person in this hospital
Dialogue: 2,0:02:39.35,0:02:46.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,is completely inexperienced in developing a vaccine for a fungus such as this.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.29,0:02:49.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the Fireflies argument is that at least there's a chance.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.73,0:02:50.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,If Ellie runs off,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.88,0:02:54.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they don't even attempt to extract any of the antibodies
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.01,0:02:59.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,or whatever the hell his inside of her brain that allows her to survive after having a bite.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.25,0:03:02.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then they will never know whether or not a vaccine is possible.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.88,0:03:07.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if they crack her skull open and try and develop some sort of vaccine at the very least,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.62,0:03:09.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,then there's a chance.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.15,0:03:11.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, in the opening for this sequel,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.97,0:03:14.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,we see that Joel is pretty confident
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.39,0:03:18.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they were trying to develop a vaccine and that they likely would have been able to,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.60,0:03:19.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,but that it would have killed her.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:19.95,0:03:24.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's Tommy's expression that I think sets the tone
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.44,0:03:27.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,for how the player is supposed to feel about Joel's decision.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.87,0:03:33.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's stunned, but at the same time he can't really blame Joel for the choice that he made.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.45,0:03:36.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, later on, in this very intro sequence,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.96,0:03:40.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy turns to Joel and tells him that he would have done the same thing.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.56,0:03:46.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, the choice to open the game in this way is very, very important.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.14,0:03:50.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,The writers over at Naughty Dog wanted to remind the player of what Joel had done
Dialogue: 2,0:03:50.55,0:03:56.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,and establish that as the fulcrum from which every narrative mechanism will hinge.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.04,0:04:01.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,After this conversation, Tommy still unsure of how to react,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.26,0:04:05.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,simply tells Joel to hop on his horse and head back into town.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:05.31,0:04:08.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,It buys Tommy some time in order to form an opinion,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:08.40,0:04:12.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it also gives the player a chance to settle back into this world.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:12.93,0:04:15.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's really common for sequels to rush into things,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.54,0:04:19.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,giving the player a chance to see something new and fresh and different
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.05,0:04:21.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they only could have dreamed of in the first game.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.87,0:04:25.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, and thankfully Naughty Dog doesn't do this.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:25.35,0:04:28.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,They take their time during this intro to set things up,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.29,0:04:30.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think it works very, very well.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:30.66,0:04:33.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,You ride through a beautiful landscape and come up on Jackson,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.87,0:04:38.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's at this time that we get our first look at a fully realized Jackson,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.37,0:04:41.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,the city that we saw peak of at the end of the first game,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.31,0:04:42.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,but that we could only imagine.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:42.86,0:04:44.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I've got to hand it to Naughty Dog.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.67,0:04:51.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,This opening sequence has one of the most well realized cities I've ever seen in any video game ever.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:51.57,0:04:53.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,It truly is fantastic.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.52,0:05:01.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Every NPC, every animation, every building, every step in the snow is detailed and realistic.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.62,0:05:03.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,As far as immersion is concerned,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.48,0:05:08.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think this is one of the most fantastically effective games that's ever been created.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.60,0:05:10.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,After you reach the inside of the city,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:10.53,0:05:16.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy and Joel hop off of their horses and Tommy offers to stow Joel's horse for him,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.26,0:05:19.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,while also saying that he'll take the truth to his grave.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.35,0:05:21.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,This implies a couple of things.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:21.06,0:05:24.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,For one, it might seem as though he's referring directly to Ellie
Dialogue: 2,0:05:24.20,0:05:28.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,that if Ellie were to find out this truth, it would cause a lot of problems.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:28.74,0:05:31.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, as far as Ellie is concerned,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.08,0:05:35.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel simply took Ellie after a bunch of tests were run,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.40,0:05:40.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it was clear that she was not going to be able to provide any sort of help towards a vaccine at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:40.77,0:05:42.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the end of the first game,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:42.03,0:05:45.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's pretty clear that Ellie sees through this lie that Joel is telling,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.54,0:05:48.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,or at the very least, she expects that there's more to this story.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.84,0:05:52.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,For the sake of their relationship, she simply goes along with it.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:52.14,0:05:54.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, I think there's another implication to this as well,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.78,0:05:59.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that is that if other people in the camp were to find out what Joel had done,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.19,0:06:01.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,I am not so sure that they would approve of it either.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:01.62,0:06:06.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, we can talk all day about how incompetent the Fireflies were in the first game.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.21,0:06:08.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think there's a real argument to be had there.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.31,0:06:11.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, if I had to entrust them with the fate of humanity,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:11.46,0:06:14.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would hop on the next asteroid off the planet.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:14.28,0:06:18.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,What I mean, though, is that Naughty Dog is trying to tell his story,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:18.24,0:06:22.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they're framing the plot points the way that they want you the player to see them.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.47,0:06:24.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,For the sake of this story,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:24.15,0:06:28.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's important to understand that the Fireflies were the ones that were trying to save humanity
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.84,0:06:36.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,and were apparently on the cusp of developing a vaccine to save countless millions of lives.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.06,0:06:40.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,And once again, for the sake of this story, that's been told in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,0:06:40.84,0:06:43.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel is the one that undid that.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:43.52,0:06:49.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, at the very least, if Ellie had gone under the knife, there would have been a chance for a vaccine.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:49.68,0:06:55.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,By killing the doctors that were about to operate on Ellie and potentially develop a vaccine,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.71,0:06:58.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,he effectively saved his "daughter figure",
Dialogue: 2,0:06:58.23,0:07:02.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,but he damned all of humanity for the rest of time.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.67,0:07:06.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,In other words, he strained at a gnat but swallowed a camel.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:06.39,0:07:11.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,He traded what seemed to be a smaller evil for a much much larger evil,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:11.31,0:07:17.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and he did this because his judgment was clouded by his own personal wants and wishes.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.10,0:07:23.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,This isn't to say that Joel would or does regret any of this in this particular sequence.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.13,0:07:26.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it is to say that the players should start seriously considering
Dialogue: 2,0:07:26.44,0:07:32.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,whether or not Joel's actions were justified, or perhaps even whether or not they were right.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:32.31,0:07:32.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:32.99,0:07:38.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog is going to help you think about this by constantly bringing it up using flashbacks
Dialogue: 2,0:07:38.39,0:07:41.25,辉英,,0,0,0,, as Ellie grew up in Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:41.25,0:07:43.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I promise you before you know it,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:43.05,0:07:46.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,you might even be convinced that Joel is in fact a villain.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:46.74,0:07:52.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,This isn't to say that Joel is unlikable character that you should hate him or wish that he were dead,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:52.65,0:07:56.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,but rather Joel is the one that damned humanity.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:56.76,0:08:03.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you tell any other story and there's a character which damns humanity for the sake of one single person,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.90,0:08:06.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,we would say he's a bad guy.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:06.00,0:08:08.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps we wouldn't even say bad guy,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:08.64,0:08:13.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,we would simply say that he was a confused or perhaps mistaken individual,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:13.56,0:08:15.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,whose motivations were complex.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:15.90,0:08:20.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the point is, it's not as simple as hero and villain.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:20.94,0:08:23.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,There is a lot of gray in between.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:23.19,0:08:28.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now this intro sequence is just shortly after Joel's arrival, while Ellie is still young.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:28.83,0:08:34.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's living out of grandmother's suite in the back of the house that is presumably owned by Joel.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:34.53,0:08:36.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's super cute that she has her own space,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:36.60,0:08:41.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it even now shows and tells a lot about their relationship.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:41.90,0:08:46.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now granted, Joel is a middle aged man that found this little girl,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:46.62,0:08:49.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,and he took her halfway across the country,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:49.32,0:08:51.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,rescued her from a bunch of cannibals,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:51.57,0:08:56.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,and now has her in a town that his brother runs with his wife.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.67,0:09:01.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,It could be presumed that her staying in his house could be considered an appropriate.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:01.71,0:09:03.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that's the point here.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:03.78,0:09:08.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel is Ellie's "father figure", and I don't think that's a controversial thing to say.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:08.58,0:09:15.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fact that Ellie wants space, physical space separated from him means a lot.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.75,0:09:18.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, we see Ellie and she's drawing something
Dialogue: 2,0:09:18.59,0:09:21.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,that will come back time and time again throughout the rest of the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:21.27,0:09:25.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's actually pretty artsy and gifted, artistically,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:25.05,0:09:29.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,you'll see this in the note book that you'll be using throughout the course of the main game.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:29.34,0:09:33.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,She often draws pictures of what she sees or sketches out different things
Dialogue: 2,0:09:33.67,0:09:36.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order to remind her to return to that area
Dialogue: 2,0:09:36.52,0:09:41.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,or simply to keep a journal of the events and happenings of the main story.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:41.40,0:09:44.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's listening to music when Joel comes in.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:44.01,0:09:48.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a really cute and awkward moment, but it's pretty damn sweet.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:48.99,0:09:52.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,It doesn't take a body language expert to see that there's a lot of tension here.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.83,0:09:57.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel's unsure of how to stand, where to move, how to talk, how to relate to her,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:57.15,0:09:59.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Ellie picks up on this as well.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:59.64,0:10:01.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,The tension is really palpable.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:01.71,0:10:05.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,They both know what happened in Utah hasn't been resolved,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:05.94,0:10:08.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,but neither knows how to broach the topic,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:08.16,0:10:10.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,so they simply delay it and push it off.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:10.56,0:10:16.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the point of this sequence is where Joel to express how much he needs Ellie in his life.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:16.68,0:10:21.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's all just take a moment to relax and appreciate how beautiful the scenery is,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:21.51,0:10:24.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,and how Ellie responds in classic Ellie fashion.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:34.00,0:10:37.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}If I ever were to lose you
Dialogue: 2,0:10:38.09,0:10:41.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}I'd surely lose myself
Dialogue: 2,0:10:42.55,0:10:46.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}Everything I have found hear
Dialogue: 2,0:10:46.65,0:10:50.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}I've not found by myself
Dialogue: 2,0:10:51.00,0:10:54.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}Try and sometimes you'll succeed
Dialogue: 2,0:10:54.92,0:10:58.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}To make this man of me
Dialogue: 2,0:10:59.68,0:11:03.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}All my stolen missing parts
Dialogue: 2,0:11:03.76,0:11:07.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}I've no need for anymore
Dialogue: 2,0:11:08.70,0:11:11.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}'Cause I believe
Dialogue: 2,0:11:13.12,0:11:17.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}And I believe 'cause I can see
Dialogue: 2,0:11:19.14,0:11:22.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}Our future days
Dialogue: 2,0:11:23.63,0:11:26.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,300)}Days of you and me
Dialogue: 2,0:11:53.46,0:11:55.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure I don't need to tell you this
Dialogue: 2,0:11:55.02,0:11:59.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,but this song is going to come up time and time again throughout the course of the main story.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:59.31,0:12:01.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,So make sure that you remember it.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:01.53,0:12:05.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Though I'm sure I don't need to tell you that because you'll likely remember this for the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:05.91,0:12:08.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,considering how unbelievably touching it was.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:08.66,0:12:11.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Also a funny little thing that Neil Druckmann tweeted out.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:11.94,0:12:16.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Apparently he had been asked many many times on Twitter and in person
Dialogue: 2,0:12:16.04,0:12:19.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,why Pearl Jam's "Future Days" was used in the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:19.11,0:12:25.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,People ask this because the song didn't actually drop until October of 2013 officially.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:25.05,0:12:28.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that is actually a month after outbreak day in this universe,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:28.80,0:12:32.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,so it shouldn't have actually existed.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:32.06,0:12:33.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Neil Druckmann responded by saying,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:40.83,0:12:43.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you can actually go look it up on Youtube,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:43.14,0:12:45.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,and sure enough, Pearl Jam performed this live,
Dialogue: 2,0:12:45.81,0:12:51.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that video was posted on July, 26th of 2013.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:51.06,0:12:53.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's the actual date of the video.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:53.25,0:12:58.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a perfect example of Naughty Dog's excessive attention to detail.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:58.59,0:13:05.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think anybody would have cared, particularly if this song released three years after outbreak day.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:05.73,0:13:11.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the fact that they took it upon themselves to find a song that fit the theme and the tone of the game
Dialogue: 2,0:13:11.44,0:13:15.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that fits so perfectly within Joel and Ellie's relationship,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:15.39,0:13:19.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then to also make sure that it fit in with the timeline they were dealing with it.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:19.71,0:13:21.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:21.15,0:13:25.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,But once again its one of the examples of Naughty Dog's perfectionism.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:25.23,0:13:28.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,They don't need to care about these little things, but they do.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:28.53,0:13:32.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's what sets them apart, whether you love them or hate them.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:32.19,0:13:36.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,After this touching flashback, we cut to Ellie, waking up late.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:36.00,0:13:39.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Jesse, a character we'll get to see a little bit throughout the course of the game
Dialogue: 2,0:13:39.53,0:13:42.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,is at her front door, giving her crap for sleeping in.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:42.44,0:13:46.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Over the next ten or so minutes as you walk through the town,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:46.08,0:13:51.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,you have a recap of everything that went down and then some in the trailer from E3 2018.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:51.60,0:13:53.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I found this particularly interesting,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:53.49,0:13:57.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,because that sequence where Dina and Ellie share their first kiss,
Dialogue: 2,0:13:57.87,0:14:00.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,I thought was a pretty important sequence to see.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:00.78,0:14:04.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Naughty Dog doesn't show it to the player, at least not right now.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:04.41,0:14:08.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Instead, they rely on the dialog to explain what happened,
Dialogue: 2,0:14:08.28,0:14:09.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I can't help to notice that
Dialogue: 2,0:14:09.48,0:14:15.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,this is the first instance where trailers are important to a contextual grasp of the game itself.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:15.45,0:14:17.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because, after all, in this case,
Dialogue: 2,0:14:17.28,0:14:21.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,the scene that's being discussed isn't actually shown to the player
Dialogue: 2,0:14:21.71,0:14:24.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,until the last 15 or so minutes of the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:24.79,0:14:32.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Time and time again, stuff that was shown in the trailers is either changed drastically or is moved around
Dialogue: 2,0:14:32.09,0:14:37.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,such that you need to have seen the trailer in order to truly understand what's going on.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:37.99,0:14:42.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I understand that it's a small thing to point out or be frustrated by,
Dialogue: 2,0:14:42.07,0:14:46.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,because after all chances are every single person who bought the game had seen that trailer.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:46.80,0:14:51.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, I still think it's strange to show a scene in a trailer,
Dialogue: 2,0:14:51.06,0:14:54.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,but then not show it in the game when that item is being discussed.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:54.87,0:14:57.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's one of countless times in this game,
Dialogue: 2,0:14:57.12,0:15:01.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Naughty Dog will take a sequence, cut it up into fifteen different parts
Dialogue: 2,0:15:01.22,0:15:05.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then spread it randomly, seemingly throughout the course of the story.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:05.04,0:15:07.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I think it helps with pacing
Dialogue: 2,0:15:07.04,0:15:11.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,by giving the player a break from a very stressful environment or activity,
Dialogue: 2,0:15:11.52,0:15:15.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,but often it feels as though it's jarring and out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:15.75,0:15:21.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we're going to get to some very egregious examples of this later on in the story.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:21.30,0:15:26.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,All that's really important to understand is that Ellie and Dina shared a first kiss,
Dialogue: 2,0:15:26.13,0:15:32.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,a character that we meet briefly, said something offensive and bigoted,
Dialogue: 2,0:15:32.73,0:15:35.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,and everybody wants you to know that it's bigoted.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:35.61,0:15:40.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,You get some sandwiches and then you go off to start on patrol.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:40.11,0:15:43.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's also important to understand that Jesse just broke up with Dina
Dialogue: 2,0:15:43.64,0:15:48.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,around a week to a week and a half before this is taking place.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:48.32,0:15:52.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or maybe Dina broke up with him, or maybe it was mutual.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:52.05,0:15:57.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know, it… it's so high school…  these first few conversations. It's kind of painful.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:57.51,0:16:02.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Jessie heads off to the stable to prepare the horses and the rest of the attendees.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:02.16,0:16:06.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,While Dina and Ellie shared a snowball fight against a bunch of kids.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:06.52,0:16:09.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I kind of found this snowball fight to be a little weird
Dialogue: 2,0:16:09.47,0:16:14.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it seemed as though it's meant to serve as some sort of combat introduction.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:14.37,0:16:19.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I think I was just reading too much into it because I don't think it does a very good job of that.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:19.38,0:16:22.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I did go back through the game a second time,
Dialogue: 2,0:16:22.17,0:16:27.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,as I stated previously on "New Game +" and on the hardest difficulty.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:27.39,0:16:32.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,After becoming completely familiarized with the controls after playing the entire game,
Dialogue: 2,0:16:32.07,0:16:37.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,this whole snowball fight was much more intriguing and interesting and frankly fun
Dialogue: 2,0:16:37.15,0:16:39.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,than it was the first time I played.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:39.12,0:16:43.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,The three tiered stance that Ellie's able to have between standing, crouch and prone
Dialogue: 2,0:16:43.90,0:16:46.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,is something that takes a minute to get used to.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:46.47,0:16:51.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,I know it sounds weird because that's true of pretty much any third person or first person shooter
Dialogue: 2,0:16:51.90,0:16:53.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they're going to have those three stances.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:53.85,0:16:59.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}, there are multiple levels of movement associated with each.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:59.25,0:17:00.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's more of my point.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:00.48,0:17:05.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,The sequence does a very poor job of introducing the player to those three stances.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:05.58,0:17:10.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,But you are able to use each of those three stances in this sequence.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:10.32,0:17:11.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,It just seems a little jarring,
Dialogue: 2,0:17:11.79,0:17:15.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I will admit I appreciate the effort that they put into this
Dialogue: 2,0:17:15.56,0:17:18.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it's still way better than the alternative,
Dialogue: 2,0:17:18.45,0:17:22.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,which would be to have the standard stereotypical sequence
Dialogue: 2,0:17:22.68,0:17:26.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,where the protagonist goes and has shown how to use a gun,
Dialogue: 2,0:17:26.58,0:17:31.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's like issue bottles or some craps…  I hate that.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:31.35,0:17:36.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Probably the most egregious example would be the opening of Fallout 3 when you're given a BB gun,
Dialogue: 2,0:17:36.57,0:17:41.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then you go downstairs, shoot some targets and then some giant radroaches.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:41.94,0:17:44.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,I just think that that's so overplayed.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:44.46,0:17:47.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you're going to introduce shooting mechanics and combat,
Dialogue: 2,0:17:47.58,0:17:50.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,you should at the very least have a little bit of a creative spin to it,
Dialogue: 2,0:17:50.94,0:17:56.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,so I appreciate that throwing compacted snow at children was presented here.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:56.00,0:17:58.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,After hucking some powder you meet up with Dina,
Dialogue: 2,0:17:58.98,0:18:03.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,there's some awkward exchanges where Ellie isn't sure how to talk to…
Dialogue: 2,0:18:03.36,0:18:05.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean again, it… it's very high school.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:05.34,0:18:09.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,The two walks out the stables and you head out on patrol.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:09.00,0:18:12.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then the first surprise of the game hits,
Dialogue: 2,0:18:12.33,0:18:15.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,and to be honest, it's a surprise, even if you had the game spoiled for you.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:15.99,0:18:20.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see the camera slowly pans over a bunch of sleeping young adults.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:20.67,0:18:22.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,It centers on one girl
Dialogue: 2,0:18:22.32,0:18:27.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,who most of us will immediately recognize from the Paris Games trailer from 2017.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:27.93,0:18:31.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,She gets up talks to a young man who asks to show her something,
Dialogue: 2,0:18:31.53,0:18:34.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then we are given control of her.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:34.02,0:18:36.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,Like I said earlier, I had the game spoiled for me.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:36.75,0:18:42.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,But all of those spoilers said that you were going to get to play half of the game as Abby
Dialogue: 2,0:18:42.35,0:18:44.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,and start halfway through.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:44.34,0:18:48.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,I did not expect to be playing as her within the first 30 to 45 minutes.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:48.81,0:18:52.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,I bet you, at this point, some people had put the game down.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:52.05,0:18:55.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, there was a very vocal minority that said
Dialogue: 2,0:18:55.25,0:19:00.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they were going to flip out if you didn't play the whole game as Ellie and or Joel.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:00.12,0:19:03.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,But a key thing to understand here is that the player must give it time and effort
Dialogue: 2,0:19:03.84,0:19:06.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,to stand on its own and justify itself.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:06.51,0:19:10.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the same way that you can't judge a book by its cover or a film by its trailer.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:10.29,0:19:14.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,You'll never get an informed opinion of the game if you don't give it a chance.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:14.91,0:19:19.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,This isn't to say that you have to play every single game in order to have an opinion of every single game,
Dialogue: 2,0:19:19.29,0:19:24.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,but rather that if you're going to have an extremely negative or critical opinion of a game,
Dialogue: 2,0:19:24.18,0:19:26.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,you have to be able to justify that critical opinion.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:26.91,0:19:31.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,And in my opinion, I don't think it's fair to say that playing as any character
Dialogue: 2,0:19:31.44,0:19:37.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,other than the one on the Box-Art is bad and means that the game is terrible and not worth your time.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:37.07,0:19:40.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,After you take control of Abby and you start exploring through the woods,
Dialogue: 2,0:19:40.77,0:19:43.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,walking through some pretty deep snow,
Dialogue: 2,0:19:43.08,0:19:45.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,seeing some interesting landscapes,
Dialogue: 2,0:19:45.27,0:19:48.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,these two characters share in some dialogue about other people in the group,
Dialogue: 2,0:19:48.93,0:19:51.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,likely the same people that you just saw the camera pan over.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:51.65,0:19:56.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now we don't know any of these people at this point and Naughty Dog will do this a lot.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:56.31,0:20:00.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,They are unapologetic in their unexplained dialogue.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:00.18,0:20:03.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,The characters will have conversations that makes sense to them,
Dialogue: 2,0:20:03.21,0:20:08.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,but might not, or perhaps don't make any sense at all to the player.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:08.82,0:20:10.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I love this,
Dialogue: 2,0:20:10.08,0:20:15.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,though I do admit that it can be confusing to those who like to enjoy their content more passively.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:15.67,0:20:17.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,But this is a narrative game,
Dialogue: 2,0:20:17.55,0:20:21.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,it seems like it comes with the territory of this type of game to have dialogue
Dialogue: 2,0:20:21.54,0:20:23.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's much more realistic and grounded
Dialogue: 2,0:20:23.36,0:20:26.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,compared to dialogue that just hit you over the head with exposition.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:26.70,0:20:32.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,I also think it's important to note that these conversations make a second run of the game AWESOME.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:32.35,0:20:34.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seriously, every single thing they are discussing here,
Dialogue: 2,0:20:34.86,0:20:38.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,it makes perfect sense and is relatable and understandable.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:38.24,0:20:42.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once you've gone through the whole game and met all of these characters
Dialogue: 2,0:20:42.12,0:20:46.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,and grown to know them and care about them throughout the course of the story,
Dialogue: 2,0:20:46.62,0:20:51.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,and as somebody that usually placed their games that I critique at least two times,
Dialogue: 2,0:20:51.72,0:20:54.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,I really appreciated this because it made it.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:54.18,0:20:59.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,So my second run through was more informed and more interesting than my first run through.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:59.78,0:21:03.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Really, I think you should play the game a second time through just to give it a shot.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:03.72,0:21:08.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think you'll be surprised at how many little things were added that you didn't hear before.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:08.64,0:21:10.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,But for the sake of a first run through,
Dialogue: 2,0:21:10.48,0:21:15.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's important to note that Abby and Owen are the names of these two characters,
Dialogue: 2,0:21:15.18,0:21:18.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,they seem to have a previous relationship.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:18.15,0:21:23.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,In other words, they dated at some sort of romantic involvement at some point.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:23.07,0:21:30.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,And also that some girl named Mel, who Owen is apparently involved with at this point, is pregnant.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:30.69,0:21:32.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,There may be, I'm all alone in this,
Dialogue: 2,0:21:32.37,0:21:36.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,but the second I heard she was pregnant, I got a pit in my stomach.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:36.90,0:21:40.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is what I meant when I tweeted out early in my first run through of the game
Dialogue: 2,0:21:40.92,0:21:44.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,that I felt as though the opening was dreadful.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:44.85,0:21:50.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,I meant it in the purest sense of the word that the game fills you with dread.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:50.37,0:21:55.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,You have a sinking feeling in your stomach that something terrible is about to happen.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:55.17,0:21:59.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I don't know if it's just that the game was spoiled and so everybody saw this coming,
Dialogue: 2,0:21:59.61,0:22:05.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,or that it's some sort of masterful way that they designed all of these conversations and scenes
Dialogue: 2,0:22:05.76,0:22:09.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,that makes you feel as though there's an impending danger and doom.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:09.36,0:22:10.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know which it is.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:10.80,0:22:17.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would love to hear your opinion of it down in the comments section below or tweeted at me @LukeStephensTV.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:17.07,0:22:23.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless I can't help but feel as though everything terrible that could happen is about to happen.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:23.10,0:22:26.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so when I heard that this girl, Mel, was pregnant,
Dialogue: 2,0:22:26.97,0:22:31.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,I just knew something horrible was going to happen to her
Dialogue: 2,0:22:31.24,0:22:37.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,and likely that one of the characters we were being introduced to on Ellie's side of the fence
Dialogue: 2,0:22:37.08,0:22:41.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,would likely become pregnant to contrast the two relationships
Dialogue: 2,0:22:41.12,0:22:45.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,and to set up narrative beats where you could have one character faced with an option,
Dialogue: 2,0:22:45.81,0:22:47.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,have the other character faced with the other option
Dialogue: 2,0:22:47.86,0:22:51.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,and see how each reacts in their individual moments.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:51.15,0:22:54.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I understand that they likely doesn't make any sense at all
Dialogue: 2,0:22:54.15,0:22:55.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,if you haven't played through the game yourself,
Dialogue: 2,0:22:55.95,0:22:59.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,so I'm simply going to move on and loop back to it later.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:59.22,0:23:00.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,I promise it'll make sense.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:00.70,0:23:04.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Owen reach their destination, and they overlook Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:04.65,0:23:06.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a massive city.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:06.45,0:23:12.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,And judging Abby's reaction, it seems as though she didn't expect it to be this massive at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:12.30,0:23:16.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not clear what they're looking for, but it's a man for sure.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:16.17,0:23:19.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,any one with two brain cells to rub together will instantly know
Dialogue: 2,0:23:19.36,0:23:22.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they're talking about and looking for Joel
Dialogue: 2,0:23:22.61,0:23:25.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,though we don't know why at this particular moment.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:25.18,0:23:31.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Owen doesn't think that they should continue on this quest to reach whoever they're looking for
Dialogue: 2,0:23:31.08,0:23:36.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they obviously aren't going to be able to infiltrate Jackson no matter how hard they try.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:36.78,0:23:39.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're a small group and they aren't going to be able to do it.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:39.15,0:23:41.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,So he thinks that they should just turn back.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:41.52,0:23:45.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Especially since Mel is now pregnant, they need to return to take care of her.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:45.76,0:23:48.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again remember this plot point,
Dialogue: 2,0:23:48.66,0:23:56.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Owen, the dude, wants to turn back to make sure that he can take care of the woman that he impregnated.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:56.34,0:23:59.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems like a weird, random thing to say.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:59.64,0:24:03.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,But this is something that's going to be repeated later in the story,
Dialogue: 2,0:24:03.06,0:24:08.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Ellie is going to be making the same decision that Abby makes in this moment, a stupid one.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:08.99,0:24:12.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog will do this a lot throughout the course of the main story
Dialogue: 2,0:24:12.68,0:24:17.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they will have Abby do something and then change it with a fresh coat of paint
Dialogue: 2,0:24:17.18,0:24:20.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,and have Ellie do the same exact thing.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:20.20,0:24:24.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,But you can't help feel as though Ellie is more justified in her actions,
Dialogue: 2,0:24:24.84,0:24:28.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,while Abby is just a bad villainess character.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:28.23,0:24:30.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,This game is all about perspectives
Dialogue: 2,0:24:30.30,0:24:36.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this flip flopping that they do constantly is an important piece of that narrative mechanism.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:36.00,0:24:38.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I'll be obviously doesn't want to turn back.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:38.37,0:24:44.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,They've traveled, presumably for days, weeks and even months to get to where they are now
Dialogue: 2,0:24:44.06,0:24:48.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,and simply to turn around upon seeing the city of Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:48.66,0:24:50.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem like it's a good option.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:50.40,0:24:53.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Owen says that they should return back to the mansion they're staying at.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:53.64,0:24:56.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Abby doesn't like their recommendation,
Dialogue: 2,0:24:56.70,0:25:02.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she starts to become enraged, and she pushes on herself towards Jackson,
Dialogue: 2,0:25:02.34,0:25:06.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,trying to find a patrol that was traveling that Owen spotted
Dialogue: 2,0:25:06.65,0:25:09.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order to get them to tell her where their target is,
Dialogue: 2,0:25:09.75,0:25:14.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that she can finish the job herself before returning back to wherever they came from.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:14.41,0:25:17.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,Controlling Abby, you push forward into an impending storm.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:17.73,0:25:22.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,You fight some zombies and you eventually find some tracks from one of the patrols.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:22.32,0:25:29.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,These patrols are the same ones that characters such as Ellie, Dina, Jesse, Joel and Tommy are all on,
Dialogue: 2,0:25:29.43,0:25:36.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this is the first of a plethora of coincidences in the early hours of the game that set up its narrative,
Dialogue: 2,0:25:36.18,0:25:39.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,the coincidence that Abby happened to be driven into a rage
Dialogue: 2,0:25:39.53,0:25:42.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,at the same time that Joel and everyone else happens to be out on patrol.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:42.99,0:25:44.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's going to happen a lot.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:44.55,0:25:47.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel is an old man as his Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,0:25:47.22,0:25:52.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,at the very least older than all the youngsters that they have out on the patrols with them.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:52.02,0:25:57.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fact that Joel is still going on patrols is, in my opinion, a bit of a stretch.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:57.48,0:25:59.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,It would be stupid for him to go on patrols,
Dialogue: 2,0:25:59.40,0:26:02.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially because he has a leadership position within the city.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:02.73,0:26:06.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,His super fancy house, I think, serves as proof positive of that,
Dialogue: 2,0:26:06.96,0:26:11.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that Tommy, his brother, who was also going out on patrols with him,
Dialogue: 2,0:26:11.61,0:26:14.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,has a leadership position within the city.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:14.85,0:26:17.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,In many ways, Tommy runs the city along with his wife.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:17.85,0:26:19.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,So to me, it just seems like a bit of a stretch
Dialogue: 2,0:26:19.76,0:26:23.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Tommy and Joel would be going out on patrols at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:23.22,0:26:28.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I understand that perhaps Joel or Tommy just want to get out and get their hands dirty.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:28.92,0:26:33.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,They don't want to feel old, they don't want to feel as though they can't contribute,
Dialogue: 2,0:26:33.27,0:26:35.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,so they want to go out and do things themselves.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:35.25,0:26:38.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,I understand that perhaps that's justifiable.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:38.52,0:26:42.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I can't help feel as though Joel and Tommy being out on patrols
Dialogue: 2,0:26:42.16,0:26:46.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,the same patrol routes that Ellie Dina and Jesse are taking
Dialogue: 2,0:26:46.65,0:26:48.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,was purely designed,
Dialogue: 2,0:26:48.49,0:26:50.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,and established that way to make sure
Dialogue: 2,0:26:50.98,0:26:57.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Abby would be able to encounter Joel and Tommy while she randomly ran through the forest.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:57.60,0:27:01.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this is the reason that I don't like narrative coincidences.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:01.32,0:27:03.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Often it's just to give a way
Dialogue: 2,0:27:03.21,0:27:09.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,that the writers are trying to force characters into normally unjustifiable situations.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:09.27,0:27:11.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's not always a bad thing.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:11.58,0:27:16.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, in some cases, I think these coincidences can lead to some really interesting sequences.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:16.80,0:27:19.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, look at that scene from Breaking Bad.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:19.29,0:27:23.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Where Jane's father runs into Walt at a bar.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:23.25,0:27:27.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,They share a short conversation about fatherhood, about kids,
Dialogue: 2,0:27:27.90,0:27:33.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they don't realize that they're talking about two characters, in this case, Jesse and Jane,
Dialogue: 2,0:27:33.87,0:27:39.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,who are inextricably tied and who are about to go on a roller coaster together.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:39.40,0:27:44.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,For those of you who have seen the show and know what happens right after this meeting,
Dialogue: 2,0:27:44.01,0:27:48.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,you are going to probably think roller coaster is a bit of an understatement.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:48.12,0:27:50.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,But… I didn't want to spoil it, so…
Dialogue: 2,0:27:50.76,0:27:53.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,The point is, go watch Breaking Bad, it's awesome.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:53.01,0:27:57.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,The other point is that narrative coincidences can be fine.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:57.24,0:28:02.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, coincidences do happen in real life all the time.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:02.46,0:28:08.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,The problem comes when they are used to make characters do things they wouldn't otherwise be doing
Dialogue: 2,0:28:08.05,0:28:11.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order to fulfill some sort of plot point.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:11.34,0:28:15.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's the same reason I hate psychics or prophecies in stories
Dialogue: 2,0:28:15.56,0:28:17.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,because I think that they're just lazy.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:17.67,0:28:20.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,The writers know that they want a character to go and do something,
Dialogue: 2,0:28:20.94,0:28:25.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,so they write some sort of prophecy to explain how it's going to happen,
Dialogue: 2,0:28:25.53,0:28:29.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then they make sure that they have characters that fit around that prophecy.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:29.13,0:28:30.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if it's a little messy,
Dialogue: 2,0:28:30.24,0:28:36.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,or if it doesn't seem to be totally justified narratively or in terms of the characters, motivations,
Dialogue: 2,0:28:36.06,0:28:40.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,they simply explain it by way of while he or she was fulfilling the prophecy.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:40.41,0:28:41.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,It had to happen.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:41.61,0:28:44.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,It must have happened because the prophecy stated.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:44.73,0:28:46.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just lazy.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:46.20,0:28:50.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while I feel as though many of the instances of coincidences in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,0:28:50.79,0:28:55.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,are not justifiable and are a grievous offences,
Dialogue: 2,0:28:55.53,0:29:00.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think that other instances are more justifiable and could be explained.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:00.33,0:29:04.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,But eventually they become so many that stack up on top of each other.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:04.95,0:29:09.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,It just seems as though Naughty Dog need Joel to run into Abby,
Dialogue: 2,0:29:09.21,0:29:13.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this was the fastest, cleanest way that they could figure out how to do that.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:13.17,0:29:17.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,In a previous episode of NitGrit, a show that I do here on Youtube,
Dialogue: 2,0:29:17.13,0:29:21.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,I discussed narrative coincidences in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,0:29:21.60,0:29:27.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I couldn't help but notice that they were all front loaded in the opening hour or two of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:27.75,0:29:32.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,I threw out a potential intro that they could have swapped where, for instance,
Dialogue: 2,0:29:32.13,0:29:35.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby, Owen and perhaps a few other members of her crew
Dialogue: 2,0:29:35.46,0:29:39.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,infiltrated Jackson working with the people being welcomed in
Dialogue: 2,0:29:39.88,0:29:44.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,and eventually earning the trust of Joel and Tommy, and Ellie
Dialogue: 2,0:29:44.92,0:29:49.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,until eventually they turned on everybody, killed Joel and escape in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 2,0:29:49.53,0:29:53.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,while the game then carries out just like it would have otherwise,
Dialogue: 2,0:29:53.19,0:29:58.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,it could have been really interesting because Abby and Ellie could have even formed a friendship,
Dialogue: 2,0:29:58.23,0:30:02.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,or at least some sort of sympathetic position towards each other,
Dialogue: 2,0:30:02.61,0:30:05.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,which would have made the betrayal all the worse.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:05.07,0:30:08.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, as of right now, Tommy and Joel are very welcoming to this group.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:08.76,0:30:12.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,They even invite them back to Jackson to restock on supplies before leaving
Dialogue: 2,0:30:12.88,0:30:16.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,right before you know the thing happens.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:16.98,0:30:19.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we know that Tommy and Joel are welcoming.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:19.35,0:30:22.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,They would have brought this group in, at least for a little bit.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:22.17,0:30:23.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Perhaps if they came in,
Dialogue: 2,0:30:23.70,0:30:29.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,they pretended to be wandering survivors simply in need of assistance in a new fresh start.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:29.94,0:30:33.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,Perhaps then they go when they work at Jackson for a few weeks,
Dialogue: 2,0:30:33.42,0:30:38.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or maybe even just a couple of days before turning and killing Joel and escaping.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:38.85,0:30:43.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the very least, then you don't have to rely on a bunch of coincidences.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:43.02,0:30:47.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I do understand that it might have been bad for pacing
Dialogue: 2,0:30:47.35,0:30:52.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,and especially considering the leaks that happened towards the game's release.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:52.08,0:30:54.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems as though is probably for the best.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:54.27,0:30:56.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,because once the game was spoiled,
Dialogue: 2,0:30:56.10,0:30:58.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,we all knew that Abby was going to kill Joel
Dialogue: 2,0:30:58.91,0:31:02.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that would have completely negated the opening sequence
Dialogue: 2,0:31:02.64,0:31:08.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,where Abby and Ellie are starting to bond, or perhaps at least tolerating each other.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:08.67,0:31:11.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've heard from various people on Twitter and through Email
Dialogue: 2,0:31:11.79,0:31:15.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Naughty Dog was actually considering this as an opening,
Dialogue: 2,0:31:15.12,0:31:18.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is funny because I just let it roll off my dome,
Dialogue: 2,0:31:18.60,0:31:20.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,I wasn't actually thinking that hard.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:20.34,0:31:24.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,But apparently this was a seriously considered intro sequence
Dialogue: 2,0:31:24.12,0:31:28.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,instead of what we got in the end product of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,0:31:28.02,0:31:35.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,But they decided to go in this current direction because the other version ran into a lot of pacing issues.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:35.25,0:31:37.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,In other words, you likely would have needed to spend
Dialogue: 2,0:31:37.75,0:31:42.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,the first five or six hours of the game in Jackson doing menial chores
Dialogue: 2,0:31:42.34,0:31:46.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,while getting to know Abby and her crew before being betrayed,
Dialogue: 2,0:31:46.35,0:31:50.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,it would have completely changed the structure of the rest of the game,
Dialogue: 2,0:31:50.25,0:31:53.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,so Naughty Dog just decided to expedite the process,
Dialogue: 2,0:31:53.49,0:31:59.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,have Abby get to Joel within the first two hours of the game and get the revenge plot moving.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:59.61,0:32:00.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think that's fair.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:00.75,0:32:06.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,I just think it's a little sloppy, considering how many coincidences they rely on to make it happen.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:06.42,0:32:10.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,After Abby finds the tracks in the snow, leading to one of the patrols,
Dialogue: 2,0:32:10.26,0:32:13.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,we swap back to Ellie, whose on patrol with Dina.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:13.65,0:32:19.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,You ride your horses through a beautifully realized landscape, walking on ice in a river.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:19.26,0:32:20.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's absolutely beautiful.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:20.82,0:32:26.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean again, how Naughty Dog achieves these graphical features, I don't know.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:26.31,0:32:29.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,It really makes it look like every other development studio isn't even trying.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:29.91,0:32:33.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of character building in this sequence as you go on your patrol.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:33.75,0:32:35.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's some light flirting,
Dialogue: 2,0:32:35.36,0:32:38.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,clearly, Dina likes Ellie and Ellie likes Dina.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:38.82,0:32:41.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the tension starts to rise here.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:41.06,0:32:45.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again there's a lot of dread, things are going too well,
Dialogue: 2,0:32:45.45,0:32:51.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the world of {\i1}TLOU{\i0}, as we know, is very cutthroat, sometimes literally.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:51.19,0:32:56.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fact that everybody's happy that they are so carefree that they're even flirting with each other.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:56.58,0:33:01.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's unsettling, because we know that something bad has to happen soon.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:01.14,0:33:05.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,But you continue exploring, you go to an outpost to explore some abandoned houses.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:05.91,0:33:06.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,And at one point,
Dialogue: 2,0:33:06.96,0:33:13.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie even says that she's going to be inviting Joel over for a movie later that night.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:13.02,0:33:17.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,This will be VERY important at the end of the game,
Dialogue: 2,0:33:17.76,0:33:19.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,so make sure you remember this.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:19.56,0:33:26.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie on this day was planning on having Joel over for a movie that night.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:26.07,0:33:27.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems like a small point,
Dialogue: 2,0:33:27.60,0:33:33.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially considering that Ellie and Joel have this deep connection with each other.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:33.09,0:33:37.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,She lives right behind him, even still in the grandmother's suite,
Dialogue: 2,0:33:37.20,0:33:40.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it makes sense that perhaps they would try to fill an empty time,
Dialogue: 2,0:33:40.74,0:33:42.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,watching movies and spending time together.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:42.60,0:33:46.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,But again, at the end of the game, we're going to find out a lot more.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:46.29,0:33:51.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this very statement by Ellie something that happens as an optional moment
Dialogue: 2,0:33:51.32,0:33:53.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,while you're exploring an abandoned house.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:54.16,0:33:56.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is going to be very important.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:56.10,0:33:59.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Dina, come up on a supermarket that's infested.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:59.07,0:34:03.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,You cleared out, gives you the chance to explore some stealth options and combat,
Dialogue: 2,0:34:03.84,0:34:07.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's a good thing that this is a really well done portion of the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:07.44,0:34:10.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because this stealth and the crafting that goes along with it
Dialogue: 2,0:34:10.76,0:34:13.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,is going to be the bread and butter of the game,
Dialogue: 2,0:34:13.71,0:34:16.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially if you're playing on higher difficulties,
Dialogue: 2,0:34:16.05,0:34:20.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're going to need to get acclimated to these mechanics as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:20.55,0:34:23.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,You are also given a quick introduction to Clickers as well,
Dialogue: 2,0:34:23.61,0:34:27.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,and these guys work almost identically to how they did in the first game.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:27.39,0:34:31.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't really feel the need to explain a lot as to how these sequences work,
Dialogue: 2,0:34:31.86,0:34:36.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,because if you've played the first game, you're going to know how this goes.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:36.00,0:34:39.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's going to be a hot minute before we're thrown anything that's markedly different.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:39.57,0:34:41.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,I will say that in the first game,
Dialogue: 2,0:34:41.25,0:34:42.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,it always bugging me that
Dialogue: 2,0:34:42.20,0:34:45.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Clickers are obviously able to navigate their environments
Dialogue: 2,0:34:45.91,0:34:51.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,by use of clicking sounds that use echolocation to map out their environment.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:51.27,0:34:55.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, they never were able to hear characters talking to each other
Dialogue: 2,0:34:55.40,0:34:59.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,or you reloading your weapon or moving your backpack on and off.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:59.88,0:35:06.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,That is mostly true again in this game, except only on the lower levels.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:06.36,0:35:11.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,In my testing, I actually found that on new game plus on Survivor difficulty,
Dialogue: 2,0:35:11.43,0:35:13.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,the Clickers can actually hear this as well.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:13.98,0:35:18.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you open your backpack to swap weapons, they'll notice and they'll come running.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:18.96,0:35:22.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was a game changer in terms of immersion.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:22.89,0:35:28.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seriously, I've never played a game where I was so attentive to everything that I was doing,
Dialogue: 2,0:35:28.53,0:35:31.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,that I was scared to even open up the inventory,
Dialogue: 2,0:35:31.74,0:35:37.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,because I knew that it was going to create a small amount of sound that could attract Clickers,
Dialogue: 2,0:35:37.56,0:35:40.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,which could mean that I die and have to reload.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:40.36,0:35:43.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Granted to some people, I'm sure that sounds absolutely terrible,
Dialogue: 2,0:35:43.44,0:35:46.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why there are difficulty settings to begin with.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:46.08,0:35:49.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if you want to be totally immersed in this game,
Dialogue: 2,0:35:49.47,0:35:52.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,I recommend you play it on the hardest possible difficulty.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:52.92,0:35:54.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,It really does change everything.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:54.90,0:35:57.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another thing to note in this supermarket sequences that
Dialogue: 2,0:35:57.68,0:36:01.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie is wearing a mask when she encounters spores now.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:01.32,0:36:02.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you played the first game,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:02.43,0:36:07.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,this is going to be kind of weird because obviously Ellie is immune to the virus,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:07.41,0:36:10.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,or so we thought, why does she need to wear a mask?
Dialogue: 2,0:36:10.41,0:36:12.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the trailers we saw before the game's launch,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:12.66,0:36:16.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,a lot of people thought that this would mean that Ellie was no longer immune,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:16.11,0:36:20.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,or perhaps she was not as immune as she once was,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:20.49,0:36:24.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,so perhaps if she inhaled spores, that would make her very very sick,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:24.06,0:36:25.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,but she would eventually pull through it.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:25.74,0:36:28.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, the explanation is far simpler.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:28.02,0:36:33.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel and Ellie obviously know that Ellie is immune, but nobody else can know that.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:33.69,0:36:35.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,If people were to find out that Ellie's immune,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:35.82,0:36:39.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,the same crap with the Fireflies would happen all over again.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:39.72,0:36:43.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now this seems to be much more Joel's wish than it is Ellie's,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:43.71,0:36:48.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,after all, Ellie was totally prepared and fine with giving her life
Dialogue: 2,0:36:48.37,0:36:51.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,to save humanity in the form of a vaccine,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:51.09,0:36:53.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this would of course make sense because Joel wanted to make sure
Dialogue: 2,0:36:53.84,0:36:58.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,nobody else would come to Ellie to try and capitalize on her gift,
Dialogue: 2,0:36:58.53,0:37:01.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,because if they did, it would mean that he would lose her.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:01.29,0:37:04.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the fact that Ellie is still using the mask, even though she doesn't need to,
Dialogue: 2,0:37:04.98,0:37:08.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think, serves as proof positive that she still cares about what he thinks,
Dialogue: 2,0:37:08.79,0:37:11.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she's yet to fully separate and become her own person.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:11.64,0:37:16.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,But this isn't something that's explained or really justified at this point in the game,
Dialogue: 2,0:37:16.14,0:37:22.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,but we will see an actual conversation between Ellie and Joel later on that explains all of this.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:22.32,0:37:24.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,If I throw a bunch of zombies and Clickers
Dialogue: 2,0:37:24.70,0:37:27.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,and eventually find your way up to the top of the supermarket,
Dialogue: 2,0:37:27.33,0:37:29.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,where you jumped down out to the front,
Dialogue: 2,0:37:29.58,0:37:35.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Dina's entire goal throughout exploring this supermarket was to clear it of infected,
Dialogue: 2,0:37:35.16,0:37:36.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they've done just that.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:36.33,0:37:40.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Honestly, it's not a bad way of forcing the player to kill zombies
Dialogue: 2,0:37:40.12,0:37:44.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order to get experience with the combat system and become more comfortable with it.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:44.01,0:37:48.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,A lot of people are going to simply try to stealth around them in most instances,
Dialogue: 2,0:37:48.33,0:37:51.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially later in the game, when resources become very scarce.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:51.45,0:37:58.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,but if the characters mission is to wipe out all infected in an area to protect Jackson, the city,
Dialogue: 2,0:37:58.23,0:38:01.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,you all of a sudden don't have to worry about players doing that
Dialogue: 2,0:38:01.04,0:38:05.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they're going to be justified narratively in killing absolutely everything.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:05.46,0:38:07.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, they can't leave the area
Dialogue: 2,0:38:07.23,0:38:11.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,unless they've completely wiped all of the infected within that area.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:11.07,0:38:15.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once you get out of the supermarket, the blizzard starts to come in full force.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:15.93,0:38:21.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Ellie and Dina race through the snow, and end up at a library that Dina knew about.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:21.66,0:38:24.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's the previous abode of somebody named Eugene,
Dialogue: 2,0:38:24.36,0:38:28.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,who, by my calculations, using the log book in the first outpost,
Dialogue: 2,0:38:28.50,0:38:34.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,likely died of a stroke laid in the previous year just a few months before this game starts.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:34.92,0:38:38.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, we know about him is that he was a firefly who served with Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,0:38:38.31,0:38:42.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,and he was also an electronics geek who was a total hippy.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:42.45,0:38:44.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,In other words, he loved weed.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:44.42,0:38:46.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,After being introduced to the workbench,
Dialogue: 2,0:38:46.32,0:38:52.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,Which has to be the most awesome and kick ass weapon customization system
Dialogue: 2,0:38:52.63,0:38:54.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,I have ever seen in a game,
Dialogue: 2,0:38:54.50,0:38:58.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,you went down to the basement where you find Eugene's true passion.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:58.68,0:39:00.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, when I first saw all of this,
Dialogue: 2,0:39:00.15,0:39:07.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,I had to ask the question: Was he actually like selling this stuff? Was he trading it?
Dialogue: 2,0:39:07.17,0:39:09.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know, maybe there's a notes that I missed,
Dialogue: 2,0:39:09.21,0:39:12.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,that explained what he was doing with all of this pot.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:12.78,0:39:17.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know, let me know if there is something there probably is, and I just didn't find it.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:17.40,0:39:22.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it seems as though it's a huge potential opportunity for Jackson in terms of trade,
Dialogue: 2,0:39:22.56,0:39:27.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,if they had a whole of this marijuana to offer, to transients coming in and out,
Dialogue: 2,0:39:27.36,0:39:32.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean it would be pretty funny if Jackson, this thriving city in the apocalypse,
Dialogue: 2,0:39:32.00,0:39:36.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,if their entire economy was based off of selling weed.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:36.42,0:39:39.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it would be hilarious and kind of cool
Dialogue: 2,0:39:39.76,0:39:44.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,that in this world, this one thing this plant has brought everybody together.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:44.58,0:39:46.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, yeah, I live in Colorado.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:46.35,0:39:50.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's why I'm partial to that argument.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:50.13,0:39:53.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean I don't smoke and I don't… I don't smoke.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:53.80,0:39:58.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,But, still, like you live in Colorado, everyone talks about pot, and this is what you do.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:58.77,0:40:00.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,What was I talking about? Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 2,0:40:00.66,0:40:02.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina and Ellie smoke a blunt.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:02.31,0:40:07.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,They shared some high school musical style discussion about their kiss from the night before.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:07.71,0:40:10.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then they share another one and then a few other ones,
Dialogue: 2,0:40:10.80,0:40:16.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,and eventually their overcome, and they begin making out as we cut to Abby, once again.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:16.62,0:40:18.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's running from all sorts of hordes.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:18.51,0:40:21.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's making a lot of noise, and they are definitely hearing it.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:21.75,0:40:26.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,This increases the tension a lot after the calm of the previous scene.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:26.04,0:40:28.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this type of pacing is going to happen often.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:28.29,0:40:29.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I love it.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:29.70,0:40:31.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a very common Naughty Dog tactic.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:31.50,0:40:32.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,They work you up,
Dialogue: 2,0:40:32.44,0:40:36.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then they contrast it with something that's very calm that lowers your heart rate
Dialogue: 2,0:40:36.05,0:40:41.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,only to whack you over the head again and then luring you back into a sense of calm.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:41.37,0:40:44.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,The best example would be in the opening of the original game.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:44.52,0:40:46.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everything's calm and relaxed,
Dialogue: 2,0:40:46.59,0:40:50.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then the world starts to fall apart and everything's terrible and then your daughter dies,
Dialogue: 2,0:40:50.88,0:40:55.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then you cut forward to Joel sleeping on a mattress twenty years later
Dialogue: 2,0:40:55.75,0:41:00.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,and having a very calm, comparatively conversation with Tess
Dialogue: 2,0:41:00.97,0:41:02.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,and prepare your butts
Dialogue: 2,0:41:02.00,0:41:06.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,because this is going to happen on a regular basis throughout all of the sequel.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:06.18,0:41:08.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,And thankfully, the predictability of this
Dialogue: 2,0:41:08.40,0:41:11.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,doesn't actually negatively affect the efficacy of this mechanism.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:11.52,0:41:12.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,It still works pretty well.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:12.70,0:41:18.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now as you run as Abby through all of these hordes, you eventually reach a chain link fence.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:18.28,0:41:21.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,You squeeze through it and a bunch of zombies grab onto you,
Dialogue: 2,0:41:21.81,0:41:28.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,start ripping your hat off and doing all sorts of gross stuff, and then one breaks through,
Dialogue: 2,0:41:28.23,0:41:29.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this happens.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:46.44,0:41:48.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now they haven't been introduced yet.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:48.00,0:41:51.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,but as of right now, Abby's just glad to be alive.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:51.54,0:41:52.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,As far as she knows,
Dialogue: 2,0:41:52.92,0:41:55.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel is just some random guy, as is Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,0:41:55.80,0:41:59.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they just happened to be in the right place at the right time to save her.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:59.71,0:42:01.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, a coincidence.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:01.32,0:42:04.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,This one's a little harder to justify and explained.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:04.75,0:42:08.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because they have no reason to be out at this dead end area
Dialogue: 2,0:42:08.34,0:42:10.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,of a building they have likely been in before.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:10.44,0:42:13.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,All of you escaped together to a ski lodge at the top of the mountain.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:13.68,0:42:14.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,You up on some horses,
Dialogue: 2,0:42:14.82,0:42:18.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,and after a brief introduction wherein Abby learns who she's with,
Dialogue: 2,0:42:18.96,0:42:21.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,she recommends that they weighed out the storm in a mansion
Dialogue: 2,0:42:21.50,0:42:23.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,that she and her friends have been staying in.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:23.55,0:42:26.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel and Tommy agree to go without any significant hesitance
Dialogue: 2,0:42:26.98,0:42:29.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,beyond the initial belief that they could survive in the lodge.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:30.05,0:42:32.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once again, it's another coincidence.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:32.55,0:42:34.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel and Tommy, aren't this naive,
Dialogue: 2,0:42:34.49,0:42:39.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,or at the very least they shouldn't be, even when pushed in these extreme conditions.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:39.27,0:42:42.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,What I mean is, I understand that there's a blizzard raging,
Dialogue: 2,0:42:42.27,0:42:47.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I understand that would push them into choices that they wouldn't otherwise make,
Dialogue: 2,0:42:47.49,0:42:49.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,should the weather be fine and dandy.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:49.35,0:42:53.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Joel and Tommy aren't stupid, and they know not to trust strangers,
Dialogue: 2,0:42:53.49,0:42:58.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,even a stranger that looks as innocent as a… hulked out heroin.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:58.44,0:43:03.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,And they definitely should know that they shouldn't trust a group of strangers
Dialogue: 2,0:43:03.51,0:43:06.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,that are living out of a mansion that's on their patrol route.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:06.93,0:43:09.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,She says they've been staying there for a few days
Dialogue: 2,0:43:09.20,0:43:14.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they have weapons, food and all sorts of things that could help Joel and Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:14.22,0:43:17.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,While it's nice that she's offering to help them in this way,
Dialogue: 2,0:43:17.55,0:43:23.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,it should also raise a lot of red flags that she's willing to help them first of all,
Dialogue: 2,0:43:23.22,0:43:30.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,and also that this giant group of people is present so close to Jackson without their knowledge.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:30.15,0:43:32.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless Joel and Tommy agree to go.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:32.36,0:43:36.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once you arrive at the cabin, Joel, Tommy, and Abby dismount and settle into the house.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:36.93,0:43:40.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby is clearly distressed, while Tommy and Joel are none the wiser.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:40.81,0:43:44.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, the dread is building.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:44.20,0:43:47.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Something is very wrong.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:47.16,0:43:52.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everyone moves into the nearby basement room, and Tommy and Joel introduce themselves.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:52.01,0:43:56.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, this might be construed as out of character
Dialogue: 2,0:43:56.08,0:43:58.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they would use their real names to a bunch of strangers.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:58.65,0:44:01.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in my opinion, it's not actually stretch
Dialogue: 2,0:44:01.29,0:44:06.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,because Tommy and Joel have no reason to believe that their first names could give them away,
Dialogue: 2,0:44:06.03,0:44:09.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,or that one of them is being hunted for that matter.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:09.18,0:44:12.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yes, they've all done a lot of really messed up stuff,
Dialogue: 2,0:44:12.18,0:44:17.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,but knowing somebody's first name and hunting them down across the country,
Dialogue: 2,0:44:17.40,0:44:19.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,that seems like a bit of a stretch.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:19.20,0:44:20.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,But here we are.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:20.39,0:44:24.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Point is I don't think that it's unrealistic that Joel and Tommy use their real names
Dialogue: 2,0:44:24.88,0:44:28.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,when introducing themselves to a group that seemingly is helping them out.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:28.71,0:44:32.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I have to say it's pretty impressive at how slow and steady
Dialogue: 2,0:44:32.52,0:44:38.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,the dread is building throughout this entire introductory sequence, the prologue of the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:38.55,0:44:39.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then at this very moment,
Dialogue: 2,0:44:39.87,0:44:47.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Joel says his name and everybody's faces turn from very friendly to cold and evil.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:47.91,0:44:50.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a moment that I'm not sure I'll ever forget
Dialogue: 2,0:44:50.41,0:44:54.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,the second Joel says his name, the room shifts.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:54.18,0:44:56.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,You could hear a pin drop.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:56.36,0:45:01.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Instead of being friendly, they all looked at him as though their hyenas looking at their next meal.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:01.53,0:45:07.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's important to note that this kindness that we feel before Joel introduces himself
Dialogue: 2,0:45:07.00,0:45:11.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,is very important and it will come up again later, I promise you.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:11.97,0:45:15.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Joel picks up on this shift, and this plays out.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:45.63,0:47:48.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,We cut back to Ellie, closing in on the cabin.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:48.06,0:47:52.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now right before Joel and Tommy pushed up to the cabin with Abby,
Dialogue: 2,0:47:52.29,0:48:01.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,We saw Jesse come across Ellie and Dina in the basement of Eugene's library in a compromised position.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:01.26,0:48:06.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,He tells them that Joel and Tommy are missing and nobody has seen them since the storm came in.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:06.48,0:48:10.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie becomes panicked and races off to help find them.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:10.35,0:48:13.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's important to note also that Ellie stressed
Dialogue: 2,0:48:13.41,0:48:17.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they should all split up to try and cover as much ground as possible.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:17.16,0:48:19.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Some people have said that this itself is a coincidence
Dialogue: 2,0:48:19.72,0:48:22.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,or a bit of a stretch that they wouldn't actually do this.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:22.37,0:48:23.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,But again, think about it.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:23.94,0:48:26.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,From her perspective, I don't think it's a stretch.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:26.73,0:48:28.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because as far as Ellie is concerned,
Dialogue: 2,0:48:28.56,0:48:33.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's very possible that Joel and Tommy simply had to bunker down somewhere because of the blizzard
Dialogue: 2,0:48:33.80,0:48:36.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,and were caught there by surprise.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:36.27,0:48:42.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not to say that she expected Joel to be hunted by some random chick from Seattle.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:42.15,0:48:46.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless everybody breaks off looking for Joel and Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:46.05,0:48:50.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,After Abby starts her attack on Joel, we cut to Ellie, closing in on the cabin,
Dialogue: 2,0:48:50.37,0:48:54.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,they give a bit of a fake out here by dropping some ammo right as you enter the cabin,
Dialogue: 2,0:48:54.54,0:48:56.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,which makes the player think that you're about to fight.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:56.70,0:48:58.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,I actually really like it.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:58.08,0:49:00.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,When games do this, do this little fake out.
Dialogue: 2,0:49:00.09,0:49:01.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you're prepped for a fight,
Dialogue: 2,0:49:01.14,0:49:04.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then it's taken away from you, but I know that's just me.
Dialogue: 2,0:49:04.23,0:49:08.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course this is in the case because the second that we enter the basement, this happens.
Dialogue: 2,0:51:15.15,0:51:19.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are some heated discussion between the members of Abby's party as to what to do with Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,0:51:19.44,0:51:22.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's all very muffled, and you can't understand any of it,
Dialogue: 2,0:51:22.14,0:51:24.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,though we will get to see this from another perspective later.
Dialogue: 2,0:51:24.90,0:51:26.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,Eventually they just knocked her out.
Dialogue: 2,0:51:26.73,0:51:30.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Ellie wakes up after some time to Dina and Jesse rescuing them.
Dialogue: 2,0:51:30.94,0:51:35.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point is not clear if Tommy survived, but it's clear that Joel did not.
Dialogue: 2,0:51:45.39,0:51:51.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,You know what? This is as good a time as any to address the elephant in the room dead on the floor.
Dialogue: 2,0:51:51.12,0:51:52.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,I had the game spoiled for me,
Dialogue: 2,0:51:52.41,0:51:55.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,so I knew that Joel was going to die at some point.
Dialogue: 2,0:51:55.56,0:51:56.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,And to be honest,
Dialogue: 2,0:51:56.37,0:52:01.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,many of us had a feeling as though Joel was going to die at some point in the game years ago
Dialogue: 2,0:52:01.83,0:52:03.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it only made sense.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:03.72,0:52:08.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,One of the stereotypes of a sequel is that they're going to kill off one of the major characters
Dialogue: 2,0:52:08.44,0:52:11.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,from the first iteration of whatever is in question,
Dialogue: 2,0:52:11.91,0:52:15.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,whether it's a movie and novel, a podcast or a video game,
Dialogue: 2,0:52:15.52,0:52:18.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,time and time again, we've seen this trope played out.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:18.59,0:52:22.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's become a trope because this actually works pretty well.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:22.17,0:52:27.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,You grow the character and the audience falls in love with them over the course of the first story.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:27.00,0:52:30.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then, with this foundation laid you pull the rug out from everybody
Dialogue: 2,0:52:30.86,0:52:34.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,and smack them over the head with a two by four of emotion.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:34.26,0:52:38.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or maybe in this case, a golf club of emotion.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:38.46,0:52:40.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's too soon, I don't care, moving on.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:40.62,0:52:46.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even with this presumption, having been established by many people before this game was launched,
Dialogue: 2,0:52:46.23,0:52:50.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog seems to have actively tried to dissuade fans from this presupposition
Dialogue: 2,0:52:50.72,0:52:52.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,by way of their pre launch trailers.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:52.98,0:52:59.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now this actually got a lot of people pretty upset when they played through the entirety of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}.
Dialogue: 2,0:52:59.61,0:53:02.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are multiple events that were shown in the trailers
Dialogue: 2,0:53:02.72,0:53:06.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,that aren't actually indicative of what the game has to offer.
Dialogue: 2,0:53:06.45,0:53:08.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,The clearest example would be this one,
Dialogue: 2,0:53:08.86,0:53:12.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,where Ellie is fighting through a bunch of WLF,
Dialogue: 2,0:53:12.00,0:53:15.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then has a hand put over her mouth,
Dialogue: 2,0:53:15.00,0:53:18.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,and when she turns round, she sees that it's Joel,
Dialogue: 2,0:53:18.06,0:53:21.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,telling her that he's not going to let her do this by herself.
Dialogue: 2,0:53:21.39,0:53:24.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I'm not going to respond in the same way that a lot of people on Twitter responded
Dialogue: 2,0:53:24.59,0:53:27.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they demanded their money back to the false advertising.
Dialogue: 2,0:53:27.42,0:53:28.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's fair,
Dialogue: 2,0:53:28.86,0:53:32.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially because you paid sixty dollars and have gotten a lot of game play out of it before.
Dialogue: 2,0:53:32.99,0:53:36.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,You know, I don't even need to explain my reasoning, I just think that's stupid.
Dialogue: 2,0:53:36.66,0:53:39.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,What I will say, however, was that this was very confusing,
Dialogue: 2,0:53:39.42,0:53:42.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least for me, the first time I play through the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:53:42.09,0:53:44.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Having watched all of the trailers multiple times,
Dialogue: 2,0:53:44.85,0:53:50.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,I knew that Joel made an appearance later on in the game because Ellie responds to him.
Dialogue: 2,0:53:50.43,0:53:53.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that never happens in the actual game.
Dialogue: 2,0:53:53.70,0:53:57.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I kept asking myself whether or not there was going to be some sort of dream sequence
Dialogue: 2,0:53:57.69,0:54:00.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,where she plays back through the same level again.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:00.33,0:54:05.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,But this time Joel is at the end of the line instead, and then that scene plays out.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:05.13,0:54:08.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, I don't have to tell you that never happens.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:08.25,0:54:11.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was simply a way to divert the attention from the fans
Dialogue: 2,0:54:11.86,0:54:14.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,away from what was actually going to happen.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:14.16,0:54:16.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Naughty Dog does have a history of doing this type of thing,
Dialogue: 2,0:54:16.68,0:54:18.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is part of the reason I can't fault them completely,
Dialogue: 2,0:54:18.99,0:54:20.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,because usually it's for a good reason.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:20.64,0:54:23.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,The most obvious example would be with the original {\i1}TLOU{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,0:54:23.58,0:54:27.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,when they said that you would only be playing as Joel throughout the entirety of the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:27.45,0:54:29.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, this isn't true.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:29.91,0:54:32.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it made it so when you actually get your hands on Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,0:54:32.97,0:54:36.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,that sounded weird when I said it out loud,
Dialogue: 2,0:54:36.03,0:54:38.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,it made it, so when you started playing as Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,0:54:38.85,0:54:45.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,the entire sequence was much more surreal because you didn't expect at all to have this opportunity.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:45.39,0:54:47.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another example would be with this very game,
Dialogue: 2,0:54:47.49,0:54:53.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\i1}TLOU2{\i0} when they said that you would only be playing as Ellie throughout the entirety of the campaign,
Dialogue: 2,0:54:53.28,0:54:55.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,something which was obviously not true.
Dialogue: 2,0:54:55.47,0:55:00.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,The problem with these sort of white lies to better the game play experience for the player
Dialogue: 2,0:55:00.85,0:55:04.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,is that they only work if people don't know any better.
Dialogue: 2,0:55:04.48,0:55:06.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,And with the original game, as far as I am aware,
Dialogue: 2,0:55:06.99,0:55:11.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,most people believed that you would only play as Joel throughout the entirety of the game,
Dialogue: 2,0:55:11.37,0:55:15.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it made it so when they got their hands on the controller playing as Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,0:55:15.48,0:55:19.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was much more interesting because they didn't expect it at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:55:19.98,0:55:25.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,But with {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} and all of the leaks that followed, people saw this coming from a mile away,
Dialogue: 2,0:55:25.80,0:55:27.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it lost a lot of its punch.
Dialogue: 2,0:55:27.75,0:55:30.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've actually spent a lot of time thinking what this game would be like
Dialogue: 2,0:55:30.88,0:55:34.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,if I had no expectations and nothing spoiled for me.
Dialogue: 2,0:55:34.83,0:55:37.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think the experience would have been much different,
Dialogue: 2,0:55:37.23,0:55:40.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I'm not sure how that would have changed my perspective.
Dialogue: 2,0:55:40.38,0:55:43.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, if you happen to be one of the few lucky people
Dialogue: 2,0:55:43.96,0:55:48.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,who got to play the entire game without having anything spoiled for you,
Dialogue: 2,0:55:48.00,0:55:52.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,I want to hear your thoughts down in the comment section below or in a tweet.
Dialogue: 2,0:55:52.04,0:55:56.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sent it to me, I'm really interested in hearing what your perspective is on all of this.
Dialogue: 2,0:55:56.73,0:56:01.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,But as for Joel's death itself, I have no problem with it.
Dialogue: 2,0:56:01.44,0:56:04.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel's actions throughout the course of the first game were quite reckless
Dialogue: 2,0:56:04.83,0:56:09.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,and he screwed over a lot of people and killed a lot of people while he was at it.
Dialogue: 2,0:56:09.84,0:56:14.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've said before, and I'll say it again: I don't think Joel is a hero.
Dialogue: 2,0:56:14.82,0:56:19.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,If anything, he's an anti hero, if you look at his actions in a vacuum.
Dialogue: 2,0:56:19.38,0:56:25.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,You can always say that life and morality is much more complicated than looking at it purely in a vacuum,
Dialogue: 2,0:56:25.08,0:56:31.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I think it still stands to say that Joel is not a pillar of morality,
Dialogue: 2,0:56:31.80,0:56:35.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,to which we should all look and pray for guidance.
Dialogue: 2,0:56:35.70,0:56:42.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think rather, he's a damaged, broken, sad and a moral character
Dialogue: 2,0:56:42.55,0:56:48.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,who is looking to do what he needs to do, to survive and protect those he cares about.
Dialogue: 2,0:56:48.06,0:56:51.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's something that I think is in a way admirable in and of itself.
Dialogue: 2,0:56:51.51,0:56:56.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that that makes you a hero quote-unquote in the same way
Dialogue: 2,0:56:56.30,0:56:59.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,that you could compare a character such as Aloy
Dialogue: 2,0:56:59.37,0:57:04.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,who is actively trying to do the moral thing in any instance that she comes across.
Dialogue: 2,0:57:04.50,0:57:08.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, from a game play perspective, we got our game with Joel.
Dialogue: 2,0:57:08.96,0:57:13.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,We know him, we have experienced him and his perspectives.
Dialogue: 2,0:57:13.11,0:57:15.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it was time for something new,
Dialogue: 2,0:57:15.00,0:57:20.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and if we had played through the entire game as Joel or half and half between Joel and Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,0:57:20.10,0:57:22.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it would have lost a lot of its punch.
Dialogue: 2,0:57:22.47,0:57:27.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Joel's death didn't come as a surprise to me, or probably any one,
Dialogue: 2,0:57:27.00,0:57:29.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially once you walk through that door in the cabin.
Dialogue: 2,0:57:29.94,0:57:36.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,That being said, it's still pretty horrible having to watch him get his head crammed in with a golf club.
Dialogue: 2,0:57:36.00,0:57:39.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's pretty haunting, but that's by design.
Dialogue: 2,0:57:39.12,0:57:44.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog needed the player to be just as haunted by this event as Ellie is
Dialogue: 2,0:57:44.04,0:57:47.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,because then they feel emotionally equivalent,
Dialogue: 2,0:57:47.31,0:57:50.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially in their hatred towards Abby,
Dialogue: 2,0:57:50.04,0:57:54.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is one of the major elements that they need to establish early on.
Dialogue: 2,0:57:54.81,0:58:00.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,You, the player, need to hate this girl with every fiber of your being.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:00.03,0:58:03.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just like Ellie hates her with every fibre of her being.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:03.99,0:58:08.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that later, when they try to flip perspectives and flip the table on you,
Dialogue: 2,0:58:08.88,0:58:10.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,they can do that effectively.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:10.92,0:58:12.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you're apathetic towards Abby
Dialogue: 2,0:58:12.68,0:58:17.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then you go through the entirety of the game trying to pursue revenge,
Dialogue: 2,0:58:17.01,0:58:19.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're not going to be motivated at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:19.26,0:58:26.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's going to be pretty uninteresting because the entire premise of the game and the story is a moot point.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:26.01,0:58:32.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if you hate Abby, just as much as Ellie hates her and wants to see her die,
Dialogue: 2,0:58:32.37,0:58:35.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,you'll be motivated to get through the first half of the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:35.85,0:58:39.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then Naughty Dog has you set up for the final act.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:39.87,0:58:42.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, after this, we enter the end of the prologue.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:42.60,0:58:47.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are an hour into this video, and we are just getting out of the prologue.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:47.64,0:58:49.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Tommy discuss their next steps.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:49.74,0:58:53.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy talk to Maria, and she's not going to let him go or do anything,
Dialogue: 2,0:58:53.43,0:58:56.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,and he's not allowed to have any sort of spare men.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:56.55,0:58:58.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,He has to keep them all in Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,0:58:58.41,0:59:00.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,She thinks that they should just move on,
Dialogue: 2,0:59:00.18,0:59:03.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,except that what happened was terrible and go on with their lives.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:03.99,0:59:07.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,As usual, Maria seems to be the one voice of reason.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:07.08,0:59:10.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy and Ellie, however, are understandably upset.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:10.23,0:59:13.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy lost his brother in a terrible way,
Dialogue: 2,0:59:13.26,0:59:17.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Ellie also lost her "father figure" in a terrible way.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:17.76,0:59:20.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,They still aren't certain why this happened,
Dialogue: 2,0:59:20.22,0:59:25.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,or what Joel did that made them seek his death out so fervently.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:25.32,0:59:30.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy happened to see some patches on their coats that read "WLF".
Dialogue: 2,0:59:30.00,0:59:32.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,And because of his previous history with the Fireflies,
Dialogue: 2,0:59:32.79,0:59:35.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,he knows that that would be the Washington Liberation Front,
Dialogue: 2,0:59:35.91,0:59:38.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is a group that's in Washington.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:38.40,0:59:39.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Huh… Go figure.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:39.54,0:59:43.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's what allows Ellie to know where she needs to go next.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:43.59,0:59:47.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a long stretch that they would have returned to Seattle
Dialogue: 2,0:59:47.60,0:59:49.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that they would still be there and that they would be findable.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:49.89,0:59:54.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when you're motivated this strongly, you're willing to go and try anything.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:54.73,0:59:59.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the same way that Abby was so desperate to go and get revenge against Joel.
Dialogue: 2,0:59:59.93,1:00:04.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie now is motivated to go to her turf and get revenge against her.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:04.26,1:00:08.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Tommy wants to go to Seattle by himself, and Hunt Abby down and get revenge.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:08.82,1:00:11.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maria, of course, is not going to let him do that.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:11.31,1:00:15.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Tommy's main objective is to prevent Ellie from going,
Dialogue: 2,1:00:15.54,1:00:19.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,he promised Joel that he would take care of Ellie, no matter what.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:19.23,1:00:22.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,And in this case, he knows that if Ellie goes to Seattle,
Dialogue: 2,1:00:22.29,1:00:24.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,her chances of survival aren't very high.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:24.51,1:00:27.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,So he'd rather go take on those chances himself
Dialogue: 2,1:00:27.90,1:00:31.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,and spare Ellie while trying to get revenge for the sake of the both of them.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:31.77,1:00:33.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie demands that they either go together,
Dialogue: 2,1:00:33.69,1:00:36.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,or that Tommy allow Ellie to go with Dina
Dialogue: 2,1:00:36.56,1:00:41.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,and some other people with some troops from the camp to get revenge herself.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:41.13,1:00:46.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy, of course, rejects this idea and asks for and more time just a day or so
Dialogue: 2,1:00:46.36,1:00:48.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that he can try and work something out.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:48.50,1:00:50.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this case, he's just buying time.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:50.55,1:00:52.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's made up his mind as to what he's going to do.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:52.71,1:00:54.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,We then see Ellie in Joel's grave site.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:54.75,1:00:56.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a really touching moment,
Dialogue: 2,1:00:56.22,1:00:59.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it reaffirms that Joel is actually gone.
Dialogue: 2,1:00:59.82,1:01:01.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know about you guys.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:01.35,1:01:06.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I had this sort of surreal feeling when I played through this game the first time.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:06.02,1:01:09.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,I kept saying to myself: Joel can't actually be dead.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:09.16,1:01:14.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,For one because we saw that trailer, where Joel was featured later on in the game in Seattle.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:14.23,1:01:16.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,And for two because Joel is Joel,
Dialogue: 2,1:01:16.74,1:01:21.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,you can't just kill off Joel that suddenly, there has to be more to it.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:21.42,1:01:22.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,But there isn't.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:22.56,1:01:26.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's dead. This is his grave and it's sad.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:26.04,1:01:28.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie then visits Joel's house with Dina,
Dialogue: 2,1:01:28.73,1:01:32.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,picks up his watch from the first game, it's still broken.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:32.48,1:01:36.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,And also takes his revolver, which you'll be using throughout the rest of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:36.30,1:01:39.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's actually pretty cool that this is where she gets it.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:39.63,1:01:43.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,We do this though, only after exploring his house a little bit,
Dialogue: 2,1:01:43.17,1:01:46.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,and there's a lot of incredible detail here,
Dialogue: 2,1:01:46.95,1:01:49.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it really encapsulates Joel's character.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:49.77,1:01:54.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's very music heavy and organized his neat and tidy,
Dialogue: 2,1:01:54.66,1:01:58.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and his house is also painfully empty.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:58.02,1:01:59.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of big, empty rooms.
Dialogue: 2,1:01:59.97,1:02:01.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,And maybe I'm just reading too much into it,
Dialogue: 2,1:02:01.74,1:02:04.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I couldn't help but feel as though there was a lot of space
Dialogue: 2,1:02:04.55,1:02:07.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,where Ellie could have stayed if she had wanted to.
Dialogue: 2,1:02:07.17,1:02:13.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Like I said earlier, there was no reason other than the emotional turmoil between the two
Dialogue: 2,1:02:13.76,1:02:17.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,for Ellie to go and live in the grandmother's suite out back.
Dialogue: 2,1:02:17.01,1:02:23.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,But truly everything from the paintings on the walls which we'll come back to later, I promise to,
Dialogue: 2,1:02:23.52,1:02:30.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel's bed still being a little rough and that there is a space magazine and books by his bed,
Dialogue: 2,1:02:30.27,1:02:32.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,that he was reading because he's interested in space
Dialogue: 2,1:02:32.38,1:02:35.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,like it's… it's so cute, and it's so touching,
Dialogue: 2,1:02:35.70,1:02:41.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's so painfully sad to know that he's never going to walk through that house ever again.
Dialogue: 2,1:02:41.10,1:02:42.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,After you grab these items,
Dialogue: 2,1:02:42.66,1:02:47.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,you walked downstairs and realized that Maria is there sitting with Dina.
Dialogue: 2,1:02:47.61,1:02:51.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,She informs you that Tommy left on his own already
Dialogue: 2,1:02:51.19,1:02:55.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,and is asking that Ellie be locked up to prevent her from following him.
Dialogue: 2,1:02:55.83,1:02:59.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maria is understandably frustrated, angry, pissed,
Dialogue: 2,1:02:59.34,1:03:01.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,whatever words you want to associate with it.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:01.89,1:03:04.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,But more than anything, she's worried.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:04.41,1:03:09.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she knows that if she sends Ellie and Dina off to try and help Tommy
Dialogue: 2,1:03:09.93,1:03:11.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least still stand a better chance.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:11.91,1:03:17.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Maria allows Ellie and Dina to leave Jackson with their horses and some extra supplies
Dialogue: 2,1:03:17.09,1:03:22.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,so long as they promised to bring back Tommy, when they return, in one piece.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:22.56,1:03:26.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,This sets up the dual purpose of your journey and theirs.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:26.12,1:03:30.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,You're going there to kill Abby, but also to save Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,1:03:30.33,1:03:33.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,although Tommy probably doesn't need much saving.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:33.39,1:03:36.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you'll realize that once we get to Seattle,
Dialogue: 2,1:03:36.36,1:03:42.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,there's going to be a third purpose in their journey and motivation to everything that they're doing,
Dialogue: 2,1:03:42.87,1:03:44.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's added on top of it.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:44.31,1:03:47.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,I find it really interesting that they set up these multiple goals
Dialogue: 2,1:03:47.24,1:03:51.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it seems as though it just complicates things which I actually like.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:51.56,1:03:57.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Having a single quest, we are just going to try and kill one person, is a little bland.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:57.57,1:03:59.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a little uninteresting.
Dialogue: 2,1:03:59.01,1:04:04.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,So to see that we have multiple things we're trying to do all at once is a little refreshing.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:04.26,1:04:10.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,After this we jumped to the start of the core game itself, Seattle day 1.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:10.98,1:04:15.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,And after this, we're done with the prologue and ready to move into the core of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:15.93,1:04:20.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,But before we do that, I want to discuss our feelings at this point.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:20.31,1:04:23.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this moment in my first run, I felt motivated.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:23.43,1:04:30.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yet still pretty dreadful, in again, the pure sense of the word dread overwhelmed me.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:30.45,1:04:34.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,These revenge quests never end well for anybody,
Dialogue: 2,1:04:34.62,1:04:38.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I couldn't help but feel as though Ellie was going to totally screw herself over
Dialogue: 2,1:04:38.69,1:04:42.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,and end up dead in a ditch somewhere if she tried to do this.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:42.93,1:04:45.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,But again, I think that's kind of the point.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:45.99,1:04:51.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,The player should be just as hesitant and doubtful as Ellie is in this pursuit.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:51.51,1:04:57.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sure, Ellie talks a big game and explains how she's going to go and kill Abby without any remorse,
Dialogue: 2,1:04:57.12,1:04:59.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she's going to get revenge for this terrible act.
Dialogue: 2,1:04:59.64,1:05:03.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,But she still shows some slight reservations every once in a while.
Dialogue: 2,1:05:03.06,1:05:06.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,She knows that this doesn't make a lot of logical sense
Dialogue: 2,1:05:06.51,1:05:11.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,in the same way that Abby knew that her plan to just go in storm Jackson
Dialogue: 2,1:05:11.05,1:05:13.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,didn't make a lot of logical sense,
Dialogue: 2,1:05:13.35,1:05:18.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,but they are going to try and do it because they felt as though it was the right thing to do,
Dialogue: 2,1:05:18.21,1:05:20.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that's what kept them going.
Dialogue: 2,1:05:20.19,1:05:23.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a tug of war of emotions and motivations.
Dialogue: 2,1:05:23.40,1:05:26.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that conflict is what makes an interesting story.
Dialogue: 2,1:05:26.88,1:05:30.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Say what you will about {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} at this point in the story.
Dialogue: 2,1:05:30.96,1:05:33.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's interesting and engaging,
Dialogue: 2,1:05:33.15,1:05:37.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,none the less, might not be fun might not be enjoyable,
Dialogue: 2,1:05:37.41,1:05:39.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it's interesting at least to me.
Dialogue: 2,1:05:39.45,1:05:43.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe you hated it, and if you did, I would love to hear your thoughts down below,
Dialogue: 2,1:05:43.50,1:05:47.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,but to be perfectly honest, you're probably not still here in this video.
Dialogue: 2,1:05:47.37,1:05:50.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you don't find the story of this game, at least somewhat interesting,
Dialogue: 2,1:05:50.82,1:05:56.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, after all, we just got through the prologue and we are well over an hour into this video.
Dialogue: 2,1:05:56.49,1:06:02.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it's with that newfound motivation to find Abby that we enter the core of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:02.55,1:06:05.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's good that we have this emotional drive behind us
Dialogue: 2,1:06:05.66,1:06:09.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,because we're about to enter a very slow sequence of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:09.77,1:06:16.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seriously there's moments in here where I became actively bored because it was all puzzle solving in platform.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:16.98,1:06:19.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just kind of… blaaaah.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:19.14,1:06:20.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we're going to get into it.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:20.67,1:06:24.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,And with that we move to Seattle Day 1.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:24.46,1:06:28.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Our first day in Seattle starts with the gate,
Dialogue: 2,1:06:28.24,1:06:31.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,basically riding through the forest, talking with Dina.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:31.05,1:06:33.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you have to try and get into the body of the city.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:33.75,1:06:36.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, there's a lot of military installations that were put up
Dialogue: 2,1:06:36.81,1:06:41.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,towards the end of quarantine that have since fallen to pieces.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:41.97,1:06:43.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless you have to get through them.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:43.89,1:06:46.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's a few supplies here and there that you can gather.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:46.17,1:06:49.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,But for the most part, this is a puzzle solving sequence.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:49.12,1:06:54.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,We climbed some buildings go up some ladders enter some codes that we find on some papers
Dialogue: 2,1:06:54.34,1:06:56.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we push into Seattle.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:56.49,1:06:59.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was probably my least favorite part of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:06:59.22,1:07:00.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're emotionally motivated.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:00.67,1:07:03.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,We want to go, kick some ass and take some names
Dialogue: 2,1:07:03.13,1:07:06.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then give those names to other people whose asses we've kicked,
Dialogue: 2,1:07:06.21,1:07:11.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,but instead we're forced to just slowly solved some basic puzzles.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:11.07,1:07:14.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,Write down some codes, walked to another place,
Dialogue: 2,1:07:14.13,1:07:19.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,pull open our note book to look back at what the codes were and then enter those in manually.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:19.29,1:07:20.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not that interesting,
Dialogue: 2,1:07:20.70,1:07:25.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it is in direct conflict with what the player wants to be doing at this point.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:25.59,1:07:28.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,I understand may be Naughty Dog wanted to slow the pace down
Dialogue: 2,1:07:28.62,1:07:33.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,after how emotionally distraught you might be after the prologue.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:33.18,1:07:37.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,But still, I can't help but feel as though there would have been a better way to do this
Dialogue: 2,1:07:37.14,1:07:41.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,may be some more combat sequences, may be introducing you to a new type of infected.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:41.61,1:07:45.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure, anything I think would have been better than this.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:45.34,1:07:51.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,We get to downtown and by my estimation, this is the largest single area of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:51.00,1:07:54.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's very open, and there's about eleven main locations,
Dialogue: 2,1:07:54.30,1:07:58.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least that I found to explore in this little area.
Dialogue: 2,1:07:58.68,1:08:03.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,This includes a bank, a synagogue, a court house all very well realized.
Dialogue: 2,1:08:03.57,1:08:08.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,The bank is cool because it's frozen in time, right after a group of people tried to rob,
Dialogue: 2,1:08:08.16,1:08:11.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,I loved seeing all of the money strewn throughout the bank
Dialogue: 2,1:08:11.79,1:08:15.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,and watching Ellie and Dina ponder what they would do with that money
Dialogue: 2,1:08:15.68,1:08:19.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,if it actually was worth anything in their world.
Dialogue: 2,1:08:19.38,1:08:23.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I gotta say Naughty Dog is really good at this sort of indirect world building,
Dialogue: 2,1:08:23.22,1:08:27.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,it makes you question your actual priorities in your current life.
Dialogue: 2,1:08:27.69,1:08:30.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you're motivated purely by money and you have fat stack
Dialogue: 2,1:08:30.64,1:08:33.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,sitting next to you as you watch this video,
Dialogue: 2,1:08:33.39,1:08:36.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,you can't help but feel a little bit strange
Dialogue: 2,1:08:36.45,1:08:41.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,when you walk into this post apocalyptic world and the money is absolutely useless.
Dialogue: 2,1:08:41.34,1:08:45.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's those types of little things that get the wheels turning in your mind
Dialogue: 2,1:08:45.41,1:08:49.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,to start putting yourself in the shoes of the characters in that world.
Dialogue: 2,1:08:49.17,1:08:55.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,That makes Naughty Dog so good at motivating players to continue engaging with the story.
Dialogue: 2,1:08:55.50,1:08:57.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,My favorite part of this chapter, however,
Dialogue: 2,1:08:57.75,1:09:01.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,is an optional item interaction in the music store of this section.
Dialogue: 2,1:09:01.92,1:09:07.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,And basically if you interact with the guitar here, Ellie will start playing and singing Take On Me to Dina.
Dialogue: 2,1:09:07.71,1:09:13.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's really beautiful and is another calm moment in this already relaxing section.
Dialogue: 2,1:09:13.36,1:09:19.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I really enjoyed it, and I recommend that you also enjoy it because it's not going to last.
Dialogue: 2,1:09:19.11,1:09:23.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,But while the story elements of this section of the game are pretty impressive,
Dialogue: 2,1:09:23.82,1:09:29.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't feel as though the expansive areas that you're meant to explore are quite as impressive
Dialogue: 2,1:09:29.38,1:09:32.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,as I think Naughty Dog was hoping they would be.
Dialogue: 2,1:09:32.25,1:09:35.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,This whole area is very reminiscent of the opening of {\i1}The Lost Legacy{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,1:09:35.76,1:09:39.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog's, other most recent {\i1}Uncharted{\i0} game.
Dialogue: 2,1:09:39.12,1:09:42.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,In The Lost Legacy, You have a huge open expanse to explore.
Dialogue: 2,1:09:42.81,1:09:44.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,But by explore,
Dialogue: 2,1:09:44.07,1:09:48.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,they pretty much mean that you move from one location to the other, fights some bad guys,
Dialogue: 2,1:09:48.60,1:09:51.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,solve a quick little puzzle and then move to the next area.
Dialogue: 2,1:09:51.75,1:09:56.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not actually exploring in the same way that you would probably show it in,
Dialogue: 2,1:09:56.61,1:10:01.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,for instance, {\i1}The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild{\i0}, where you're actively exploring the map.
Dialogue: 2,1:10:01.23,1:10:03.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe my expectations were just out of check
Dialogue: 2,1:10:03.52,1:10:06.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,because Naughty Dog did talk these sections up a lot,
Dialogue: 2,1:10:06.60,1:10:11.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,saying that these were the largest levels they had ever designed in any of their games ever,
Dialogue: 2,1:10:11.52,1:10:15.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is true and they're pretty impressive on that front.
Dialogue: 2,1:10:15.81,1:10:18.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in the age of {\i1}Red Dead Redemption 2{\i0}
Dialogue: 2,1:10:18.46,1:10:22.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,riding a horse through a field really isn't an incredible achievement.
Dialogue: 2,1:10:22.26,1:10:25.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, it's not a competition between Naughty Dog and Rockstar.
Dialogue: 2,1:10:25.77,1:10:30.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're both the prettiest girl in the ball, and you can't have either of them,
Dialogue: 2,1:10:30.00,1:10:35.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I can't help but notice as though the foliage and the horses in {\i1}Red Dead Redemption 2{\i0}
Dialogue: 2,1:10:35.37,1:10:42.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,looked a lot better two years ago, in an open world game, when compared to those in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}.
Dialogue: 2,1:10:42.35,1:10:47.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm just really picky or may be my preferences are a skew.
Dialogue: 2,1:10:47.31,1:10:48.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let me know in the comments section below.
Dialogue: 2,1:10:48.90,1:10:54.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I really do feel as though there's a strong difference between these two and it's in Red Dead's favor.
Dialogue: 2,1:10:54.54,1:10:58.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, you continue exploring the map and eventually pushed through the gate that was locked,
Dialogue: 2,1:10:58.98,1:11:00.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,keeping you in this area,
Dialogue: 2,1:11:00.72,1:11:04.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,everything's quiet and you simply ride your horse through the checkpoint,
Dialogue: 2,1:11:04.77,1:11:07.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least until this happens.
Dialogue: 2,1:11:41.61,1:11:48.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,We open back up with Ellie, tied to a desk in a small elementary school called Eastbrook.
Dialogue: 2,1:11:48.96,1:11:52.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is not really important, what's important is that Ellie is being held hostage,
Dialogue: 2,1:11:52.80,1:11:55.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Dina seems to have escaped.
Dialogue: 2,1:11:55.02,1:12:01.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie is about to be executed when Dina comes in and saves the day… Well, at least… almost.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:03.09,1:12:07.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,You watches this guy tries to strangle Dina, feeling absolutely helpless.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:07.59,1:12:09.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's actually pretty well done.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:09.48,1:12:12.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,I found my heart rate increasing quite drastically during this.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:12.96,1:12:15.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,Eventually, use your foot to grab a shard of glass,
Dialogue: 2,1:12:15.39,1:12:16.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,use it to cut your bindings.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:16.86,1:12:20.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Ellie goes up and kills Dina's attacker,
Dialogue: 2,1:12:20.10,1:12:23.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,at which point she grabs a letter and picture from his pocket.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:23.52,1:12:26.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Which will be important in just a little bit.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:26.04,1:12:29.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,You are through a few combat sequences here that pair you against human enemies.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:29.97,1:12:35.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a nice change of pace from the infected that you've been dealing with exclusively up to this point,
Dialogue: 2,1:12:35.49,1:12:37.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it forces you to change your approach.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:37.92,1:12:41.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,For instance, you have to really be careful managing your flashlights.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:41.46,1:12:45.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Going up against most infected, you don't have to worry about your flashlight being on or off
Dialogue: 2,1:12:45.32,1:12:48.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they can't see it or don't respond to it.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:48.70,1:12:51.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,With humans, of course they do.
Dialogue: 2,1:12:51.21,1:12:54.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're much more visual and much less auditory,
Dialogue: 2,1:12:54.03,1:12:58.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,though tactically flank you and maneuver around you if they need to,
Dialogue: 2,1:12:58.71,1:13:03.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,though they can be lured with sound into traps very easily.
Dialogue: 2,1:13:03.15,1:13:07.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,But on Survivor difficulty, I will say it can be frustrating if you run out of ammo,
Dialogue: 2,1:13:07.59,1:13:13.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,as your only option in dealing with them and ranged attacks is to throw bottles and rush
Dialogue: 2,1:13:13.31,1:13:15.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,or just sit and pray that they come around.
Dialogue: 2,1:13:15.78,1:13:21.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,I understand that it's a post apocalyptic world, and not everything is going to be convenient within it.
Dialogue: 2,1:13:21.21,1:13:24.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, it's pretty frustrating.
Dialogue: 2,1:13:24.12,1:13:25.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,After fighting your way to safety,
Dialogue: 2,1:13:25.74,1:13:30.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie looks at the document and the picture that she swiped off of Dina's attacker.
Dialogue: 2,1:13:30.57,1:13:36.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a new picture that Leah gave to her boyfriend, Jordan, who is actually the guy that you just killed.
Dialogue: 2,1:13:36.32,1:13:40.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,And sorry boys, but there's a blood smear that covers all of the good stuff,
Dialogue: 2,1:13:40.32,1:13:42.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,so no use in pausing the video.
Dialogue: 2,1:13:42.84,1:13:47.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, Leah happens to be one of the people that joined Abby on their "kill-cation",
Dialogue: 2,1:13:47.46,1:13:52.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,another coincidence that leads Ellie to the Channel 13 Station to find Leah,
Dialogue: 2,1:13:52.44,1:13:55.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,who might be able to help them find the Abby in turn.
Dialogue: 2,1:13:55.77,1:14:03.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Dina also hear about this guy Isaac in conversations that can be overheard from the WLF members.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:03.15,1:14:10.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now not much is known about this guy or revealed about him for that matter, for quite a while.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:10.14,1:14:15.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,But what we do know is that he seemingly runs the WLF, and he has a firm grip on power.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:15.66,1:14:18.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everyone does what he says and are scared of him.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:18.21,1:14:23.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog games of the past would use this as a set up for the later boss fight with Isaac.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:23.16,1:14:26.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,If he's mentioned, he'll be a key part of the story later, right?
Dialogue: 2,1:14:26.82,1:14:28.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, actually wrong.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:28.65,1:14:33.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,This will happen again with another character later, maybe it's a set up for a sequel or something.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:33.24,1:14:40.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,But… as for Isaac himself and the other lady that's going to be shown off, it actually doesn't come around.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:40.26,1:14:45.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,All of that said Ellie and Dina head into the heart of the city to find the Channel 13 Station
Dialogue: 2,1:14:45.00,1:14:49.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,to hunt down Leah to try and in turn, get more information on Abby.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:49.08,1:14:53.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,You push through a ton of WLF soldiers and lots of infected as well.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:53.67,1:14:58.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,You find some trip wire traps set up that reminded me of Bill from the first game.
Dialogue: 2,1:14:58.29,1:15:03.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,But here they don't seem to serve any purpose other than to slow down game play and exploration then.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:03.99,1:15:09.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,Personally I just soon find these trip wire bombs fun. They're just annoying.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:09.30,1:15:13.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's good to shake up the monotony of game play every once in a while that something new and different,
Dialogue: 2,1:15:13.68,1:15:15.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,such as these trip wire minds.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:15.63,1:15:20.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in this case, these things don't really come up again for the rest of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:20.19,1:15:26.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're just a one of frustration that doesn't actually drive you into any sort of new habitual behavior.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:26.76,1:15:30.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,In other words in most games, when they introduce you to a new gameplay element,
Dialogue: 2,1:15:30.90,1:15:33.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's because it's going to be used throughout the rest of the game,
Dialogue: 2,1:15:33.75,1:15:36.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why you need to be taught how to deal with it.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:36.72,1:15:42.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in this case they're used very sparingly and in most cases they are entirely avoidable.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:42.24,1:15:45.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,But granted. This is probably just a pet peeve on my end.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:45.27,1:15:49.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you come up on the station after finding the best collectable in the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:53.97,1:15:55.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you begin exploring it,
Dialogue: 2,1:15:55.62,1:15:58.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,you find the remnants of a Scar ceremony of some sort.
Dialogue: 2,1:15:58.83,1:16:03.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's a bunch of bodies that are strung up everywhere and that have been disemboweled.
Dialogue: 2,1:16:03.43,1:16:07.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it's not clear exactly when this happened, but it seems relatively recent.
Dialogue: 2,1:16:07.86,1:16:11.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now if you're anything like me, you would have immediately realized that
Dialogue: 2,1:16:11.52,1:16:17.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Leah is probably not going to be in any sort of condition to help you find Abby,
Dialogue: 2,1:16:17.07,1:16:20.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially after all of this Scar stuff.
Dialogue: 2,1:16:20.34,1:16:24.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,If she's even still in the station, she is probably dead.
Dialogue: 2,1:16:24.02,1:16:28.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,And sure enough you finally at the top of the station in an office
Dialogue: 2,1:16:28.50,1:16:31.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,shot dead with a bunch of arrows sticking out of her.
Dialogue: 2,1:16:31.08,1:16:35.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the coincidence is common clutch and save the day
Dialogue: 2,1:16:35.64,1:16:39.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,because Ellie decides to open up Leah's duffel bag underneath her cot,
Dialogue: 2,1:16:39.51,1:16:48.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,which just happens to have pictures of all of the team members that went to Jackson and killed Joel.
Dialogue: 2,1:16:48.45,1:16:51.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Apparently, they basically have logged the whole thing,
Dialogue: 2,1:16:51.60,1:16:54.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why I called a "kill-cation" earlier.
Dialogue: 2,1:16:54.24,1:16:58.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is probably, and to be perfectly honest, I think it is
Dialogue: 2,1:16:58.68,1:17:03.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,the most egregious example of coincidence is driving this story.
Dialogue: 2,1:17:03.36,1:17:07.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,They needed Ellie to be reminded and have some sort of firm idea
Dialogue: 2,1:17:07.30,1:17:10.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,of what these people looked like and what their names were,
Dialogue: 2,1:17:10.44,1:17:14.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that she could ask other people who they were and where they were,
Dialogue: 2,1:17:14.85,1:17:19.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,they couldn't come up with any reasonable way of her coming up with this information herself,
Dialogue: 2,1:17:19.14,1:17:26.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,so instead they had to have her stumble onto it by finding a bag that happened to be left behind,
Dialogue: 2,1:17:26.04,1:17:31.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,that happened to have all of these pictures placed in it by some lady that was on a work assignment.
Dialogue: 2,1:17:31.35,1:17:35.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's the thing she wasn't even really supposed to be at this TV station for very long,
Dialogue: 2,1:17:35.49,1:17:39.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,so I don't understand why she would have brought all of these pictures very precious to…
Dialogue: 2,1:17:39.73,1:17:41.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,I… I just, I don't understand.
Dialogue: 2,1:17:41.55,1:17:43.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I'll stop beating the dead horse there.
Dialogue: 2,1:17:43.43,1:17:48.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right as you find the photos, WLF members show up and assuming that you're a Scar
Dialogue: 2,1:17:48.65,1:17:51.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,pushed through the entire building to find Ellie and Dina.
Dialogue: 2,1:17:51.51,1:17:53.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,You fight them and escaped through the basement
Dialogue: 2,1:17:53.67,1:17:57.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,which leads to the underground tunnel system for the subway.
Dialogue: 2,1:17:57.12,1:17:59.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,This encounter seems really intimidating at first,
Dialogue: 2,1:17:59.64,1:18:02.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,but rest assured, it's actually pretty easy to spam.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:02.56,1:18:08.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,As you can see in this instance, if you know what I use a good Molotov cocktail, you can work wonders.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:08.19,1:18:09.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once you're in the subway system,
Dialogue: 2,1:18:09.54,1:18:16.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,you find some new zombies known as Shamblers, which eject a sort of acidic cloud when at the road.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:16.36,1:18:21.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,At Normal difficulty, I will actually say that these things are disappointingly easy to kill,
Dialogue: 2,1:18:21.87,1:18:25.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,like they do not meet the expectation at all.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:25.65,1:18:29.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Their bite is nowhere near as bad as their bark,
Dialogue: 2,1:18:29.64,1:18:35.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,but on Survivor new game plus, these things can eat my entire ass,
Dialogue: 2,1:18:35.55,1:18:39.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,and maybe it was just me that had an easy time with these Shamblers,
Dialogue: 2,1:18:39.45,1:18:42.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,or perhaps just expected way more for them.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:42.32,1:18:47.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because there are some signs that Naughty Dog expected players to have more trouble with these guys.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:47.10,1:18:49.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, look at how Dina locks this door.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:49.62,1:18:51.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,I thought this was kind of weird in my first run through
Dialogue: 2,1:18:51.80,1:18:55.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,because there was nothing left to keep from getting through.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:55.11,1:18:57.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,All of the zombies were dead.
Dialogue: 2,1:18:57.12,1:19:01.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,I killed them all, and there was nothing left in that room to prevent from escaping.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:01.74,1:19:03.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in my new game plus run,
Dialogue: 2,1:19:03.75,1:19:09.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,I snuck through this section, leaving many or even most of those infected alive.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:09.30,1:19:13.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,In that case, locking this door made a lot more sense.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:13.47,1:19:17.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,But on my first run, on a normal difficulty with all of the zombies dead,
Dialogue: 2,1:19:17.55,1:19:22.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,it really seemed strange that Dina wanted to lock this door down.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:22.32,1:19:25.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, I guess it can't hurt, but still it just seemed odd.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:25.44,1:19:28.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is a simple, but I think it's an effective example of
Dialogue: 2,1:19:28.72,1:19:33.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,how Naughty Dog likely expected more players to stealth their way through these sections.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:33.63,1:19:36.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Ellie and Dina continue to push through these tunnels.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:36.51,1:19:41.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's actually a pretty cool sequence going through these things again when remembering the first game.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:41.70,1:19:45.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because of course, in the first game, Ellie couldn't even swim.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:45.48,1:19:50.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Joel had to use all sorts of floating platforms to get her from one area to the next.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:50.40,1:19:52.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this case, Ellie is much more capable.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:52.50,1:19:56.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if anything, it's Dina, who requires a little more babying.
Dialogue: 2,1:19:56.16,1:20:02.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,But after exploring a few of these tunnels and climbing through some train cars, one of them collapses.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:02.01,1:20:08.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie takes a tumble as they're jumped by a bunch of infected and Ellie's mask actually cracks,
Dialogue: 2,1:20:08.07,1:20:10.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,leaving her exposed to the spores.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:10.08,1:20:14.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina understandably starts to freak out, thinking that Ellie is going to die.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:14.58,1:20:17.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie says she's fine as they raced to the street level
Dialogue: 2,1:20:17.52,1:20:21.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,and insists that Dina does not take off her mask to share between the two of them.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:21.66,1:20:24.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,You fight your way all the way up to the street level,
Dialogue: 2,1:20:24.51,1:20:29.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,locked the door behind you and look across the street and see an old theatre.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:29.10,1:20:30.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,You decide to take refuge there,
Dialogue: 2,1:20:30.84,1:20:37.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,and thankfully it's fairly well guarded, defensible, and the doors do lock from the inside.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:37.03,1:20:41.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Dina break in, take refuge and start to rest.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:41.16,1:20:45.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina is understandably upset because she thinks that Ellie is going to die.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:45.99,1:20:49.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, she just saw her inhale spores.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:49.02,1:20:53.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,And for any other human being that she knows that would be an instant death sentence.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:53.25,1:20:57.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,But instead, Ellie seems fine. There's no problem.
Dialogue: 2,1:20:57.87,1:21:02.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's at this point that Ellie again explains how she's actually immune.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:02.76,1:21:05.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,She previously explained this to Dina
Dialogue: 2,1:21:05.67,1:21:10.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,back when they were in Eugene's basement weed emporium.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:10.02,1:21:12.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, it seemed back then that Dina did not believe her thought
Dialogue: 2,1:21:12.85,1:21:16.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,that she was pulling your leg and just thought it was a cruel joke.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:16.44,1:21:20.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,But now Dina understands that this might actually be true,
Dialogue: 2,1:21:20.19,1:21:24.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,although I will say that Dina never really seems to go any further with this.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:24.69,1:21:31.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,Her love interest is immune from the fungus that is infecting all of life on the planet.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:32.07,1:21:34.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,And she doesn't seem that interesting in it.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:34.41,1:21:38.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,Really, I'm not sure if she brings it up ever again throughout the entire game,
Dialogue: 2,1:21:38.73,1:21:42.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,even in the later cut scenes and sequences.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:42.06,1:21:43.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just a little strange,
Dialogue: 2,1:21:43.29,1:21:46.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,I understand there's a lot to get through during the course of this story.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:46.80,1:21:50.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,And perhaps there were scenes that had been written where they discuss it further,
Dialogue: 2,1:21:50.40,1:21:53.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it was eventually cut… I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:53.43,1:21:58.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,But all I know is that it seems strange that Dina doesn't engage with Ellie further on this matter.
Dialogue: 2,1:21:58.62,1:22:03.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,While also in the theater, Dina explains that she thinks that she's pregnant.
Dialogue: 2,1:22:03.93,1:22:08.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see, she dated Jesse, broke up with him a week before Ellie and Dina's kiss.
Dialogue: 2,1:22:08.85,1:22:12.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that would mean that the baby is Jesse's.
Dialogue: 2,1:22:12.30,1:22:15.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,This, of course complicates the relationship between all of them.
Dialogue: 2,1:22:15.87,1:22:19.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, personally, this came as no surprise at all to me.
Dialogue: 2,1:22:19.05,1:22:24.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all of the signaling that they did for the last three or so hours of game play
Dialogue: 2,1:22:24.36,1:22:26.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,and if you were reading Ellie's journal at all,
Dialogue: 2,1:22:26.73,1:22:29.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,you'll know this well ahead of Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,1:22:29.81,1:22:34.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina was puking a lot, saying that she wasn't feeling well, saying that she was tired,
Dialogue: 2,1:22:34.74,1:22:40.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,blaming a lot of things on the gore around her, but in reality it was morning sickness.
Dialogue: 2,1:22:40.62,1:22:48.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, having heard Abby and Owen discuss Mel, Owen's other love interest, and her pregnancy,
Dialogue: 2,1:22:48.87,1:22:50.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,it seemed like a slam dunk
Dialogue: 2,1:22:50.63,1:22:55.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Naughty Dog was going to have somebody in Ellie's friend circle become pregnant
Dialogue: 2,1:22:55.05,1:22:57.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that they could draw a further parallel later.
Dialogue: 2,1:22:57.69,1:23:00.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sure enough, that's exactly what they did.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:00.51,1:23:03.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, Ellie breaks away, allowing Dina to sleep.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:03.81,1:23:07.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,You get some electricity running after the awkward conversation
Dialogue: 2,1:23:07.80,1:23:11.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and stumble upon a radio in a technician's closet.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:11.10,1:23:15.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's broken, Ellie becomes frustrated and wax at in frustration,
Dialogue: 2,1:23:15.12,1:23:20.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is how she actually finds the keys that led her into the deeper areas of the theater.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:20.76,1:23:23.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know why the keys were under the radio.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:23.34,1:23:27.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's almighty convenient that she hit the radio in frustration in the first place
Dialogue: 2,1:23:27.59,1:23:29.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,because if she didn't, she wouldn't have found the keys.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:29.40,1:23:35.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,But whatever, you get the point, I have been complaining about coincidences in this whole videos.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:35.72,1:23:37.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you get the point. I'll just, I'll move on.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:37.91,1:23:39.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,You find a guitar in the back of the theater
Dialogue: 2,1:23:39.71,1:23:43.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,and play the same song that we saw Joel played for Ellie in the flashback
Dialogue: 2,1:23:43.95,1:23:46.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,wherein he was teaching Ellie how to play.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:46.14,1:23:49.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,She plays the first few bars, and then we cut to a flashback.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:49.83,1:23:53.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,Probably my favorite flashback of the entire game.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:53.43,1:23:55.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's Joel and Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,1:23:55.32,1:23:57.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems to be Ellie's birthday,
Dialogue: 2,1:23:57.18,1:24:00.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Joel is taking her to find her birthday gift.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:00.24,1:24:05.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's not much to say about this sequence other than that it's very touching and sweet.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:05.16,1:24:09.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel found this museum that had a giant dinosaur statue in it
Dialogue: 2,1:24:09.16,1:24:12.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,because he knew that Ellie dreamed of seeing dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:12.63,1:24:17.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,She also wants to go to space, one of her dreams is to go to space.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:17.49,1:24:19.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,And he takes her to the astronaut exhibit,
Dialogue: 2,1:24:19.98,1:24:24.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,wherein she can put on a helmet and then climb into the actual capsule.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:24.84,1:24:30.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel hops in too, gives her a headset and allows her to zone out
Dialogue: 2,1:24:30.04,1:24:34.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,while imagining herself going into space and taking off.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:34.47,1:24:40.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,This sequence is actually just like the arcade one in {\i1}Left Behind{\i0} the DLC from the first game
Dialogue: 2,1:24:40.70,1:24:45.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,wherein Ellie and Riley were imagining playing this video game.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:45.15,1:24:48.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course they couldn't play it, it was long since broken.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:48.54,1:24:53.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Riley had Ellie close her eyes and imagine everything while she described it.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:53.34,1:24:57.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,You'd better believe it's no coincidence that these two events are so similar.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:57.63,1:24:59.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a super simple scene.
Dialogue: 2,1:24:59.52,1:25:07.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it just serves to further establish that Joel and Ellie had a deep relationship and care for each other.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:07.26,1:25:10.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Also that their relationship is pretty complicated.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:10.35,1:25:15.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because at the very end of this scene you come across a writing on the wall.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:15.87,1:25:21.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,And needless to say, it's something that Joel and Ellie don't want to discuss.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:21.27,1:25:22.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,So they just leave.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:22.62,1:25:25.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,And after that we jumped to Seattle Day 2.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:25.29,1:25:27.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,Starting out our second day in Seattle,
Dialogue: 2,1:25:27.39,1:25:31.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie wakes up in the theater and finds Dina in the radio room vomiting,
Dialogue: 2,1:25:31.91,1:25:36.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,a not so subtle reminder of the revelation that we saw before the flashback.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:36.72,1:25:40.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's been listening to the radio, deciphering the WLF's communications
Dialogue: 2,1:25:40.58,1:25:44.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,to figure out where members of Joel's assassination party might be.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:44.47,1:25:51.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina and Ellie overhear a WLF broadcast together that there's a lone gunman in Zone 14.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:51.66,1:25:57.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,They guess that this is a neighborhood called Hillcrest and Ellie heads out to investigate.
Dialogue: 2,1:25:57.03,1:26:00.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,They think that this could be Tommy because, well, who else could it be?
Dialogue: 2,1:26:00.48,1:26:05.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the bell, I have a kitten on my lap and she's making noise.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:05.67,1:26:08.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,But yeah, shocker have… of course it's not Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:08.49,1:26:11.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,Playing as Ellie, you push through a few different areas,
Dialogue: 2,1:26:11.30,1:26:14.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,fighting all sorts of wolfs and looting lots of buildings.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:15.12,1:26:17.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Not much happens for around thirty minutes of exploring
Dialogue: 2,1:26:17.78,1:26:21.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,until all of the WLF seems to descend at the same spot,
Dialogue: 2,1:26:21.84,1:26:24.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,a smoke signal that Ellie also follows.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:24.52,1:26:27.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,The level design here is really fantastic.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:27.15,1:26:32.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,This use of a visual objective in the distance that you can follow as you go through the level.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:32.73,1:26:37.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's really well done, and it's something Naughty Dog has been doing for a long time
Dialogue: 2,1:26:37.66,1:26:39.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that they really have perfected.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:39.69,1:26:42.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now these level really crescendos in difficulty,
Dialogue: 2,1:26:42.54,1:26:47.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially in harder difficulty settings where difficulty spikes are far more severe.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:47.67,1:26:51.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now the thing about this is that you'll get caught with no ammo in this level
Dialogue: 2,1:26:51.54,1:26:54.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,if you're not careful and use it all too early.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:54.24,1:26:57.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you have to be very careful to preserve it.
Dialogue: 2,1:26:57.09,1:27:00.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the problem is on your first run through you're not going to know
Dialogue: 2,1:27:00.13,1:27:02.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,that you're going to run out of ammo so quickly.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:02.64,1:27:03.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,You couldn't have known.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:03.96,1:27:09.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in turn you are always careful and never want to use any of your ammo whatsoever.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:09.48,1:27:12.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when that's the case, you are always careful,
Dialogue: 2,1:27:12.57,1:27:17.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,which also means that you never are because your behavior isn't changing in any way.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:17.10,1:27:18.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,You are just refusing to use ammo,
Dialogue: 2,1:27:18.78,1:27:21.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,so you're effectively playing through the game as a melee game.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:21.30,1:27:26.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's this game play hesitance that I have noticed in a lot of horror video games,
Dialogue: 2,1:27:26.46,1:27:29.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially where ammo is very limited.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:29.82,1:27:36.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's strange to me because I don't think it actually reflects a better game play experience
Dialogue: 2,1:27:36.29,1:27:40.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it just ends up with the player refusing to use multiple mechanics
Dialogue: 2,1:27:40.22,1:27:42.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they are scared that if they do use them,
Dialogue: 2,1:27:42.36,1:27:45.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,they're going to run out of ammo and be unable to use them later on.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:45.99,1:27:51.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I understand that getting rid of this system could also be like throwing the baby out with the bathwater.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:51.69,1:27:54.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Though regardless, Ellie pushes to the smokestack,
Dialogue: 2,1:27:54.57,1:27:58.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,killing and evading all sorts of WLF members while she goes.
Dialogue: 2,1:27:58.26,1:28:00.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,You eventually unlock the bow and arrow here,
Dialogue: 2,1:28:00.45,1:28:04.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is actually probably my favorite weapon of the whole game.
Dialogue: 2,1:28:04.44,1:28:08.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's silent, you can recollect a lot of the ammo depending on where you hit the enemy
Dialogue: 2,1:28:08.53,1:28:10.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,and on what difficulty you're playing.
Dialogue: 2,1:28:10.86,1:28:14.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,And all around I just like it, I find it really satisfying.
Dialogue: 2,1:28:14.61,1:28:19.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,She reaches the location of the smoke stack, and then this happens.
Dialogue: 2,1:28:48.00,1:28:53.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is really weird to me… because…
Dialogue: 2,1:28:53.02,1:28:56.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,as far as I knew, this was going to be Joel when Ellie turned around,
Dialogue: 2,1:28:56.97,1:29:01.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I was really confused when I saw that we were getting to that point where the trailer happened.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:01.64,1:29:03.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I knew that Joel was dead.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:03.69,1:29:05.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,How could he possibly show up and save the day?
Dialogue: 2,1:29:05.79,1:29:08.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,But sure enough, it ends up being Jesse.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:08.88,1:29:13.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just strange to me that they chose to do this fake out,
Dialogue: 2,1:29:13.02,1:29:17.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,where we thought that it was going to be Joel here,
Dialogue: 2,1:29:17.07,1:29:18.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,because that's what the trailer showed,
Dialogue: 2,1:29:18.87,1:29:23.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then it ends up being just… It's just it's weird… It's weird to me.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:23.07,1:29:24.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know what else to say.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:24.30,1:29:27.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you have more information on this, let me know in the comments section below,
Dialogue: 2,1:29:27.06,1:29:29.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,I just…  it's weird. I don't know what to make of it.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:29.64,1:29:33.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, Ellie and Jessie managed to escape by way of a stolen car
Dialogue: 2,1:29:33.12,1:29:39.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they drive into a river in a pretty impressive sequence that also leaked pre launch.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:39.48,1:29:43.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a superfluid sequence, and no, I'm not just saying that because they end up in a river,
Dialogue: 2,1:29:43.47,1:29:47.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it's very well polished and it looks incredible to boot.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:47.76,1:29:51.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,But then again, I mean, this is a Naughty Dog game wouldn't expect anything else.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:51.78,1:29:55.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,You bring Jesse back to Dina and there's a ton of tension here.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:55.77,1:29:59.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie, of course, leaves because she feels very awkward.
Dialogue: 2,1:29:59.07,1:30:03.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all Ellie's girlfriend's baby daddy just showed up.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:03.54,1:30:05.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't blame her for wanting to leave.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:05.44,1:30:10.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,As Ellie walks away, we jump into another flashback, and this one's actually pretty simple.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:10.56,1:30:14.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Joel are exploring a hotel while on their way to a music store
Dialogue: 2,1:30:14.10,1:30:17.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,after Ellie receives a lesson on sniping from Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:17.73,1:30:19.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this may seem really random,
Dialogue: 2,1:30:19.14,1:30:25.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially because sniping will not be a major mechanic for Ellie throughout the entire game.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:25.11,1:30:31.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,But there actually is a reason for them showing the player this sniping tutorial.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:31.02,1:30:33.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'll get to that more in a little bit, though.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:33.52,1:30:40.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,After you finish your sniping tutorial with Tommy, ride back down the hill and find Joel sitting there
Dialogue: 2,1:30:40.08,1:30:45.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you prepare to go out with him to find some guitar strings at a music store.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:45.66,1:30:52.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, A fun little detail is that this actually was originally an entirely different plot.
Dialogue: 2,1:30:52.53,1:30:56.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Originally after Ellie finished her sniping tutorial with Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,1:30:56.55,1:31:03.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,she and Joel were going to go and say Hi to Joel's girlfriend who lived just a little ways down the road.
Dialogue: 2,1:31:03.21,1:31:08.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,They were going to ride up, find Joel's girlfriend having been freshly bitten
Dialogue: 2,1:31:08.76,1:31:11.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they were going to be forced to make a difficult choice.
Dialogue: 2,1:31:11.46,1:31:15.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,While they all negotiated back and forth what they should do about it,
Dialogue: 2,1:31:15.15,1:31:19.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,they send Ellie outside to grab some fresh water from the stream.
Dialogue: 2,1:31:19.49,1:31:23.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once Ellie walks outside, she hears a gunshot,
Dialogue: 2,1:31:23.01,1:31:27.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then Joel walks out, and they know that something happened.
Dialogue: 2,1:31:27.00,1:31:29.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,They know that… she's gone.
Dialogue: 2,1:31:29.79,1:31:34.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,And either Joel put her out of her misery at her request,
Dialogue: 2,1:31:34.11,1:31:39.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,or she put herself out of her own misery because she knew that she didn't want Joel have to do it for her,
Dialogue: 2,1:31:39.63,1:31:41.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they knew how this was going to end.
Dialogue: 2,1:31:41.76,1:31:45.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, it would have been a very touching moment
Dialogue: 2,1:31:45.60,1:31:50.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,and interesting thing to see Joel and Ellie experience together.
Dialogue: 2,1:31:50.85,1:31:56.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel experiencing another loss and using Ellie to help him get through it.
Dialogue: 2,1:31:56.07,1:32:03.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,But apparently, according to the press release and comments by Neil Druckmann and all of his writing staff,
Dialogue: 2,1:32:03.81,1:32:07.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,this scene was cut in favor of this new scene
Dialogue: 2,1:32:07.18,1:32:11.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they go and explore a hotel cutting through to a music store.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:11.07,1:32:16.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because they felt as though it was too much of a diversion from the priorities of the story.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:16.35,1:32:21.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,In other words, this is a game about Ellie, it's not a game about Joel.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:21.33,1:32:28.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if they had this scene focused on Joel, it would start to feel much more like a Joel AND Ellie Game.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:28.56,1:32:33.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,But a Joel and Ellie game, where your only playing as Ellie, but make of that what you will.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:33.52,1:32:36.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,You cut through the resort, clearing out a ton of infected
Dialogue: 2,1:32:36.42,1:32:40.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it actually feels a lot like the first game, it's pretty nice.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:40.23,1:32:44.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,As they pushed through the resort, Joel insists that Ellie wear her mask,
Dialogue: 2,1:32:44.79,1:32:47.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though she's immune to the spores.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:47.67,1:32:50.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,she asks why she'd would need to do this,
Dialogue: 2,1:32:50.04,1:32:52.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,after all, it's just them exploring the hotel.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:52.56,1:32:57.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,And he says, because if somebody saw her, they would have a lot of questions understandably.
Dialogue: 2,1:32:57.60,1:33:00.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it's better to be safe than sorry, she should just wear it.
Dialogue: 2,1:33:00.66,1:33:02.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this explains why she was wearing it
Dialogue: 2,1:33:02.63,1:33:05.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,and all of the other sequences like we talked about at the beginning.
Dialogue: 2,1:33:05.85,1:33:11.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,She wore the mask at Joel's insistence because she didn't want to risk anybody finding out
Dialogue: 2,1:33:11.28,1:33:13.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it would cause too much trouble,
Dialogue: 2,1:33:13.47,1:33:17.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,or it just wasn't worth the headache of explaining everything that went down with the Fireflies,
Dialogue: 2,1:33:17.67,1:33:22.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,even if Joel was going to stick to his original story of what happened.
Dialogue: 2,1:33:22.20,1:33:26.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,But after pushing through a ton of infected fighting, a mini boss fight with Joel again,
Dialogue: 2,1:33:26.97,1:33:32.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,very reminiscent of the first game touching and tugging on all of my heart strings,
Dialogue: 2,1:33:32.73,1:33:36.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,they end up finding a couple that left Jackson a few months before
Dialogue: 2,1:33:36.68,1:33:40.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,which spurs a conversation about what happened at the hospital.
Dialogue: 2,1:33:40.47,1:33:44.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, Joel continues to lie.
Dialogue: 2,1:34:27.68,1:34:30.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,We then cut to Ellie, patching up a cut in the theater.
Dialogue: 2,1:34:30.47,1:34:33.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina helps her and they try to resolve some of the awkward tension
Dialogue: 2,1:34:33.44,1:34:36.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they just experienced after Jesse's arrival.
Dialogue: 2,1:34:36.14,1:34:40.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina reveals that she's figured out using the radio that Nora, one of the Joel's squad
Dialogue: 2,1:34:40.85,1:34:45.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,is stationed at the hospital and may know where Abby is.
Dialogue: 2,1:34:45.89,1:34:48.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie takes off immediately and heads for that hospital,
Dialogue: 2,1:34:48.98,1:34:51.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this is actually pretty quiet chapter of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:34:51.23,1:34:53.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because Ellie is, of course by herself.
Dialogue: 2,1:34:53.45,1:34:57.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's no one to bounce anything off of, she's just alone.
Dialogue: 2,1:34:57.32,1:35:01.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,And they are actually able to throw a couple curve balls at the player as a result of this,
Dialogue: 2,1:35:01.13,1:35:04.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,which I actually really really enjoyed.
Dialogue: 2,1:35:04.01,1:35:07.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,The best example would probably be when Ellie walks up to a workbench,
Dialogue: 2,1:35:07.40,1:35:10.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is where you do all of your maintenance on all of your weapons,
Dialogue: 2,1:35:10.31,1:35:14.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,adding upgrades changing things out using the scrap that you find in the world,
Dialogue: 2,1:35:14.42,1:35:16.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,at which point she's jumped.
Dialogue: 2,1:35:35.69,1:35:39.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,I thought this was super cool when I saw it,
Dialogue: 2,1:35:39.32,1:35:43.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,I was like ah… shoot! I'm not even safe in the menus now!
Dialogue: 2,1:35:43.91,1:35:47.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,I… I… I understand this probably pissed some people off when freaked them out.
Dialogue: 2,1:35:47.75,1:35:52.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because if anything, in video games' menus are sacred, you should be safe in a menu.
Dialogue: 2,1:35:52.91,1:35:56.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in this case you're not, and I just thought it was awesome.
Dialogue: 2,1:35:56.27,1:35:59.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now let's also take this chance to discuss crafting a little bit.
Dialogue: 2,1:35:59.36,1:36:02.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,The crafting system is pretty much identical to the first game,
Dialogue: 2,1:36:02.15,1:36:04.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,except there's a few new items like pipe bombs.
Dialogue: 2,1:36:04.61,1:36:09.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Most character upgrades will only get about halfway through their upgrade tree
Dialogue: 2,1:36:09.15,1:36:11.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,if you want to call it that throughout most runs.
Dialogue: 2,1:36:11.63,1:36:15.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,New game plus lets you max Level Ellie and Abby
Dialogue: 2,1:36:15.26,1:36:18.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,by the time you're done playing each of their respective halves of the game,
Dialogue: 2,1:36:18.86,1:36:21.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,which does make you feel like a superhero.
Dialogue: 2,1:36:21.03,1:36:26.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now on higher difficulties, these crafting items are stupid scarce, really.
Dialogue: 2,1:36:26.00,1:36:32.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're pretty hard to find than they don't tend to generate or populate in the world itself
Dialogue: 2,1:36:32.26,1:36:35.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,unless you are really struggling later in the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:36:35.30,1:36:41.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,But these dynamic policemen systems that Naughty Dog uses in these {\i1}TLOU{\i0} games works pretty well
Dialogue: 2,1:36:41.02,1:36:44.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they don't have a lot of complaints about them, except for healing items.
Dialogue: 2,1:36:44.63,1:36:51.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,These quick snacks and things that refill your health are far too plentiful on high difficulties,
Dialogue: 2,1:36:51.29,1:36:54.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least in my mind, it makes the game too easy,
Dialogue: 2,1:36:54.38,1:36:59.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though the combat is remarkably hard on, for instance, Survivor.
Dialogue: 2,1:36:59.59,1:37:04.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,Part of the reason this is a problem in my mind is because Molotovs are crafted using the same materials.
Dialogue: 2,1:37:04.63,1:37:07.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,So effectively, the player is always faced with a choice
Dialogue: 2,1:37:07.21,1:37:10.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,between crafting a health kit and a Molotov cocktail.
Dialogue: 2,1:37:10.95,1:37:15.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seems like a stupid delineation to draw, but I think it's important.
Dialogue: 2,1:37:15.52,1:37:20.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see, health kits just represent a major mistake on the part of the player.
Dialogue: 2,1:37:20.54,1:37:24.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you make a major mistake, you're probably going to die on a higher difficulty,
Dialogue: 2,1:37:24.71,1:37:26.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,so it's not worth continuing.
Dialogue: 2,1:37:26.62,1:37:30.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,You're usually just going to reload and save and continue on
Dialogue: 2,1:37:30.53,1:37:33.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,with all the ammo you had before you made that big mistake.
Dialogue: 2,1:37:33.74,1:37:36.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means that in my new game plus run on Survivor,
Dialogue: 2,1:37:36.53,1:37:42.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,I almost never crafted any healing kits at all because Molotovs were far more useful.
Dialogue: 2,1:37:42.53,1:37:46.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if I ever got to the point where my health was really, really low,
Dialogue: 2,1:37:46.40,1:37:49.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would have just restarted from the previous save
Dialogue: 2,1:37:49.16,1:37:53.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,and not made that same mistake that landed me in that tough spot.
Dialogue: 2,1:37:53.12,1:37:57.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,The other piece to all of this looting and crafting crap is that
Dialogue: 2,1:37:57.17,1:38:01.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,looting materials does make it feel as though you are exploring the levels.
Dialogue: 2,1:38:01.04,1:38:05.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it motivates the player to explore the levels in most instances.
Dialogue: 2,1:38:05.45,1:38:10.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the developers used a balanced, dynamic generation system that makes it.
Dialogue: 2,1:38:10.75,1:38:14.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if you were preparing to go up against a boss fight, for instance,
Dialogue: 2,1:38:14.99,1:38:18.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,more ammo will generate as you get closer to that boss
Dialogue: 2,1:38:18.43,1:38:23.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,to bring you up to the recommended level that they set for that boss fighting counter.
Dialogue: 2,1:38:23.90,1:38:26.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now of course, nothing is forcing you to pick up these items,
Dialogue: 2,1:38:26.45,1:38:31.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,but the game will generate them more frequently and present them to you more obviously
Dialogue: 2,1:38:31.49,1:38:34.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,if it calculates that you are in need of them.
Dialogue: 2,1:38:34.22,1:38:38.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,On higher difficulties, it calculates you as needing less of them.
Dialogue: 2,1:38:38.09,1:38:41.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, it calculates you as needing these items,
Dialogue: 2,1:38:41.51,1:38:45.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,which means that you don't actually have to explore the levels to find the items
Dialogue: 2,1:38:45.65,1:38:47.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,you just have to get to the end of the level,
Dialogue: 2,1:38:47.84,1:38:52.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,at which point there's a software gate before you move on to the next section.
Dialogue: 2,1:38:52.28,1:38:57.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,And before that software gate is going to be a generation of items in certain stashes
Dialogue: 2,1:38:57.89,1:39:00.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,that are going to refill your supplies before you move on.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:00.92,1:39:03.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,But to be honest, I don't think that this is a major issue.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:03.50,1:39:06.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,If anything, it's just a perk for speed runners.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:06.07,1:39:09.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,And to be honest, it probably does more good than it does harm,
Dialogue: 2,1:39:09.64,1:39:14.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it makes it so if players overlooked a certain area that had a lot of gear in it,
Dialogue: 2,1:39:14.18,1:39:16.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,they're not going to be totally screwed over in the next level.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:16.88,1:39:19.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,But after this little jump scare, we keep pushing through.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:19.80,1:39:22.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie fights some Seraphites, or Scars,
Dialogue: 2,1:39:22.64,1:39:25.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,solve some more puzzles, fight some more zombies,
Dialogue: 2,1:39:25.37,1:39:27.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,including some stealth focused zombies
Dialogue: 2,1:39:27.47,1:39:31.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,that could have been an interesting if they weren't so damn stupid.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:31.55,1:39:37.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the peak of this chapter is when we get our first extensive exposure to the Seraphites.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:37.00,1:39:40.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see, they fight differently. They're much more stealthy and careful.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:40.97,1:39:43.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,They communicate also through whistling.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:43.04,1:39:47.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now depending on your sound system, tweaking the audio settings could really work wonders.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:47.70,1:39:52.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seriously, you can figure out where enemies are without needing to use the listen mode at all.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:52.85,1:39:57.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you have a good pair of headphones or a surround sound theater, it's pretty damn cool.
Dialogue: 2,1:39:57.92,1:40:02.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,And from what I can tell there's going to be even more of this type of thing on next gen consoles
Dialogue: 2,1:40:02.57,1:40:06.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,with all of the PlayStation 5 3D audio stuff they're doing.
Dialogue: 2,1:40:06.44,1:40:08.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's really awesome, I can't wait.
Dialogue: 2,1:40:08.58,1:40:13.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now a fun little detail just to prove the point of Naughty Dogs attention to detail
Dialogue: 2,1:40:13.46,1:40:15.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,here as we push up on a bunch of Seraphites.
Dialogue: 2,1:40:15.92,1:40:21.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,If we blow up all of the cult members before they're able to disembowel this man,
Dialogue: 2,1:40:21.11,1:40:22.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,they actually have a backup.
Dialogue: 2,1:40:22.78,1:40:27.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Bear in mind, this is only possible if you happen to have explosive arrows unlocked
Dialogue: 2,1:40:27.20,1:40:28.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,and crafted at this point in the game,
Dialogue: 2,1:40:28.99,1:40:31.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is a long stretch, if you're playing through on the first run,
Dialogue: 2,1:40:31.98,1:40:34.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,so it's more of a new game plus problem.
Dialogue: 2,1:40:34.64,1:40:38.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you do have it unlocked and you blow up all of the cult members
Dialogue: 2,1:40:38.79,1:40:43.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,surrounding this man that's being hung and about to be disemboweled and killed,
Dialogue: 2,1:40:43.88,1:40:49.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,he'll actually just hang and it's a much slower and more aggravated death,
Dialogue: 2,1:40:49.10,1:40:51.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,unless you put him out of his misery.
Dialogue: 2,1:40:51.26,1:40:52.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,I actually tested this,
Dialogue: 2,1:40:52.31,1:40:55.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,where I tried to shoot the rope and cut him down to allow him to escape,
Dialogue: 2,1:40:55.64,1:40:57.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I wasn't able to get it to work.
Dialogue: 2,1:40:57.08,1:41:00.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe there is a way to do it, and I just have bad aim on the shore.
Dialogue: 2,1:41:00.53,1:41:05.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, it's still pretty cool that they have two states available.
Dialogue: 2,1:41:05.38,1:41:09.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,For one, if they are able to finish their little ceremony,
Dialogue: 2,1:41:09.32,1:41:13.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,kill him by hanging and disemboweling at the same time;
Dialogue: 2,1:41:13.70,1:41:18.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then the other case being that you kill them before they are able to disembowel him,
Dialogue: 2,1:41:18.23,1:41:22.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,at which point they just kick the bucket out and he hangs slowly.
Dialogue: 2,1:41:22.40,1:41:28.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now you fight and sneak through multiple levels of these guys finishing on a mini boss fight
Dialogue: 2,1:41:28.76,1:41:34.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,with a big Seraphite Brute, the same one that was seen in the Dina Ellie kiss trailer.
Dialogue: 2,1:41:34.31,1:41:38.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it's a little less polished in this final version, at least in my opinion,
Dialogue: 2,1:41:38.99,1:41:41.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's less fluid, but it's still awesome.
Dialogue: 2,1:41:41.99,1:41:47.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,What I mean by that is that there seems to be a lot less scripted elements and animations.
Dialogue: 2,1:41:47.00,1:41:50.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,But to be honest, you'd probably expect that from a trailer.
Dialogue: 2,1:41:50.09,1:41:52.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now there are grunts in the back room during this fight,
Dialogue: 2,1:41:52.88,1:41:56.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,which actually makes this a really difficult to encounter a new game plus
Dialogue: 2,1:41:56.26,1:42:00.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,considering that I had used all of my ammo by the time that I got here,
Dialogue: 2,1:42:00.65,1:42:04.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,meaning that I had to take him on pretty much entirely with melee.
Dialogue: 2,1:42:04.10,1:42:10.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now one of the frustrations with {\i1}TLOU{\i0} is that it requires a lot of trial and error.
Dialogue: 2,1:42:10.97,1:42:15.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,A lot of the time the only way to figure out exactly how to get through a particular encounter
Dialogue: 2,1:42:15.64,1:42:18.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,is by dying repeatedly and trying again.
Dialogue: 2,1:42:18.65,1:42:21.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,The worst examples would be, for instance, this scene
Dialogue: 2,1:42:21.36,1:42:23.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,where I had to run around into the back room,
Dialogue: 2,1:42:23.69,1:42:28.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,try killing those guys first and then moving outside melee, trying to fight the big brute in the back room,
Dialogue: 2,1:42:28.52,1:42:31.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,trying to fight the big brute in the front room, and then moving to the back room.
Dialogue: 2,1:42:31.70,1:42:35.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,It required a lot of trial and error to figure out the best way to do it.
Dialogue: 2,1:42:35.09,1:42:38.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another example would be when Ellie was trying to get the boat
Dialogue: 2,1:42:38.40,1:42:41.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,in this flooded mall sequence a little bit later.
Dialogue: 2,1:42:41.90,1:42:44.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's visually fascinating as a scene,
Dialogue: 2,1:42:44.63,1:42:49.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,but on Survivor it took around thirty minutes of experimenting to find the path
Dialogue: 2,1:42:49.61,1:42:52.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,that just narrowly dodged everybody's perception.
Dialogue: 2,1:42:52.94,1:42:55.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,And even then I'm not convinced that I should have escaped
Dialogue: 2,1:42:55.84,1:43:01.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,because I got in the boat, started it and was spotted and then shot started coming in,
Dialogue: 2,1:43:01.55,1:43:04.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,at which point a lot of bullets definitely hit Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,1:43:04.94,1:43:08.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she probably should have died, but I was still allowed to escape.
Dialogue: 2,1:43:08.74,1:43:12.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,From what I can tell Naughty Dog tweaked their aim while you're inside this boat
Dialogue: 2,1:43:12.88,1:43:15.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,to make it feel as though you are whizzing past incoming fire.
Dialogue: 2,1:43:15.62,1:43:18.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,But here I actually forgot that the boat controls in this game
Dialogue: 2,1:43:18.83,1:43:22.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,are defaulted to the stupidest lay out possible.
Dialogue: 2,1:43:22.37,1:43:25.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I sat there for a second holding down R2 like a chump
Dialogue: 2,1:43:25.35,1:43:29.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,before I realized that it was all steered using the left stick,
Dialogue: 2,1:43:29.42,1:43:31.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,and by the time I figured it out,
Dialogue: 2,1:43:31.37,1:43:34.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,I definitely should have died, but nonetheless I was allowed to live.
Dialogue: 2,1:43:34.34,1:43:37.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the player and Ellie pushed to the hospital after the fight with the mini boss.
Dialogue: 2,1:43:37.97,1:43:40.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,We stealth our way into the hospital.
Dialogue: 2,1:43:40.04,1:43:45.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,We kill this check that is holding the Vita who we will also see again later in Abby's sections.
Dialogue: 2,1:43:45.92,1:43:49.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, she's only in there for a couple of seconds.
Dialogue: 2,1:43:49.13,1:43:52.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then we find out that WLF are clearing the hospital, which makes sense,
Dialogue: 2,1:43:52.91,1:43:54.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,they want to make sure that there's no infected here,
Dialogue: 2,1:43:54.80,1:43:59.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,but they're also taking all of their supplies back to their headquarters
Dialogue: 2,1:43:59.69,1:44:02.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,for some reason that isn't explained.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:02.21,1:44:06.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,Though we will figure it out later on when we play as Abby.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:06.29,1:44:09.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,But as for right now, all we know is that Isaac, the leader,
Dialogue: 2,1:44:09.65,1:44:14.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,ordered that all of the supplies be returned to the centralized location.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:14.36,1:44:15.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now we go through a bunch of sequences
Dialogue: 2,1:44:15.88,1:44:19.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,where we can either stealth or fight our way through a bunch of WLF.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:19.34,1:44:23.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not particularly important, it's just more of the same.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:23.09,1:44:26.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,But eventually we push up to the top floor and find Nora.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:26.96,1:44:29.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's talking with some other WLF about Abby.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:29.69,1:44:32.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,Apparently she's missing and these WLF think
Dialogue: 2,1:44:32.47,1:44:37.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Nora knows something about where she is headed and how she escaped.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:37.22,1:44:40.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a little confusing for Ellie because as far as Ellie knew,
Dialogue: 2,1:44:40.07,1:44:42.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby was one of the head honchos with the WLF.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:42.68,1:44:45.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why is she being sought out by some of the members?
Dialogue: 2,1:44:45.71,1:44:47.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why was she imprisoned?
Dialogue: 2,1:44:47.21,1:44:52.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why is Nora going to be in trouble if it turns out she knows where Abby is?
Dialogue: 2,1:44:52.97,1:44:55.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's very confusing, but it will make sense later.
Dialogue: 2,1:44:55.76,1:44:57.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,As for the player right now,
Dialogue: 2,1:44:57.02,1:45:01.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,it just seems as though Abby is in some sort of direct conflict with the group.
Dialogue: 2,1:45:01.04,1:45:02.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, for a brief moment,
Dialogue: 2,1:45:02.03,1:45:06.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,I thought that perhaps we were going to pair up with WLF members to hunt Abby down.
Dialogue: 2,1:45:06.92,1:45:09.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, an enemy of our enemy is our friend.
Dialogue: 2,1:45:09.92,1:45:12.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, they're not going to do this.
Dialogue: 2,1:45:12.26,1:45:13.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,You chase Nora through the hospital
Dialogue: 2,1:45:13.79,1:45:17.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,after a brief interaction where she pushes back at Ellie asking:
Dialogue: 2,1:45:38.96,1:45:43.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,You chase her to a dead end with a break in the hallway that leads to the spore filled basement
Dialogue: 2,1:45:43.79,1:45:45.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,as armed guards chase you.
Dialogue: 2,1:45:45.71,1:45:48.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie takes Nora hostage and holds her as a body shield,
Dialogue: 2,1:45:48.20,1:45:49.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,realizing that there's no way out,
Dialogue: 2,1:45:49.91,1:45:53.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that Nora's knowledge of her immunity is of no importance
Dialogue: 2,1:45:53.15,1:45:56.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,since she's going to die from the spores in just a few moments,
Dialogue: 2,1:45:56.45,1:45:58.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie takes Nora into the basement,
Dialogue: 2,1:45:58.31,1:46:02.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,kills some zombies and finds Nora cowering in a dead end hallway.
Dialogue: 2,1:46:02.72,1:46:07.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then this sequence plays out wherein we see Ellie get her hands dirty.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:02.33,1:48:05.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie returns to the theater covered in Nora's blood.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:05.15,1:48:08.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's clearly distressed at what she's just done to figure out where Abby is.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:08.93,1:48:10.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,But she did it.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:10.28,1:48:15.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,And she knows that she's at the aquarium, for some reason.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:15.05,1:48:16.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina helps Ellie Clean up,
Dialogue: 2,1:48:16.85,1:48:19.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's here that we see the first visual example of
Dialogue: 2,1:48:19.18,1:48:22.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,what this revenge pursuit is doing to Ellie, physically.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:22.40,1:48:26.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,We can infer Ellie's mental distress through the dialog and behavior,
Dialogue: 2,1:48:26.09,1:48:28.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it's still largely up to interpretation.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:28.61,1:48:32.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,But these physical injuries are visual and apparent.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:32.93,1:48:34.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a brief and quiet scene.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:34.64,1:48:37.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,And after this touching moment, Ellie and Dina fall asleep,
Dialogue: 2,1:48:37.85,1:48:40.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,which takes us to Seattle Day 3.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:40.49,1:48:42.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,We begin with a flashback to two years earlier
Dialogue: 2,1:48:42.89,1:48:46.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Ellie returned to the hospital from the end of the first game.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:46.08,1:48:50.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,After exploring the hospital, discovering some paper work and eventually recording,
Dialogue: 2,1:48:50.87,1:48:53.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,she finds out what truly happened here.
Dialogue: 2,1:48:53.27,1:48:57.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Joel is forced to tell the truth finally, so as to not lose her forever.
Dialogue: 2,1:52:24.95,1:52:28.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,This marks a significant pivot in Joel and Ellie's relationship.
Dialogue: 2,1:52:28.37,1:52:31.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie is known for a long time that Joel was being less than truthful.
Dialogue: 2,1:52:31.55,1:52:32.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,She had her suspicions.
Dialogue: 2,1:52:32.90,1:52:35.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, even with those suspicions,
Dialogue: 2,1:52:35.15,1:52:39.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,she still gave Joel the benefit of the doubt so as to not wreck their relationship.
Dialogue: 2,1:52:39.50,1:52:44.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, now, with the truth fully released out into the open air, Ellie feels betrayed.
Dialogue: 2,1:52:44.81,1:52:47.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everything she feared is true.
Dialogue: 2,1:52:47.18,1:52:51.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the odds of successfully making a vaccine were not particularly high,
Dialogue: 2,1:52:51.95,1:52:56.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially considering how incompetent the Fireflies were throughout the entire first game.
Dialogue: 2,1:52:56.93,1:52:59.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, it's important to note that with this revelation,
Dialogue: 2,1:52:59.75,1:53:02.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's made clear to Ellie that the odds were not zero.
Dialogue: 2,1:53:02.93,1:53:06.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sure, they might not have been great, but they weren't zero.
Dialogue: 2,1:53:06.11,1:53:10.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,That places a huge burden on Ellie shoulders, where she feels a duty to humanity,
Dialogue: 2,1:53:10.73,1:53:17.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,to give her life so that others can live and so that humanity could potentially build itself back up.
Dialogue: 2,1:53:17.03,1:53:20.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's an interesting question, especially when you put yourself into her shoes.
Dialogue: 2,1:53:20.75,1:53:23.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,What if you were in Ellie's position in this world?
Dialogue: 2,1:53:23.81,1:53:28.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,What if your life held the answer to the cure for all of this?
Dialogue: 2,1:53:28.67,1:53:33.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,All of the misery could be fixed if you were to sacrifice your life.
Dialogue: 2,1:53:33.44,1:53:38.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now there is an emphasis on COULD because there's no guarantee that it would actually work.
Dialogue: 2,1:53:38.06,1:53:41.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,And even if a vaccine were successfully developed,
Dialogue: 2,1:53:41.39,1:53:46.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,who's to say that anyone would be able to distribute that vaccine throughout the planet?
Dialogue: 2,1:53:46.07,1:53:51.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, one of the big focuses in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} is the fact that the world has gone to absolute hell.
Dialogue: 2,1:53:51.62,1:53:55.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,People betray each other left and right for seemingly no reason at all.
Dialogue: 2,1:53:55.61,1:54:00.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,Trust is something that basically doesn't exist in this world any more.
Dialogue: 2,1:54:00.05,1:54:03.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,And without a doubt, if somebody were to waltz up to the front of your complex,
Dialogue: 2,1:54:03.80,1:54:08.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,claiming that they had the vaccine, the cure to the Cordyceps fungus,
Dialogue: 2,1:54:08.15,1:54:13.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,chances are you would be highly skeptical and wouldn't allow them into the base at all.
Dialogue: 2,1:54:13.13,1:54:18.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,The point is, I understand that Ellie is frustrated that choice was removed from her,
Dialogue: 2,1:54:18.26,1:54:21.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that decision was made for her.
Dialogue: 2,1:54:21.08,1:54:25.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, even with that being the case, it doesn't change the reality
Dialogue: 2,1:54:25.28,1:54:29.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,that this decision is not as simple as cure versus no cure,
Dialogue: 2,1:54:29.40,1:54:33.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,or Ellie saving humanity versus not saving humanity.
Dialogue: 2,1:54:33.35,1:54:37.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Nothing is that simple. Nothing is black and white in this world.
Dialogue: 2,1:54:37.70,1:54:42.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,Perhaps for purposes of general analysis within the story of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}
Dialogue: 2,1:54:42.38,1:54:46.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,you could point at Joel's actions and say that he damned humanity
Dialogue: 2,1:54:46.10,1:54:50.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,for the sake of saving one individual that he cared greatly about.
Dialogue: 2,1:54:50.24,1:54:54.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, I think there's two sides to the coin and you could say that
Dialogue: 2,1:54:54.25,1:55:00.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,even if they were able to develop some sort of vaccine, it wouldn't have actually gone anywhere,
Dialogue: 2,1:55:00.59,1:55:04.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,or at the very least it would have been contained within a very small community.
Dialogue: 2,1:55:04.37,1:55:08.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,But at the same time you could also say that if that were the case
Dialogue: 2,1:55:08.25,1:55:13.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,and if the vaccine were only used within the Fireflies or the WLF
Dialogue: 2,1:55:13.20,1:55:17.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,as they eventually became after being splintered across the country,
Dialogue: 2,1:55:17.66,1:55:21.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,then you could say that Ellie sacrifice would have been worth it
Dialogue: 2,1:55:21.09,1:55:25.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,because she could have saved dozens or perhaps hundreds or even thousands of lives.
Dialogue: 2,1:55:25.64,1:55:30.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sure, it's less than millions or billions, but none the less that's a significant number.
Dialogue: 2,1:55:30.17,1:55:34.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,The broader point is that Ellie feels as though this choice was made for her,
Dialogue: 2,1:55:34.19,1:55:35.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it was,
Dialogue: 2,1:55:35.51,1:55:37.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she feels as though Joel betrayed her,
Dialogue: 2,1:55:37.64,1:55:41.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially considering that he's been lying to her about it for years.
Dialogue: 2,1:55:41.84,1:55:45.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,But after this flashback, we cut back to Ellie waking up in the theater,
Dialogue: 2,1:55:45.29,1:55:47.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she goes looking for Jesse and Dina.
Dialogue: 2,1:55:47.66,1:55:50.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,After a brief conversation about Dina's pregnancy,
Dialogue: 2,1:55:50.36,1:55:53.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie and Jesse decided to push out towards the aquarium together.
Dialogue: 2,1:55:53.84,1:55:56.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,They think that Abby is likely hiding out there.
Dialogue: 2,1:55:56.81,1:55:58.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,They don't know why she would be there,
Dialogue: 2,1:55:58.67,1:56:04.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they don't know why she would be running from or have reason to be afraid of the WLF.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:04.82,1:56:08.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, they seemed to be the group that she originated from.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:08.33,1:56:12.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,So at the very least it should get the player intrigued as to what actually happened.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:12.44,1:56:13.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,When I first played the game,
Dialogue: 2,1:56:13.52,1:56:16.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,I thought, perhaps it was that they were acting out against her
Dialogue: 2,1:56:16.32,1:56:20.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,after she took this group AWOL to go and find Joel.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:20.24,1:56:22.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, that doesn't actually make much sense,
Dialogue: 2,1:56:22.43,1:56:26.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,considering that all of the other people that went with her on that trip
Dialogue: 2,1:56:26.20,1:56:29.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,seemed to be operating in their regular profession just fine.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:29.42,1:56:30.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,So at the end of the day,
Dialogue: 2,1:56:30.95,1:56:35.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,all we're left with is a suspicious absence on Abby's part from the group
Dialogue: 2,1:56:35.48,1:56:39.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,and lots of gossip that's overheard between the characters.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:39.23,1:56:42.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless Ellie and Jesse push up towards the aquarium.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:42.48,1:56:45.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the section in my opinion, is actually pretty unremarkable.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:45.95,1:56:48.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's not a lot of interesting fight sequences here,
Dialogue: 2,1:56:48.32,1:56:52.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,and more broadly, it's just served as a chance for Ellie and Jesse
Dialogue: 2,1:56:52.28,1:56:55.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,to get all of the drama about Dina's pregnancy out on the table.
Dialogue: 2,1:56:55.73,1:57:00.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,Over the course of the sequence, they determined that she has to return to Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:00.50,1:57:01.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's no other way.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:01.60,1:57:07.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,If she is to receive any semblance of healthcare in the lead up to the delivery of the child,
Dialogue: 2,1:57:07.37,1:57:10.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's going to need to return to where they came from.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:10.07,1:57:13.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,This, in turn means that this is likely their last chance to find Abby,
Dialogue: 2,1:57:13.73,1:57:15.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,because once they find Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,1:57:15.53,1:57:18.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,they're all going to pack up and head back to Jackson together.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:18.50,1:57:24.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Chances are Jesse and Dina, and especially Tommy, are not going to allow Ellie to remain.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:24.06,1:57:26.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Jesse knows that it's his baby.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:26.18,1:57:29.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's heard that Dina hasn't told him that she's pregnant yet.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:29.74,1:57:35.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's keeping it a secret, which seems kind of stupid, but I guess that's just me.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:35.42,1:57:38.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, the motivations have shifted.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:38.27,1:57:43.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Jesse is not as concerned about finding Abby and getting revenge.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:43.07,1:57:47.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Rather, he's looking for Tommy so that they can all return to Jackson together
Dialogue: 2,1:57:47.15,1:57:49.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,whereas Ellie claims the same.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:49.01,1:57:53.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, she is much more concerned with finding Abby as we'll see in just a moment.
Dialogue: 2,1:57:53.87,1:57:59.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,This whole climaxes when Jesse and Ellie here over a radio that there's a sniper on the pier,
Dialogue: 2,1:57:59.18,1:58:03.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's taking out a bunch of WLF members in causing trouble more generally.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:03.56,1:58:05.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Jesse and Ellie determined that this has to be Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:05.93,1:58:10.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's actually a fair point because the WLF wouldn't be sniping themselves.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:10.85,1:58:16.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the Scars don't actually use sniper rifles in this way, so it's likely not them.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:16.85,1:58:19.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it's either Tommy or another rogue individual
Dialogue: 2,1:58:19.90,1:58:23.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,who happens to just be sniping WLF members for fun.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:23.45,1:58:26.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,And of course it ends up being Tommy at the end of the day,
Dialogue: 2,1:58:26.51,1:58:30.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it's here that we see Ellie make a decision that's much harder to justify.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:30.47,1:58:35.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,She insists that Tommy is going to be OK by himself and that he doesn't need her help.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:35.48,1:58:39.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,While this is perhaps true, it's more the thought that counts.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:39.32,1:58:41.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, Tommy has made it this long.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:41.30,1:58:43.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the fact that he sniping WLF members
Dialogue: 2,1:58:43.96,1:58:48.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,shows that he's at least somewhat confident in his abilities to deal with them.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:48.32,1:58:54.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, Ellie isn't saying this because she wants to protect Jesse or herself, or Dina's well being.
Dialogue: 2,1:58:54.85,1:59:00.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Rather, she's seeing it purely because she wants to get to Abby quickly, kill her,
Dialogue: 2,1:59:00.08,1:59:04.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then be able to leave with Tommy, Jesse and Dina back to Jackson,
Dialogue: 2,1:59:04.58,1:59:07.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,having accomplished everything she set out to do.
Dialogue: 2,1:59:07.16,1:59:08.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know about you guys,
Dialogue: 2,1:59:08.45,1:59:09.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,but when I first played the game,
Dialogue: 2,1:59:09.98,1:59:14.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,this was the moment that I immediately lost all sympathy for Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,1:59:14.81,1:59:19.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point, she's making, what seems to me, the wrong decision.
Dialogue: 2,1:59:19.28,1:59:27.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's potentially damning all of those that she seems to love, for her own selfish pursuit,
Dialogue: 2,1:59:27.77,1:59:31.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is thematically related to what Joel did in the first game,
Dialogue: 2,1:59:31.34,1:59:35.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,where he seemingly screwed over humanity to serve his own private interests.
Dialogue: 2,1:59:35.84,1:59:38.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,And once again, this is something that they do time and time again
Dialogue: 2,1:59:38.87,1:59:40.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,throughout the course of the game.
Dialogue: 2,1:59:40.55,1:59:47.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's parallels all over the course mirror sequences that are meant to echo what happened previously.
Dialogue: 2,1:59:47.48,1:59:48.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's all over the place.
Dialogue: 2,1:59:48.71,1:59:52.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Needless to say, Jesse is just as disappointed in Ellie for this decision
Dialogue: 2,1:59:52.70,1:59:55.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,as the player is likely disappointed in her.
Dialogue: 2,1:59:55.55,1:59:58.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,So he breaks off and goes to find Tommy
Dialogue: 2,1:59:58.33,2:00:01.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,and help him get back to the theater so that they can all leave together.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:01.55,2:00:03.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, Ellie splits off alone.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:03.50,2:00:06.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,And she fights for a boat that she saw driving through a canal
Dialogue: 2,2:00:06.80,2:00:09.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,that she hopes to take to the aquarium that's across the harbour.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:09.98,2:00:14.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now this sequence is super tough and especially in higher difficulties.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:14.51,2:00:18.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,It requires an almost exclusively stealth approach.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:18.35,2:00:22.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, thankfully, the designers seem to have anticipated this fact,
Dialogue: 2,2:00:22.49,2:00:25.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why most of the levels have secret passageways
Dialogue: 2,2:00:25.56,2:00:28.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,that you can find to get around most of the enemies
Dialogue: 2,2:00:28.59,2:00:32.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that you either don't have to kill any of them to get through to the next checkpoint,
Dialogue: 2,2:00:32.87,2:00:35.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,or you only have to kill a select few.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:35.78,2:00:40.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,In my opinion, these are the best designed levels in the entirety of the game.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:40.64,2:00:46.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's where the stealth mechanics really shine, and {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} is at its best.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:46.22,2:00:48.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you continue pushing to the aquarium
Dialogue: 2,2:00:48.71,2:00:52.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you fight your way through several waves of Seraphites,
Dialogue: 2,2:00:52.10,2:00:55.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,take on a Bloater or two, and you solve some environmental puzzles.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:55.76,2:00:58.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,Nothing too difficult, but none the less they're there.
Dialogue: 2,2:00:58.40,2:01:00.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,You eventually get your boat to the mouth of the harbour
Dialogue: 2,2:01:00.72,2:01:04.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you start heading towards the shore over by the aquarium.
Dialogue: 2,2:01:04.28,2:01:07.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's at this point that Ellie's overtaken with a rogue wave and almost drowned,
Dialogue: 2,2:01:07.94,2:01:12.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,but ends up just barely escaping to the shore of the aquarium outcrop.
Dialogue: 2,2:01:12.05,2:01:17.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I will just say this whole sequence is done so smoothly and beautifully well.
Dialogue: 2,2:01:17.57,2:01:19.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,I can't complemented enough.
Dialogue: 2,2:01:19.82,2:01:21.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm not a game developer myself,
Dialogue: 2,2:01:21.56,2:01:28.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I have delved into a lot of the intricacies involved with designing levels and managing memory systems
Dialogue: 2,2:01:28.06,2:01:31.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,to see what they're able to do throughout the course of this game,
Dialogue: 2,2:01:31.25,2:01:34.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,and especially this sequence is absolutely ridiculous,
Dialogue: 2,2:01:34.43,2:01:38.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I have to applaud all of the developers over a Naughty Dog for their hard work.
Dialogue: 2,2:01:38.42,2:01:39.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,But with that out of the way,
Dialogue: 2,2:01:39.74,2:01:43.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie pushes into the aquarium and finds a few strange things.
Dialogue: 2,2:01:43.52,2:01:45.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are several doors locked,
Dialogue: 2,2:01:45.29,2:01:50.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,there's lights on and there's bloody instruments strewn across an operation table.
Dialogue: 2,2:01:50.32,2:01:52.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,With the context we have in the game so far,
Dialogue: 2,2:01:52.64,2:01:57.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,we assume that there must have been some strange torture session going on here and nothing more.
Dialogue: 2,2:01:57.83,2:02:02.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, as we'll see later, this wasn't as terrible as it seems.
Dialogue: 2,2:02:02.69,2:02:06.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie climbs into an air duct, and then the following sequence plays out.
Dialogue: 2,2:02:37.04,2:02:39.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,This dog may seem like it's just another dog.
Dialogue: 2,2:02:39.71,2:02:44.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, it was shown off in the trailers, as just some mud that you put down.
Dialogue: 2,2:02:44.15,2:02:47.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we're going to see a lot more of her later.
Dialogue: 2,2:02:47.13,2:02:51.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie recovers, but here's some muffled voices through a double door,
Dialogue: 2,2:02:51.59,2:02:54.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,She pushes through, and the following happens.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:03.59,2:06:07.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Needless to say, this is a deeply upsetting sequence.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:07.67,2:06:10.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's one that I personally saw coming a mile away.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:10.61,2:06:13.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see one thing I do know about the writer's over a Naughty Dog,
Dialogue: 2,2:06:13.37,2:06:15.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially Neil Druckmann and Halley Gross,
Dialogue: 2,2:06:15.47,2:06:17.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,is that they love their similes.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:17.83,2:06:20.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,They loved the reflections between characters.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:20.36,2:06:24.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,It gives you a chance to see how these two different people respond to similar situations.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:24.92,2:06:30.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so whenever you start to see things that are similar or things that characters have in common,
Dialogue: 2,2:06:30.20,2:06:32.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,you have to assume that the developers and writers
Dialogue: 2,2:06:32.57,2:06:38.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,are going to force those two characters into a similar situation where those similarities can come out.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:38.18,2:06:42.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this case, Ellie's girlfriend, Dina, is pregnant.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:42.29,2:06:46.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,And one of the first things that we hear about Owen and Abby's group in general
Dialogue: 2,2:06:46.83,2:06:48.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,is that Mel is pregnant.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:48.87,2:06:51.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point in the game we don't know who Mel is
Dialogue: 2,2:06:51.83,2:06:55.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,when we're standing on this snowy hillside overlooking Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,2:06:55.49,2:06:58.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I personally knew that there was a very good chance
Dialogue: 2,2:06:58.67,2:07:02.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Ellie would end up killing her pregnant friend Mel
Dialogue: 2,2:07:02.28,2:07:05.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,simply because Dina was likely going to end a pregnant as well.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:05.78,2:07:08.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,And sure enough, when Dina is revealed to be pregnant,
Dialogue: 2,2:07:08.69,2:07:10.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,this point was solidified for me.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:10.47,2:07:15.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now besides the predictability of this plot point, I have to ask one other question,
Dialogue: 2,2:07:15.02,2:07:20.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is whether or not Ellie would have actually killed Owen and Mel if they had tattled on Abby.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:20.93,2:07:24.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,And given what we know about Ellie in this game,
Dialogue: 2,2:07:24.53,2:07:27.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think the odds are pretty good that she probably would have.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:27.60,2:07:31.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's horrible to say, but Ellie was here for revenge.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:31.70,2:07:36.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,She knows that these people were there, even though technically she owes her life to Owen.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:36.36,2:07:40.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,Owen is the one that stepped in when Ellie was on the floor, staring at Joel's corpse.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:40.61,2:07:44.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,While everyone else wanted to kill her to clean up after themselves,
Dialogue: 2,2:07:44.06,2:07:46.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,which objectively probably would have been the smarter thing to do,
Dialogue: 2,2:07:46.97,2:07:49.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially considering how {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} plays out.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:49.91,2:07:53.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, she technically owes her life to Owen.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:53.69,2:07:56.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even so, I think she would have killed him.
Dialogue: 2,2:07:56.15,2:08:00.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,The other question that you have to ask is where is Abby and what happened.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:00.14,2:08:01.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Where did she go?
Dialogue: 2,2:08:01.22,2:08:04.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,How long is it going to be before she finds out what Ellie is done?
Dialogue: 2,2:08:04.91,2:08:07.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why did she leave in the first place?
Dialogue: 2,2:08:07.19,2:08:09.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it's implied that she's fleeing from Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:09.77,2:08:12.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, this doesn't really make a lot of sense,
Dialogue: 2,2:08:12.62,2:08:16.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially when you consider that she's already fleeing something else.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:16.82,2:08:22.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems as though she's involved in something that's taking her away from her duties within the WLF,
Dialogue: 2,2:08:22.25,2:08:24.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why Isaac seems to be upset with her.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:24.44,2:08:28.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, I think Naughty Dog is trying to keep the story moving along
Dialogue: 2,2:08:28.28,2:08:33.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that you don't think about it long enough to realize that there's got to be more to it.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:33.08,2:08:34.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,And honestly, I'm okay with that.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:34.67,2:08:38.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Especially because Ellie herself isn't particularly interested
Dialogue: 2,2:08:38.48,2:08:42.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,in the reasons why Abby is going to the places she's going
Dialogue: 2,2:08:42.04,2:08:45.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,or why Abby seems to be at odds with the rest of her group.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:45.53,2:08:47.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,All she's interested in is revenge.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:47.96,2:08:50.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the last thing about this sequence is that I can't help but feel as though
Dialogue: 2,2:08:50.97,2:08:57.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's a little strange that Tommy, Jesse and Ellie just leave after this.
Dialogue: 2,2:08:57.11,2:09:01.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,They see the dead bodies on the floor, and don't do anything more.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:01.64,2:09:04.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,That rhymed, I didn't mean it to rhyme.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:04.19,2:09:06.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but I'm… you know what we're leaving it in.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:06.74,2:09:08.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not demanding an elaborate sequence
Dialogue: 2,2:09:08.83,2:09:12.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,where we clear the entire aquarium of any sort of bogey
Dialogue: 2,2:09:12.50,2:09:16.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,to make sure that Abby is not some were hiding within the aquarium.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:16.04,2:09:17.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,But at the very least,
Dialogue: 2,2:09:17.84,2:09:22.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,it seems odd that they wouldn't have done a more elaborate check throughout the rest of the building.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:22.07,2:09:27.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,They just find Ellie, and clearly she's pretty shaken up about what she has just done.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:27.62,2:09:29.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,But they just leave.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:29.36,2:09:33.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,Perhaps at this point, they have just accepted that they're not going to find Abby.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:33.29,2:09:35.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's not destined to be.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:35.12,2:09:37.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that they've done enough damage that they've made their point.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:37.93,2:09:43.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, the scenes after this are actually quite calm and it's fairly refreshing.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:43.55,2:09:46.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,We see Ellie in bed with Dina, and they're just resting.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:46.92,2:09:50.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,After a while Ellie goes, and talks with Jesse and Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,2:09:50.21,2:09:52.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,trying to determine the best route back to Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,2:09:52.97,2:09:56.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,They've officially determined that they can't stay and find Abby,
Dialogue: 2,2:09:56.21,2:10:00.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,but rather need to get Dina somewhere safe for the sake of her unborn child.
Dialogue: 2,2:10:00.44,2:10:03.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,All is normal, until this…
Dialogue: 2,2:11:12.26,2:11:16.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is a stunningly sudden and sharp narrative beat.
Dialogue: 2,2:11:16.34,2:11:20.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,I knew something was coming, but I didn't know that it would happen this suddenly.
Dialogue: 2,2:11:20.61,2:11:25.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Jesse's death happens almost instantaneously as the cut scene begins,
Dialogue: 2,2:11:25.91,2:11:31.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,there's no warning, there was no forethought, it simply happens and Jesse's dead.
Dialogue: 2,2:11:31.76,2:11:36.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's also a problem with what the fuc… what it…  What is that?
Dialogue: 2,2:11:36.20,2:11:39.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,What it… That's gross. Stop it, OK, OK, a slight detour.
Dialogue: 2,2:11:39.74,2:11:42.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,I know this is a serious scene and it's sad and everything.
Dialogue: 2,2:11:42.41,2:11:46.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it was almost completely ruined because the first time that I play through the game,
Dialogue: 2,2:11:46.67,2:11:49.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie has a bandage on her arm.
Dialogue: 2,2:11:49.31,2:11:51.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not actually supposed to be there.
Dialogue: 2,2:11:51.32,2:11:54.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's from the previous sequence when she patched herself up.
Dialogue: 2,2:11:54.56,2:12:01.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, it did something strange where it's warped the actual mesh of her arm.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:01.13,2:12:06.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it looks that she has some sort of weird noodle bone disease.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:06.62,2:12:11.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,It… it's bizarre and I wouldn't complain about it,
Dialogue: 2,2:12:11.87,2:12:16.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,except that when I went back through the game on new game plus
Dialogue: 2,2:12:16.29,2:12:19.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,it didn't happen and her arm looked normal.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:19.04,2:12:21.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I can tell that this was a glitch.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:21.02,2:12:26.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just a really, really weird one that I don't really know what to make of.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:26.15,2:12:28.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless it… it happened,
Dialogue: 2,2:12:28.16,2:12:33.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I am going to have nightmares about this weird T-Rex arm that she has.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:33.14,2:12:36.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless it happened, hopefully this didn't happen to you,
Dialogue: 2,2:12:36.62,2:12:42.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,but for me it almost spoiled the entire scene because I found myself giggling at her messed up arm.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:42.53,2:12:44.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,But… you know, I'll leave it there.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:44.86,2:12:48.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now this marks the end of the first half of the game.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:48.24,2:12:50.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,And don't worry, we're going to discuss midpoint thoughts
Dialogue: 2,2:12:50.97,2:12:56.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,and where I was at in my play through, what my emotions were, what I thought of everything.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:56.06,2:12:58.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,But first, I want to go through the next scene.
Dialogue: 2,2:12:58.11,2:13:05.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see right after Abby kills Jesse, seemingly kills Tommy, and is holding Ellie at gunpoint,
Dialogue: 2,2:13:05.66,2:13:11.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,we jump to a clip of a young, non-yoked Abby.
Dialogue: 2,2:13:11.09,2:13:15.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's looking for her dad, who is in turn looking for some animal,
Dialogue: 2,2:13:15.47,2:13:18.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,that turns out to be a zebra that's just given birth.
Dialogue: 2,2:13:18.77,2:13:24.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's cute, and it's a nice break from the dread that the last ten hours have brought.
Dialogue: 2,2:13:24.06,2:13:29.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seriously I didn't realize how much of a trudge the first half of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} felt like
Dialogue: 2,2:13:29.93,2:13:34.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,until we got to the sequence and it felt like something straight out of the first game.
Dialogue: 2,2:13:34.73,2:13:42.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie, God bless her, is a really difficult person to relate to in this sequel, at least for me.
Dialogue: 2,2:13:42.03,2:13:44.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the first game, there was something really human about her,
Dialogue: 2,2:13:44.63,2:13:48.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,something that was reflective of all of us.
Dialogue: 2,2:13:48.44,2:13:53.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,We can all connect with her and we can all connect with Joel in some weird, distant way.
Dialogue: 2,2:13:53.45,2:13:57.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, in the second game, there's not much of that to be seen or had.
Dialogue: 2,2:13:57.89,2:14:02.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless I can't help but feel as though Ellie is painfully unlikable in the sequel,
Dialogue: 2,2:14:02.21,2:14:07.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why it's all the more bizarre to go through the first half of the game with Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,2:14:07.85,2:14:12.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,where you don't particularly like her, or condone any thing that she's doing.
Dialogue: 2,2:14:12.59,2:14:17.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then you reach this point after this character you're playing as Abby
Dialogue: 2,2:14:17.10,2:14:24.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,has killed characters that you really began to respect and enjoy and even love.
Dialogue: 2,2:14:24.92,2:14:31.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,But now you find yourself relating to her and liking her personality way more than Ellie's.
Dialogue: 2,2:14:31.19,2:14:35.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's really bizarre and I think it was half intentional and half not.
Dialogue: 2,2:14:35.66,2:14:41.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,What I mean is that I think Abby's relatability and likability, was completely intentional,
Dialogue: 2,2:14:41.30,2:14:46.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,that I don't think that Ellie's lack of likability was completely intended.
Dialogue: 2,2:14:46.40,2:14:52.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now of course, at this point in the game, players for the most part are going to hate Abby.
Dialogue: 2,2:14:52.04,2:14:53.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't blame them.
Dialogue: 2,2:14:53.51,2:14:58.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,She killed Joel, one of the most beloved characters in gaming history.
Dialogue: 2,2:14:58.46,2:15:03.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I understand that frustration that now we are forced to play as her.
Dialogue: 2,2:15:03.20,2:15:05.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, they want you to give Abby a chance,
Dialogue: 2,2:15:05.57,2:15:10.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why they rewind the clock to four years before the events of this game.
Dialogue: 2,2:15:10.40,2:15:11.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, as I mentioned earlier,
Dialogue: 2,2:15:11.69,2:15:16.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,I conducted a massive poll of all of you guys to see what you thought of the game,
Dialogue: 2,2:15:16.82,2:15:20.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,and whether or not you felt as though it lived up to your expectations.
Dialogue: 2,2:15:20.51,2:15:22.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if it didn't, what it could have done better.
Dialogue: 2,2:15:22.73,2:15:26.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,There were several dozens of questions involved in the survey,
Dialogue: 2,2:15:26.69,2:15:31.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,so I'm not going to go through all of them, but I will include a Excel spreadsheet
Dialogue: 2,2:15:31.28,2:15:35.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,that you can actually use to sift through all of the answers yourself if you would like to.
Dialogue: 2,2:15:35.66,2:15:38.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's actually a lot of really interesting information in here,
Dialogue: 2,2:15:38.24,2:15:41.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I've spent the better part of a week sifting through a lot of the responses,
Dialogue: 2,2:15:41.81,2:15:44.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,because there's a lot of really good stuff here.
Dialogue: 2,2:15:44.66,2:15:46.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,But one of the things that I was stunned to realize
Dialogue: 2,2:15:46.99,2:15:51.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,is that a lot of people actually gave up on the game at this point.
Dialogue: 2,2:15:51.26,2:15:55.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,They got through the first half of the game enjoyed Ellie's sections for the most part,
Dialogue: 2,2:15:55.55,2:15:59.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,but once they saw that they are going to be forced to play as Abby,
Dialogue: 2,2:15:59.03,2:16:02.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,they felt betrayed and stopped playing completely.
Dialogue: 2,2:16:02.36,2:16:07.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I was going to show some direct quotations from some of the gamers that expressed this frustration.
Dialogue: 2,2:16:07.46,2:16:13.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, many of them had too much profanity for me to comfortably include in this video
Dialogue: 2,2:16:13.70,2:16:16.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,with any hopes of getting monetized at the end of the day.
Dialogue: 2,2:16:16.46,2:16:19.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I am simply going to paraphrase.
Dialogue: 2,2:16:19.13,2:16:23.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if you want to read the actual word for word responses again,
Dialogue: 2,2:16:23.27,2:16:27.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'll have the entire survey and all of the responses linked below.
Dialogue: 2,2:16:27.56,2:16:31.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,In general, the people that quit the game at this point felt as though
Dialogue: 2,2:16:31.60,2:16:36.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,they were being forced to relate to somebody that had no interest in relating to.
Dialogue: 2,2:16:36.00,2:16:38.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's kind of a bizarre idea when you think about it,
Dialogue: 2,2:16:38.90,2:16:42.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,that somebody would be so upset that they would have to relate to somebody
Dialogue: 2,2:16:42.61,2:16:45.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they would turn off the game entirely and walk away.
Dialogue: 2,2:16:45.26,2:16:46.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,But here we are.
Dialogue: 2,2:16:46.97,2:16:50.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,If anything, it could be construed as a compliment to the character building
Dialogue: 2,2:16:50.92,2:16:56.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the relatability and care that people felt towards Joel initially,
Dialogue: 2,2:16:56.19,2:17:01.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they are so loyal to him and this imaginary character that he represents
Dialogue: 2,2:17:01.97,2:17:08.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they won't even give the time of day effectively to the character that brought on his demise.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:08.84,2:17:14.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I completely understand how polarizing this decision was on Naughty Dog's part.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:14.08,2:17:15.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,It would have been a very early decision
Dialogue: 2,2:17:15.76,2:17:20.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,in the development process to have Abby and Ellie costars of this game,
Dialogue: 2,2:17:20.08,2:17:24.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,to the point where they're both playable for roughly half of the game each.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:24.23,2:17:30.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,And thankfully it seems to have for the most part, been done fairly well, at least in my opinion.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:30.47,2:17:34.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,I understand that some people who disagree with the thematic decision at the outset.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:34.70,2:17:38.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that's not really the question. the question is whether or not it was well executed.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:38.69,2:17:40.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, once we've gotten through Abby sections,
Dialogue: 2,2:17:40.73,2:17:43.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'll be able to talk a lot more about whether or not I feel as though
Dialogue: 2,2:17:43.76,2:17:48.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,they struck a good balance in trying to present both characters equally.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:48.95,2:17:53.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think the biggest problem with {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} has to do was its pace.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:53.09,2:17:59.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,It gets really easy to doze off and lose focus, especially in the last third of the game.
Dialogue: 2,2:17:59.45,2:18:04.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} asks a lot of the player.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:04.01,2:18:09.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not that easy actually to stay intrigued and involved in everything that's going on,
Dialogue: 2,2:18:09.74,2:18:12.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially because it's so emotionally taxing.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:12.59,2:18:15.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we're going to get into all of that a little bit later.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:15.32,2:18:16.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,As you go through this sequence,
Dialogue: 2,2:18:16.55,2:18:19.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,you eventually find the zebra that's been trapped in some barbed wire,
Dialogue: 2,2:18:19.91,2:18:24.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Abby helps her father with Owen's assistance cut her loose.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:24.65,2:18:27.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,She runs off in cuddles with her newborn in a field
Dialogue: 2,2:18:27.30,2:18:32.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,directly across from the hospital that we saw at the end of the first game, St. Mary's.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:32.81,2:18:36.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Their group is informed that Marlin's girl just arrived
Dialogue: 2,2:18:36.21,2:18:40.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that it seems as though she actually is immune as they were initially told.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:40.85,2:18:42.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is, of course, Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:42.56,2:18:44.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just as she was found at the end of the first game,
Dialogue: 2,2:18:44.93,2:18:48.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,we then cut to Marlin from the first game, arguing with Abby's dad
Dialogue: 2,2:18:48.74,2:18:52.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,about whether or not to perform the operation that could lead to a vaccine.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:52.37,2:18:54.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's actually the conversation that we always wanted to hear.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:54.92,2:18:56.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see Abby's dad wants to do it.
Dialogue: 2,2:18:56.93,2:19:00.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,He feels as though the sacrifice of Ellie is going to be worth it
Dialogue: 2,2:19:00.07,2:19:03.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it could potentially save thousands or even millions of lives.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:03.80,2:19:07.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,The problem is that they can't afford to ask Ellie or Joel.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:07.82,2:19:10.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,They have to do it and ask for forgiveness.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:10.52,2:19:13.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,If they were to ask Ellie, she would likely say yes.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:13.76,2:19:17.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if they were to ask Joel, he would likely say no.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:17.15,2:19:21.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,And as we found out, he would also likely go berserk.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:21.53,2:19:26.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's at the end of this discussion that Abby comes in the room, bringing her father some dinner.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:26.06,2:19:29.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,And she offers a fairly interesting anecdote.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:46.64,2:19:51.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Immediately after this, we cut to black and we transitioned the Abby running into the operating room.
Dialogue: 2,2:19:51.68,2:19:53.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Finding her dad, dead.
Dialogue: 2,2:20:15.02,2:20:18.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is why Abby wanted to kill Joel.
Dialogue: 2,2:20:18.29,2:20:23.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,This made all the clear by the immediate cut to Joel's death to reaffirm the point.
Dialogue: 2,2:20:23.30,2:20:25.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,It may seem a little ham fisted, but I actually really like this,
Dialogue: 2,2:20:25.82,2:20:29.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,because now we can hear this sequence without the murmur and drowning out
Dialogue: 2,2:20:29.56,2:20:31.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,that we had the first time that we saw it.
Dialogue: 2,2:20:31.82,2:20:36.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now we can hear the entire conversation, the debate that goes back and forth.
Dialogue: 2,2:21:24.56,2:21:27.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is the midpoint of the game, really.
Dialogue: 2,2:21:27.62,2:21:30.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,As far as we can tell, we're done playing as Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,2:21:30.95,2:21:34.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,The next sequence pops up with "Seattle Day 1",
Dialogue: 2,2:21:34.10,2:21:38.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,implying that we're going to be going back through the entirety of what we just did with Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,2:21:38.57,2:21:40.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,but from Abby's perspective.
Dialogue: 2,2:21:40.73,2:21:41.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's an interesting flip,
Dialogue: 2,2:21:41.98,2:21:48.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the change of perspective is, after all, the operative narrative element of this entire game's design.
Dialogue: 2,2:21:48.80,2:21:53.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I can't help but feel as though many players are going to already be exhausted
Dialogue: 2,2:21:53.28,2:21:55.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,from the journey that they just endeavored on.
Dialogue: 2,2:21:55.67,2:21:59.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is why at this point in the game, pace is more important than ever.
Dialogue: 2,2:21:59.12,2:22:01.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,You have to keep the player engaged,
Dialogue: 2,2:22:01.25,2:22:04.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially because many of us probably felt as though
Dialogue: 2,2:22:04.36,2:22:07.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,we had just played through an entire game by itself.
Dialogue: 2,2:22:07.16,2:22:12.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,And now you're asking us to play through another game with another character,
Dialogue: 2,2:22:12.68,2:22:15.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,but in this case, the villain, as far as we're concerned,
Dialogue: 2,2:22:15.72,2:22:19.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you want us to give her the same time of day and attention that we give Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,2:22:19.85,2:22:23.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,a character that we have a deep relationship built up with
Dialogue: 2,2:22:23.10,2:22:26.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,after having played a game with her back in 2013.
Dialogue: 2,2:22:26.93,2:22:28.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,It really is a lot to ask,
Dialogue: 2,2:22:28.46,2:22:32.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I don't really blame a lot of players that decided to walk away at this point.
Dialogue: 2,2:22:32.75,2:22:36.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sure, they may never get the actual story resolved with what happened
Dialogue: 2,2:22:36.91,2:22:39.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,when that Abby pulled the gun on Ellie in the theater,
Dialogue: 2,2:22:39.95,2:22:45.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,or perhaps they simply fast forwarded and watched a run through of the game after that point.
Dialogue: 2,2:22:45.02,2:22:51.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,And lastly, most players are going to have a very skeptical outlook at this second half.
Dialogue: 2,2:22:51.11,2:22:54.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're all looking for reasons to dislike Abby.
Dialogue: 2,2:22:54.53,2:22:59.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, she's done something that we would deem most likely unforgivable.
Dialogue: 2,2:22:59.63,2:23:04.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, I would like to think that most of us would have an open enough mind to play through this
Dialogue: 2,2:23:04.34,2:23:08.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,and see whether or not they could be convinced of whether or not she was justified.
Dialogue: 2,2:23:08.90,2:23:10.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,In that survey I conducted,
Dialogue: 2,2:23:10.44,2:23:15.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,it seemed as though the overwhelming majority of people that decided to walk away from the game
Dialogue: 2,2:23:15.59,2:23:18.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,didn't play it after this particular point,
Dialogue: 2,2:23:18.74,2:23:25.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,and those people tended to rate the game very negatively, averaging around a 4 to 5.
Dialogue: 2,2:23:25.61,2:23:29.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, of the people that played the game all the way through,
Dialogue: 2,2:23:29.04,2:23:33.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,the majority of them rated the game in the range of an 8 to 9.
Dialogue: 2,2:23:33.28,2:23:35.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seems to be the conclusion is fairly clear.
Dialogue: 2,2:23:35.90,2:23:39.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Those that gave the game the chance to prove itself to them
Dialogue: 2,2:23:39.36,2:23:42.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,ended up enjoying it once they experienced the whole thing.
Dialogue: 2,2:23:42.77,2:23:45.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,Whereas those that decided to cut and run
Dialogue: 2,2:23:45.01,2:23:48.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,had the experience that you would expect from somebody who cuts and runs.
Dialogue: 2,2:23:48.44,2:23:50.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,It really is that simple.
Dialogue: 2,2:23:50.09,2:23:55.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,You have to give a game like this the chance to do its job.
Dialogue: 2,2:23:55.31,2:23:59.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,What they're trying to do is convince you that a character you hate
Dialogue: 2,2:23:59.42,2:24:03.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,is actually a human being that has feelings and emotions
Dialogue: 2,2:24:03.34,2:24:08.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,that are perhaps just as justified as the character you'd find relatable.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:08.06,2:24:12.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,That argument isn't made over the course of an hour gameplay sequence.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:12.98,2:24:16.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,It takes time and it takes a lot of effort.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:16.43,2:24:20.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,And more than anything, it takes the open mind of the observer.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:20.63,2:24:23.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,It may seem like a cliche for many people to say
Dialogue: 2,2:24:23.44,2:24:27.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,"Well, if you didn't like {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} when you quit halfway through,
Dialogue: 2,2:24:27.32,2:24:30.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,you just didn't get it, and you were never going to like it".
Dialogue: 2,2:24:30.14,2:24:32.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, I think there is a fair amount of truth in that.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:32.99,2:24:34.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I don't know, let me know what you think.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:34.76,2:24:41.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,What I do know is that at this point, in my first run of the game, I was highly exhausted.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:41.30,2:24:47.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby Sequences required a lot of effort, both emotionally and physically, to get through.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:47.96,2:24:50.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,With the emotional tension and all of the gore,
Dialogue: 2,2:24:50.99,2:24:54.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's an exhausting 10 to 15 hours of game play to get through.
Dialogue: 2,2:24:54.98,2:25:01.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I will be honest, even I considered taking a break before continuing on with Abby sequences.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:01.10,2:25:05.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I decided to put my head down and give the game the chance that it was asking for.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:05.78,2:25:09.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless, this is the time when we begin playing as Abby.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:09.65,2:25:14.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,The pace changes, the attitude changes, the tone changes.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:14.13,2:25:19.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,And more broadly, even the style of character work changes.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:19.52,2:25:25.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,In many ways, it's going to feel like a different game entirely both for better and worse.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:25.01,2:25:27.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we're going to get into all of it.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:27.29,2:25:28.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seattle Day 1,
Dialogue: 2,2:25:28.62,2:25:31.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby wakes up and we begin the second half of the game
Dialogue: 2,2:25:31.64,2:25:35.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,playing as who most of us will consider to be the antagonist.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:35.87,2:25:38.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, this might change by the time we get to the end.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:38.99,2:25:42.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,This whole game is, of course, about perspective in relativism,
Dialogue: 2,2:25:42.29,2:25:44.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,and to that extent it works fairly simply.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:44.78,2:25:46.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're going to be forced to play as Abby
Dialogue: 2,2:25:46.96,2:25:53.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least until we either start to enjoy her as a character like her or even love her,
Dialogue: 2,2:25:53.75,2:25:57.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,or at the very least, until we forget how much we hate her.
Dialogue: 2,2:25:57.80,2:25:59.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not going to happen instantly,
Dialogue: 2,2:25:59.18,2:26:02.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,but over the course of the next 8 to 12 hours of game play,
Dialogue: 2,2:26:02.78,2:26:07.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're probably going to start to lose the hatred you felt for her at one point.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:07.24,2:26:11.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Here Abby is paired with Manny, who was one of the assailants in Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:11.54,2:26:17.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,You'll see a lot of them in very casual settings here, it almost feels surreal.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:17.66,2:26:21.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,You hate these people, these people killed Joel.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:21.32,2:26:26.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why are they so normal, and why do they seem so happy and relaxed.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:26.76,2:26:32.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,You explore the WLF base where their station, which is actually built out of a stadium.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:32.09,2:26:33.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,You're preparing to go out on a mission,
Dialogue: 2,2:26:33.80,2:26:38.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,and so naturally you grab guns, a burrito and play fetch with a dog.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:49.25,2:26:53.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Mel is going with Abby and Manny on this patrol.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:53.21,2:26:57.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, this is the same girl that we just saw Ellie kill.
Dialogue: 2,2:26:57.57,2:27:00.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once again, it's a little surreal.
Dialogue: 2,2:27:00.14,2:27:04.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,You just saw this woman get murdered, and Ellie freak out as a result,
Dialogue: 2,2:27:04.79,2:27:10.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you also know that Abby freaked out as a result of Ellie's actions towards Mel and Owen,
Dialogue: 2,2:27:10.73,2:27:16.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,so to see her seemingly fine in this particular instance, is a little startling.
Dialogue: 2,2:27:16.73,2:27:20.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, Abby and Manny debate for a brief moment
Dialogue: 2,2:27:20.28,2:27:22.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,as to whether or not Mel should be allowed to go with them.
Dialogue: 2,2:27:22.55,2:27:26.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, she's pretty damn pregnant, as you can probably see.
Dialogue: 2,2:27:26.39,2:27:29.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,But they dismiss it because they don't expect to see any action.
Dialogue: 2,2:27:29.36,2:27:31.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're basically just going to go on a quick patrol,
Dialogue: 2,2:27:31.73,2:27:34.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,make sure that there's nothing to concerning out there,
Dialogue: 2,2:27:34.25,2:27:36.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,and if there is, they're going to call in support,
Dialogue: 2,2:27:36.38,2:27:39.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,at which point it wouldn't actually matter that Mel is there.
Dialogue: 2,2:27:39.35,2:27:44.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,In my opinion, it's still a stupid decision to bring what is a very pregnant woman
Dialogue: 2,2:27:44.40,2:27:49.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,on what is effectively a military mission to scout out the surrounding area.
Dialogue: 2,2:27:50.54,2:27:53.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that's just me, and it's actually Abby too.
Dialogue: 2,2:27:53.45,2:27:59.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the end of this sequence, Abby actually gives Manny crap for having brought Mel along
Dialogue: 2,2:27:59.07,2:28:02.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,and says that she definitely should never have been allowed to come in the first place.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:02.93,2:28:06.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, they allowed her to go, from the outset.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:06.60,2:28:12.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, while speaking of Mel, the fact that she's pregnant and we just saw her get murdered by Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,2:28:12.26,2:28:15.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it's also important that we addressed the elephant in the room
Dialogue: 2,2:28:15.20,2:28:17.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,that some have said actually ruins the game.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:17.99,2:28:23.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,That is that knowing what's going to happen removes all of the stakes in the story.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:23.24,2:28:28.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,After Ellie's whole half of the game, we know that most of these characters are going to die.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:28.57,2:28:32.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,And more importantly, we know how they're going to die and when they're going to die.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:32.89,2:28:39.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so going through these sequences where we're trying to protect them or do things with and for them,
Dialogue: 2,2:28:39.17,2:28:43.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,it removes a lot of the tension, since we know how it's all going to end.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:43.01,2:28:46.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, I strongly disagree with this idea.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:46.94,2:28:53.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are countless stories where the conclusion is known before the story even really begins.
Dialogue: 2,2:28:53.03,2:28:57.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,You could look at something as simple and kitschy as the movie Titanic,
Dialogue: 2,2:28:57.05,2:29:02.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,a fascinating film about an albeit cheesy and captivating romance.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:02.48,2:29:06.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,But at its core, we all know how that story is going to end.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:06.59,2:29:10.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Titanic is not magically going to make it back to New York,
Dialogue: 2,2:29:10.55,2:29:15.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,but rather it's going down and many people are going to die.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:15.14,2:29:18.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's still an interesting and captivating story
Dialogue: 2,2:29:18.35,2:29:22.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it's not actually about the destination that the story reaches.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:22.33,2:29:24.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's about the journey to that destination.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:24.86,2:29:28.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or in a gaming example, we could look at {\i1}God of War{\i0} from 2018.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:28.88,2:29:34.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,We know from the beginning of the game that the story is going to end with Kratos and Atreus
Dialogue: 2,2:29:34.20,2:29:38.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,spreading Faye's ashes from the highest peak in the realms.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:38.04,2:29:40.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,We know the ending from the start.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:40.49,2:29:45.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,and yet the story is still captivating because it's not just about reaching that destination.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:45.76,2:29:48.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, to me this seems fairly obvious,
Dialogue: 2,2:29:48.65,2:29:55.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it is actually a pretty common accusation against stories that have presumed endings.
Dialogue: 2,2:29:55.68,2:29:58.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,In my mind, if you're going to allow a story to be ruined,
Dialogue: 2,2:29:58.64,2:30:03.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,simply because you know how the characters are going to end up at the end of that story,
Dialogue: 2,2:30:03.41,2:30:09.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're not actually engaging and absorbing the media in the correct,
Dialogue: 2,2:30:09.56,2:30:11.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,or at the very least, most effective way.
Dialogue: 2,2:30:11.63,2:30:16.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, Abby leaves on the back of a truck out on patrol with Manny, and Mel
Dialogue: 2,2:30:16.76,2:30:19.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and of course, the dog, Alice.
Dialogue: 2,2:30:19.63,2:30:24.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Remember, I said, that that dog that we found in the aquarium earlier that
Dialogue: 2,2:30:24.10,2:30:28.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie actually stabs the crap out of would come back again
Dialogue: 2,2:30:28.01,2:30:31.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,well… yeah, this… this is actually the same dog.
Dialogue: 2,2:30:31.28,2:30:36.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's Alice, and she's cute and lovable, and Ellie kills the crap out of her.
Dialogue: 2,2:30:36.67,2:30:38.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Mel talk about how they're doing.
Dialogue: 2,2:30:38.63,2:30:43.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Apparently everybody's been struggling with sleep ever since they killed Joel in Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,2:30:43.76,2:30:49.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Owen are also going out on countless open assignments trying to keep busy
Dialogue: 2,2:30:49.02,2:30:52.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,and exhaust themselves to the point where they don't have to think about what they've done.
Dialogue: 2,2:30:52.52,2:30:54.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,These are hardened militaristic people
Dialogue: 2,2:30:54.72,2:30:58.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the fact that they're so torn up over what they did to Joel.
Dialogue: 2,2:30:58.82,2:31:00.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's interesting.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:00.03,2:31:03.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because at the very least, it shows that they were somewhat distressed by what they did
Dialogue: 2,2:31:03.88,2:31:05.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,and perhaps even some of them regretted.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:05.75,2:31:10.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is the first step towards humanizing these people that you wanted to villainize from the start.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:10.70,2:31:12.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's subtle, but it works.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:12.89,2:31:17.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,It also breaks the perception that Abby and the crew are simply cold blooded killers.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:17.66,2:31:20.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're humans, and yeah, they do so messed up stuff.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:20.30,2:31:24.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,But some of them can feel regret over something that they felt was unjust.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:24.56,2:31:27.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or at the very least, a bad choice.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:27.23,2:31:32.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, this gets interrupted by a group of Seraphites, ambushing the group on horseback.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:32.93,2:31:35.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,I personally hate these sequences.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:35.45,2:31:41.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,The aiming is awkward, the damage feels unfair, and often it's just generally awkward.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:41.48,2:31:43.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,If we compare it to other car sequences,
Dialogue: 2,2:31:43.37,2:31:48.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,like the one earlier with Jesse traveling all the way down into the river.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:48.65,2:31:50.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not quite the same.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:50.84,2:31:55.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,The one with Ellie and Jesse is very scripted from start to finish
Dialogue: 2,2:31:55.62,2:31:58.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,and feels fair because it's so heavily scripted.
Dialogue: 2,2:31:58.40,2:32:00.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,The player doesn't actually have that much agency.
Dialogue: 2,2:32:00.89,2:32:06.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, if you don't do anything in this car sequence when you're ambushed by the Seraphites
Dialogue: 2,2:32:06.92,2:32:09.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're going to be killed and have to reload.
Dialogue: 2,2:32:09.88,2:32:14.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you have to be actively engaging with the game in its most awkward state,
Dialogue: 2,2:32:14.75,2:32:20.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,which to me means that it's subject and worthy of criticism since you're forced to engage with it.
Dialogue: 2,2:32:20.72,2:32:23.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, Abby and her group eventually get to safety.
Dialogue: 2,2:32:23.72,2:32:25.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,You push through several different buildings,
Dialogue: 2,2:32:25.61,2:32:30.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,and after fighting through multiple waves of infected and more Seraphites,
Dialogue: 2,2:32:30.29,2:32:35.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,you find yourself in a gas station being ambushed by yet another wave of Seraphites.
Dialogue: 2,2:32:35.18,2:32:37.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now a lot of this just feels like bloat.
Dialogue: 2,2:32:37.49,2:32:39.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,And when we're talking about pacing,
Dialogue: 2,2:32:39.26,2:32:44.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's the last thing that you want to be thinking when going through this stage of the game,
Dialogue: 2,2:32:44.93,2:32:50.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,players need to be more engaged than they have been in the entire game to this point.
Dialogue: 2,2:32:50.06,2:32:55.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I think most people are going to start to feel bored because it just feels like more of the same.
Dialogue: 2,2:32:55.37,2:32:57.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are some interesting moments of levity,
Dialogue: 2,2:32:57.29,2:33:01.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and there are moments where these characters are actually humanized a lot,
Dialogue: 2,2:33:01.10,2:33:04.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is perhaps more the point of this section of the game.
Dialogue: 2,2:33:04.73,2:33:07.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not really about keeping the player super engaged,
Dialogue: 2,2:33:07.37,2:33:12.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's about making sure that the player starts to relate to these people that they previously hated.
Dialogue: 2,2:33:12.23,2:33:18.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,I know it's a lot to ask that we get both an interesting game play sequence that keeps the player engaged
Dialogue: 2,2:33:18.17,2:33:20.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,and humanizing sequences with these characters.
Dialogue: 2,2:33:20.99,2:33:24.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, I wish that there were something a little bit more engaging.
Dialogue: 2,2:33:24.62,2:33:28.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,My favorite part is probably when Abby is discussing her fear of heights with Mel.
Dialogue: 2,2:33:28.94,2:33:32.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a small moment, and it's something that could be easily missed,
Dialogue: 2,2:33:32.39,2:33:34.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I actually find it really endearing.
Dialogue: 2,2:34:01.58,2:34:05.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once you at the gas station and after a shoot out in a rail yard,
Dialogue: 2,2:34:05.33,2:34:06.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,a crew of WLF members,
Dialogue: 2,2:34:06.98,2:34:10.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,presumably alerted by the assault that happened just a few minutes before,
Dialogue: 2,2:34:10.73,2:34:12.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,come in and save the day,
Dialogue: 2,2:34:12.32,2:34:15.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,killing all of the Seraphites that we're about to get the jump on you.
Dialogue: 2,2:34:15.41,2:34:19.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so you're all rescued, and you brought to the forward base as it's called.
Dialogue: 2,2:34:19.53,2:34:23.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Mel goes to get patched up while Abby and Manny go into see Isaac.
Dialogue: 2,2:34:23.69,2:34:26.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,Finally, we're going to get to meet the head honcho,
Dialogue: 2,2:34:26.27,2:34:27.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,the guy that we've been hearing all about
Dialogue: 2,2:34:27.98,2:34:33.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,for the last 12 or so hours of gameplay since Ellie got to Seattle.
Dialogue: 2,2:34:33.51,2:34:36.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,On the way up to see Isaac Abby and Manny are told
Dialogue: 2,2:34:36.23,2:34:39.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Owen was actually off with another member of the squad,
Dialogue: 2,2:34:39.86,2:34:45.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that he shot that guy, Danny in order to save quote unquote "some Scar".
Dialogue: 2,2:34:45.89,2:34:50.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Needless to say, this could lead to a death sentence for Owen if proven true.
Dialogue: 2,2:34:50.48,2:34:52.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,We don't really know what exactly happened.
Dialogue: 2,2:34:52.43,2:34:55.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if Owen did actually kill a WLF member
Dialogue: 2,2:34:55.90,2:35:01.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,simply to save what's considered a barbarian pest on their people,
Dialogue: 2,2:35:01.04,2:35:03.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,It ain't good end a pretty bad for Owen.
Dialogue: 2,2:35:03.08,2:35:05.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so Abby and Manny head up to talk with Isaac
Dialogue: 2,2:35:05.88,2:35:10.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Isaac probably has the most badass introduction of any character in this game.
Dialogue: 2,2:36:00.47,2:36:03.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Isaac doesn't want them to go and save Owen
Dialogue: 2,2:36:03.24,2:36:08.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they are revving up for some big assault on the Scars, and he can't spare them.
Dialogue: 2,2:36:08.03,2:36:11.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby says "Screw it" and they go after him anyways,
Dialogue: 2,2:36:11.17,2:36:13.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,because why not?
Dialogue: 2,2:36:13.04,2:36:14.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now there's two things about this.
Dialogue: 2,2:36:14.27,2:36:18.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,For one, Abby leaving the group to go and find Owen
Dialogue: 2,2:36:18.34,2:36:22.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,explains why she seems to have gone AWOL in all of those sequences,
Dialogue: 2,2:36:22.46,2:36:25.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Ellie was trying to figure out what was going on;
Dialogue: 2,2:36:25.25,2:36:27.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,and why Abby was not with the rest of the group.
Dialogue: 2,2:36:27.62,2:36:30.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,The WLF were upset with her and wanted to hunt her down
Dialogue: 2,2:36:30.73,2:36:34.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,because she went AWOL and disobeyed Isaac's orders.
Dialogue: 2,2:36:34.19,2:36:37.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,This, of course, doesn't mean that she's not a threat to Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,2:36:37.22,2:36:42.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it does mean that she's not as interested in simply pursuing the goals
Dialogue: 2,2:36:42.56,2:36:47.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,and hopes and aspirations of the WLF as Ellie perhaps initially thought.
Dialogue: 2,2:36:47.19,2:36:49.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby is much more of an individual,
Dialogue: 2,2:36:49.08,2:36:53.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,and perhaps that's even something that Ellie and Abby have in common.
Dialogue: 2,2:36:53.06,2:36:57.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,The other thing about this is that it seems relatively easy for Abby to go AWOL
Dialogue: 2,2:36:57.76,2:37:00.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,and disobey direct orders like this.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:00.35,2:37:02.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's just that she's particularly capable,
Dialogue: 2,2:37:02.96,2:37:05.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,and so she was able to sneak out with any major issue.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:05.96,2:37:09.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,But she also doesn't seem particularly threatened by Isaac,
Dialogue: 2,2:37:09.02,2:37:14.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is strange considering that our introduction to him is of him torturing a guy.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:14.51,2:37:18.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,So whether its hubris or simply a lack of consideration,
Dialogue: 2,2:37:18.59,2:37:22.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby breaks out and decides to go find Owen herself.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:22.31,2:37:25.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Her hope, of course, being that she's going to be able to save Owen
Dialogue: 2,2:37:25.67,2:37:29.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,and figure something out before the big raid on the Seraphites
Dialogue: 2,2:37:29.33,2:37:32.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that she's never realized to have gone missing.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:32.00,2:37:37.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,We then have a quick cutaway where we go to a short date between Abby and Owen.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:37.30,2:37:40.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're on a Ferris wheel, and it's actually super cute.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:40.49,2:37:43.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once again we see that Abby is terrified of heights,
Dialogue: 2,2:37:43.19,2:37:49.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's again a humanizing moment to see her chilling with Owen and also freaked out.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:49.46,2:37:54.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, once again, this is a point when the pace really starts to come into question.
Dialogue: 2,2:37:54.59,2:37:58.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,What is the deal here? Why is it moving so slowly?
Dialogue: 2,2:37:58.46,2:38:02.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why are we going through all of these cutaways with characters we don't particularly know,
Dialogue: 2,2:38:02.87,2:38:06.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,and most people probably don't care that much about yet?
Dialogue: 2,2:38:06.44,2:38:12.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,When we need to be engaged and going through a much more interesting and fast base sequences?
Dialogue: 2,2:38:12.41,2:38:18.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now perhaps I'm alone, and my tolerance for fast pace narrative sequences is much much higher.
Dialogue: 2,2:38:18.86,2:38:20.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I need a lot more.
Dialogue: 2,2:38:20.60,2:38:25.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's what it is, and the pace isn't actually as bad as it seems to me.
Dialogue: 2,2:38:25.43,2:38:30.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in these sequences that are coming over the course of Seattle Day 2 and 3,
Dialogue: 2,2:38:30.62,2:38:34.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,the games really going to slow to a crawl in multiple moments.
Dialogue: 2,2:38:34.79,2:38:36.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I don't know, let me know what you think.
Dialogue: 2,2:38:36.83,2:38:38.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,The date is relatively cute
Dialogue: 2,2:38:38.24,2:38:44.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,and at ends within the aquarium with Abby and Owen talking about their feelings.
Dialogue: 2,2:38:44.03,2:38:47.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,At one point, Abby breaks away, she's got something else on her mind,
Dialogue: 2,2:38:47.81,2:38:50.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it turns out that she's still thinking about Joel.
Dialogue: 2,2:38:50.45,2:38:55.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're trying to find some way of finding him so that they can enact some sort of revenge.
Dialogue: 2,2:38:55.76,2:38:59.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Owen doesn't seem particularly interested in that pursuit,
Dialogue: 2,2:38:59.18,2:39:03.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though he did know Abby's father fairly well from what we can tell.
Dialogue: 2,2:39:03.83,2:39:06.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,But he understands this means a lot to Abby,
Dialogue: 2,2:39:06.92,2:39:09.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,and so he goes along with it, at least for the most part.
Dialogue: 2,2:39:09.62,2:39:13.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,What is clear is that this is Abby's pursuit, and this is what Abby wants.
Dialogue: 2,2:39:13.61,2:39:17.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,And she's not going to quit until she finds Joel and kills him.
Dialogue: 2,2:39:17.39,2:39:20.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,She references multiple times that they need to get back to training,
Dialogue: 2,2:39:20.15,2:39:24.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,which explains why she is currently not particularly shredded,
Dialogue: 2,2:39:24.05,2:39:26.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least compared to what we see in the present day
Dialogue: 2,2:39:26.87,2:39:33.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,quote unquote sequences of Abby going through and fighting infected, and of course Ellie and her gang.
Dialogue: 2,2:39:33.62,2:39:37.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's why in many moments I think her physical buffness and appearance
Dialogue: 2,2:39:37.68,2:39:40.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,is a direct reflection of her mental state,
Dialogue: 2,2:39:40.19,2:39:44.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why later in the game, when she's led off of that revenge-base pursuit,
Dialogue: 2,2:39:44.39,2:39:48.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,she actually thins out a lot and is no longer as much of a meat head.
Dialogue: 2,2:39:48.89,2:39:52.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,But other than the pace, this is actually starting to work.
Dialogue: 2,2:39:52.19,2:39:55.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,I found myself actually caring about Abby and Owen,
Dialogue: 2,2:39:55.34,2:39:59.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,and being involved and interested in what was going on within their lives.
Dialogue: 2,2:39:59.27,2:40:04.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's kind of bizarre to say, but I was starting to feel bad for Joel's murderer.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:04.28,2:40:08.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,We then cut to Abby and Manny at the outskirts of the WLF's territory.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:08.72,2:40:14.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's going to find Owen, and for some reason Manny leaves her to go on by herself.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:14.33,2:40:18.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,He claimed, so it's not to draw too much attention and to get them in trouble with Isaac.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:18.83,2:40:20.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even with this excuse,
Dialogue: 2,2:40:20.57,2:40:24.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,it seems like a bit of a stretch that Manny would leave her to go on by herself.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:24.53,2:40:27.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I'm willing to let it slide, it's not that big of a deal.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:27.74,2:40:31.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now the navigation in this chapter is actually pretty interesting,
Dialogue: 2,2:40:31.25,2:40:34.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's done in a subtle and beautiful way.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:34.31,2:40:37.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is follow the sunset.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:37.46,2:40:39.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's simple, it's elegant,
Dialogue: 2,2:40:39.29,2:40:43.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's easy to understand and follow as you explore a given level.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:43.70,2:40:47.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because pretty much all of the lighting in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} is ambient.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:47.57,2:40:52.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,You're always in tune with the direction of light that's coming in from the outside.
Dialogue: 2,2:40:52.20,2:40:55.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I have to say while exploring multiple of these levels,
Dialogue: 2,2:40:55.52,2:41:00.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,focusing on the sunlight coming in through the windows to reorient myself,
Dialogue: 2,2:41:00.14,2:41:05.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,I found it remarkably natural and really cool at just how fluidly this worked.
Dialogue: 2,2:41:05.75,2:41:08.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,I personally can't remember the last time
Dialogue: 2,2:41:08.08,2:41:12.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,that a game used the sunlight to direct players in a particular way,
Dialogue: 2,2:41:12.56,2:41:14.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I find that kind of refreshing.
Dialogue: 2,2:41:14.81,2:41:20.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sure, a lot of games use cardinal directions to point players in the right direction.
Dialogue: 2,2:41:20.21,2:41:22.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,They'll say, go north or go west,
Dialogue: 2,2:41:22.32,2:41:26.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,or they have a compass on screen that allows you to figure out where you need to go.
Dialogue: 2,2:41:26.66,2:41:28.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that that's the same thing.
Dialogue: 2,2:41:28.75,2:41:31.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,For one, it forces you to look at the compass itself.
Dialogue: 2,2:41:31.76,2:41:35.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Look at a game such as {\i1}Skyrim{\i0}, if you ever want to reorient yourself,
Dialogue: 2,2:41:35.60,2:41:38.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,if you don't happen to know the map like the back of your hand,
Dialogue: 2,2:41:38.69,2:41:42.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,you have to glance up at the compass and figure out where you need to go.
Dialogue: 2,2:41:42.32,2:41:44.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,This takes your eyes off of the map
Dialogue: 2,2:41:44.08,2:41:47.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,and in turn off of all of the amazing artwork
Dialogue: 2,2:41:47.08,2:41:51.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,that all of the developers over at the studio spent years and years working on.
Dialogue: 2,2:41:51.29,2:41:56.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've always thought of this as a real tragedy when it comes to open world game design
Dialogue: 2,2:41:56.33,2:41:59.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,that a developer can spend all this time working on something,
Dialogue: 2,2:41:59.33,2:42:04.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,only to have the player completely distracted from it by way of simple exploration,
Dialogue: 2,2:42:04.88,2:42:07.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,something that should go hand in hand with it.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:07.34,2:42:11.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is why I'm often a fan of completely mixing UI on screen.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:11.69,2:42:13.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,I just don't think that it's worth it.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:13.43,2:42:17.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,Especially when there's other alternatives such as having in game UI.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:17.92,2:42:20.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Look at a game such as {\i1}Death Stranding{\i0}.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:20.26,2:42:24.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Whenever you want to navigate to a given destination to complete a delivery,
Dialogue: 2,2:42:24.53,2:42:26.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,you set the way point on your map.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:26.72,2:42:31.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then, as you head out into the game world to reach your destination,
Dialogue: 2,2:42:31.34,2:42:37.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,you find that all of the direction that you're given is interspersed with the terrain.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:37.82,2:42:42.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means that the guidance you are given to get from one destination to another
Dialogue: 2,2:42:42.11,2:42:46.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,doesn't pull you out of the game world or distract you from it,
Dialogue: 2,2:42:46.13,2:42:48.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,but rather it pulls you in even more.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:48.83,2:42:53.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,It makes you look at every hill crest, every ridge, every mountain top.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:53.51,2:42:58.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's at that point that these open world games really shine.
Dialogue: 2,2:42:58.37,2:43:04.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I honestly believe that's why {\i1}Death Stranding{\i0} even though its world is subjectively quite empty,
Dialogue: 2,2:43:04.34,2:43:08.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,can still captivate players in such an intriguing way.
Dialogue: 2,2:43:08.48,2:43:10.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if you want to hear all of my thoughts on that,
Dialogue: 2,2:43:10.64,2:43:13.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,go check out my full length critique of {\i1}Death Stranding{\i0}.
Dialogue: 2,2:43:13.55,2:43:15.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's over two hours' long, it's… it's a monster.
Dialogue: 2,2:43:15.89,2:43:19.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if you're this far into this video, you're probably gained for it.
Dialogue: 2,2:43:19.68,2:43:23.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,All of this to say, I think that the level design in the direction
Dialogue: 2,2:43:23.56,2:43:27.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Naughty Dog gives the player in this particular sequence with Abby
Dialogue: 2,2:43:27.82,2:43:30.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,is phenomenal and I can't applauded enough.
Dialogue: 2,2:43:30.26,2:43:35.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Something as simple as having the player follow sunlight is implemented so well,
Dialogue: 2,2:43:35.67,2:43:38.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,that I think it's absolutely astonishing.
Dialogue: 2,2:43:38.81,2:43:43.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,Any studio could set up a scene where they demand that the player follow the sunlight.
Dialogue: 2,2:43:43.37,2:43:49.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's much harder to have that sunlight carry through in every scene, every area, every room
Dialogue: 2,2:43:49.40,2:43:54.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,that the player enters, such that they know exactly where they need to go next.
Dialogue: 2,2:43:54.02,2:43:58.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so it's with this guidance that Abby heads west to try to get to the aquarium,
Dialogue: 2,2:43:58.76,2:44:00.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,where she thinks Owen is hiding out.
Dialogue: 2,2:44:00.56,2:44:05.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,She wants to speak to Owen because she needs to figure out why exactly he shot Danny,
Dialogue: 2,2:44:05.72,2:44:08.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,and whether or not there's two sides to the story.
Dialogue: 2,2:44:08.72,2:44:10.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Throughout this relatively calm sequence,
Dialogue: 2,2:44:10.91,2:44:15.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're mostly collecting ammo and exploring buildings, grabbing some collectibles.
Dialogue: 2,2:44:15.50,2:44:18.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,This really is the calm before the storm because after this
Dialogue: 2,2:44:18.88,2:44:22.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,is when the game is really going to pick up and carry through to the final act.
Dialogue: 2,2:44:22.76,2:44:27.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this descent into chaos begins when Abby's climbing through a crack in the wall.
Dialogue: 2,2:44:27.38,2:44:29.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,And well, this happens.
Dialogue: 2,2:44:55.52,2:44:59.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,I love these you-are-not-safe moments, I really do.
Dialogue: 2,2:44:59.84,2:45:04.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,As we mentioned earlier, Ellie actually gets jumped while she's adjusting weapons,
Dialogue: 2,2:45:04.79,2:45:07.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you're upgrading abilities at a workbench.
Dialogue: 2,2:45:07.99,2:45:13.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,And now Abby while you're in what is presumed to be a covered, loading space,
Dialogue: 2,2:45:13.49,2:45:15.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Abby even gets jumped.
Dialogue: 2,2:45:15.00,2:45:19.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,I just, I think it's so cool, I… I know that maybe I'm in the minority with this,
Dialogue: 2,2:45:19.76,2:45:22.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I really do think that it's cool to see.
Dialogue: 2,2:45:22.07,2:45:26.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,This also reminded me of a flashback when Ellie and Joel were climbing through a crack in the wall,
Dialogue: 2,2:45:26.84,2:45:30.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the Clicker punched through the wall, pulling Ellie out,
Dialogue: 2,2:45:30.38,2:45:32.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it starts in many boss fight.
Dialogue: 2,2:45:32.09,2:45:36.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a similarly between Abby and Ellie to make you think of them as relatable and similar.
Dialogue: 2,2:45:36.92,2:45:39.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,But perhaps I'm reading too much into it.
Dialogue: 2,2:45:39.29,2:45:43.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the end of the level you come upon a checkpoint from the initial quarantine.
Dialogue: 2,2:45:54.86,2:45:59.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's a shrine set up here dedicated to the Prophet of the Seraphites cult.
Dialogue: 2,2:45:59.42,2:46:05.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's also all of these notes surrounding the shrine that are asking her for various things,
Dialogue: 2,2:46:05.78,2:46:07.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think it makes the player realize
Dialogue: 2,2:46:07.73,2:46:12.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,just how different the Seraphites are from the WLF and in turn Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,2:46:12.08,2:46:17.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now we never get to see or meet the Prophetess, which I actually like,
Dialogue: 2,2:46:17.21,2:46:21.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,similar to how we don't end up having a major boss fight or clash with Isaac,
Dialogue: 2,2:46:21.68,2:46:24.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,something I think video games are definitely guilty of doing
Dialogue: 2,2:46:24.77,2:46:27.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,whenever there's a notable character introduced.
Dialogue: 2,2:46:27.35,2:46:30.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you see a bad guy introduced to the story at some point,
Dialogue: 2,2:46:30.83,2:46:35.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,chances are you're going to have some sort of boss fight with him or her.
Dialogue: 2,2:46:35.24,2:46:37.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Otherwise they wouldn't have been introduced in the first place.
Dialogue: 2,2:46:37.94,2:46:41.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,And maybe I'm alone, but I really appreciate that Naughty Dog bucked this trend
Dialogue: 2,2:46:41.75,2:46:44.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,and made sure that these characters stood by themselves
Dialogue: 2,2:46:44.92,2:46:48.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,and simply turn them into a trophy on your Playstation achievements list.
Dialogue: 2,2:46:48.84,2:46:50.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now speaking of the Prophetess,
Dialogue: 2,2:46:50.40,2:46:54.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,or as she's more commonly referred to in the game, just "the Prophet",
Dialogue: 2,2:46:54.93,2:46:57.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,we don't actually get to find out a lot about her.
Dialogue: 2,2:46:57.89,2:47:02.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,I did a lot of digging to try to figure out who this lady actually was,
Dialogue: 2,2:47:02.03,2:47:08.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I say WAS because it's implied that she actually was killed before the events of this second game.
Dialogue: 2,2:47:08.15,2:47:13.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see, it seems that soon after the outbreak and Seattle fell into absolute chaos,
Dialogue: 2,2:47:13.46,2:47:17.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,this woman arose as the leader of a small cult.
Dialogue: 2,2:47:17.24,2:47:22.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,She claimed that the infection was effectively a punishment on humanity
Dialogue: 2,2:47:22.15,2:47:24.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,for their overreliance on technology.
Dialogue: 2,2:47:24.80,2:47:32.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,So naturally she prescribed all of her followers to years and years of hard manual labour,
Dialogue: 2,2:47:32.36,2:47:38.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,working in the fields to produce their own food in a way that was congruity with nature itself.
Dialogue: 2,2:47:38.84,2:47:42.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,This obviously lead to a very strict lifestyle for all of the Seraphites,
Dialogue: 2,2:47:42.47,2:47:45.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,but they were willing to do it because of her guidance.
Dialogue: 2,2:47:45.53,2:47:49.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, she died, at some point, somehow.
Dialogue: 2,2:47:49.46,2:47:54.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,As far as I could find, there's never a mention of exactly how she died.
Dialogue: 2,2:47:54.62,2:47:58.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you came across something, please comment down below, I would love to know.
Dialogue: 2,2:47:58.61,2:48:02.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in all of my digging in my multiple runthroughs of the game,
Dialogue: 2,2:48:02.21,2:48:06.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,I couldn't find anything detailing specifically how she died.
Dialogue: 2,2:48:06.47,2:48:08.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,What we do know is that soon after she died,
Dialogue: 2,2:48:08.72,2:48:13.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,a bunch of other elders in the church of the Seraphites took over
Dialogue: 2,2:48:13.31,2:48:19.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,and started ramping up the critical element of the cult, which was control.
Dialogue: 2,2:48:19.79,2:48:24.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naturally, many of the new leaders started to fall into corrupt states.
Dialogue: 2,2:48:24.32,2:48:29.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,They started to hog more food, they started to control different territories,
Dialogue: 2,2:48:29.36,2:48:30.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,and before they knew it,
Dialogue: 2,2:48:30.59,2:48:34.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,the Seraphites cult wasn't about living incongruity with nature,
Dialogue: 2,2:48:34.82,2:48:41.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,but rather was much more about control and strict adherence to the guidance and dictum of the elders.
Dialogue: 2,2:48:41.75,2:48:44.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is an interesting choice by Naughty Dogs writers.
Dialogue: 2,2:48:44.48,2:48:50.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,Specifically because it makes it so that the Seraphites followers are much more relatable and sympathetic.
Dialogue: 2,2:48:50.42,2:48:51.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Whenever you feel as though
Dialogue: 2,2:48:51.72,2:48:57.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,they're employing some very animalistic and barbarian tactic to achieve a certain ends,
Dialogue: 2,2:48:57.38,2:49:03.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,such as gutting somebody to release them into the heavens for some reason,
Dialogue: 2,2:49:03.11,2:49:05.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,you can always fall back and partially excuse it
Dialogue: 2,2:49:05.92,2:49:10.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,because these are people simply following directions that they believe are coming from on high.
Dialogue: 2,2:49:10.94,2:49:15.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Most of the Seraphites aren't viciously evil and despicable people
Dialogue: 2,2:49:15.94,2:49:19.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,trying to do despicable things because they enjoy it.
Dialogue: 2,2:49:19.31,2:49:25.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Rather, they're people simply trying to survive in a world that's really really messed up.
Dialogue: 2,2:49:25.10,2:49:28.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's no mystery that this is set up right around the time
Dialogue: 2,2:49:28.16,2:49:35.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Abby is starting to feel sympathy towards members, or in this case, former members of the cult.
Dialogue: 2,2:49:35.39,2:49:37.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again this game is all about perspectives.
Dialogue: 2,2:49:37.88,2:49:40.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's all about trying to get you to sympathize with people
Dialogue: 2,2:49:40.91,2:49:44.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,that you didn't think you could possibly sympathize with before.
Dialogue: 2,2:49:44.28,2:49:47.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,The point is, the Prophet is a very interesting character,
Dialogue: 2,2:49:47.93,2:49:53.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,specifically considering the control that she seems to have over the Seraphites.
Dialogue: 2,2:49:53.36,2:49:58.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, without many details on exactly when she died or how she died,
Dialogue: 2,2:49:58.16,2:50:01.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's unclear at just how long she's been gone.
Dialogue: 2,2:50:01.52,2:50:04.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,It would be one thing if she had been dead for just a few years,
Dialogue: 2,2:50:04.82,2:50:07.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this is what's starting to ramp up.
Dialogue: 2,2:50:07.28,2:50:12.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's an entirely another case for her to have been dead for ten or fifteen years,
Dialogue: 2,2:50:12.29,2:50:18.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,leading to over a decade of power struggles, which eventually bred this new, morphed cult.
Dialogue: 2,2:50:18.62,2:50:21.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, I think the Seraphites are fairly interesting.
Dialogue: 2,2:50:21.83,2:50:23.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the very least they are a little bit different,
Dialogue: 2,2:50:23.68,2:50:25.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they offer a fresh perspective
Dialogue: 2,2:50:25.76,2:50:31.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,on how a group of people might go about surviving in a world that's this messed up.
Dialogue: 2,2:50:31.04,2:50:36.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,I especially like it because so often these types of narratives are completely drowned out
Dialogue: 2,2:50:36.84,2:50:42.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,with cannibals and barbarians and looters and raiders,
Dialogue: 2,2:50:42.11,2:50:45.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,and basically everybody that you encountered in the first game.
Dialogue: 2,2:50:45.29,2:50:49.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's only in these more interesting and creative, in my opinion, stories
Dialogue: 2,2:50:49.92,2:50:52.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,where you find something that's a little bit different.
Dialogue: 2,2:50:52.91,2:50:58.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,Such as in {\i1}Mad Max{\i0}, the strange obsession and worship of gasoline and cars.
Dialogue: 2,2:50:58.79,2:51:01.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's something that's just really cool, and different.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:01.64,2:51:02.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I digress.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:02.90,2:51:08.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby pushes through this checkpoint and officially enters Scars' territory.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:08.24,2:51:11.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,Here we'll fight a ton of Scars,
Dialogue: 2,2:51:11.59,2:51:15.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,and believe me, you're going to be ploughing through them by the end of this sequence.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:23.09,2:51:26.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's actually a great many boss fight here that I really enjoyed
Dialogue: 2,2:51:26.06,2:51:29.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,with a woman that I can only assume is named Helga.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:29.12,2:51:32.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't actually know if her name is Helga by the way
Dialogue: 2,2:51:32.12,2:51:34.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying that because she looks like Helga.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:34.28,2:51:38.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless Abby bites off a part of her ear, which I thought was kind of funny.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:38.93,2:51:41.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,But eventually a bunch of her friends come over.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:41.00,2:51:43.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,They overpower Abby and knock her out,
Dialogue: 2,2:51:43.10,2:51:47.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,which then leads straight into a flashback to four months before.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:47.55,2:51:52.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,This would place this flashback right before the events of the prologue,
Dialogue: 2,2:51:52.43,2:51:55.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Abby and her whole group left for Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,2:51:55.55,2:52:00.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's Winter, Abby finds Owen in the aquarium with a bunch of pretty lights put up.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:00.32,2:52:01.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's really relaxing,
Dialogue: 2,2:52:01.73,2:52:08.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it really is this calming contrast that's the name of the game for the second half of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:08.70,2:52:10.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Something horrible will happen,
Dialogue: 2,2:52:10.52,2:52:13.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then we'll see something pretty and relaxing,
Dialogue: 2,2:52:13.16,2:52:16.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then something, even more horrible will happen.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:16.19,2:52:19.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then we cut back to a nice winter scene, and so on.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:19.68,2:52:24.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,In here there's actually many game where you can shoot some targets with a kitty bow and arrow.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:24.17,2:52:29.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's pretty damn stupid, but it gives the players something to do that isn't just talking.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:29.15,2:52:34.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Otherwise this entire flashback would simply be Abby, talking to Owen,
Dialogue: 2,2:52:34.04,2:52:37.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,walking up some stairs and then talking some more.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:37.04,2:52:42.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not to say that Naughty Dogs afraid of doing that in games or having a 10 minute cut scene,
Dialogue: 2,2:52:42.44,2:52:45.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it seems to me that if they can avoid it, they will,
Dialogue: 2,2:52:45.47,2:52:49.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they'll interspersed little mini game such as this to break up the monotony.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:49.48,2:52:53.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now the point of the sequence, though, is to show that Abby found Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,2:52:53.45,2:52:57.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,or, at the very least has a lead that he's living in Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,2:52:57.56,2:53:02.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the point, of course, is that they hope that Tommy could help them find Joel.
Dialogue: 2,2:53:02.48,2:53:05.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, we know that Joel was living there too,
Dialogue: 2,2:53:05.24,2:53:08.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,But apparently, at this time Abby didn't know that.
Dialogue: 2,2:53:08.09,2:53:09.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not clear to me at least
Dialogue: 2,2:53:09.86,2:53:14.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,if Abby still thought they were looking only for Tommy in the opening sequence,
Dialogue: 2,2:53:14.81,2:53:18.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,or if by that time she thinks that Joel could be there too.
Dialogue: 2,2:53:18.02,2:53:22.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I mean some of the dialogue seems to imply that she's looking for Joel primarily,
Dialogue: 2,2:53:22.79,2:53:25.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,but that they only expected to find Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,2:53:25.25,2:53:28.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,But again, I just don't think it matters too much.
Dialogue: 2,2:53:28.01,2:53:32.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,The point is they're going to Jackson for Joel by way of Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,2:53:32.78,2:53:35.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,and if Joel happens to be there, great.
Dialogue: 2,2:53:35.03,2:53:41.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,But they mostly expect to find Tommy and hope to convince him to share Joel's location or whereabouts.
Dialogue: 2,2:53:41.42,2:53:45.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless after breaking to Owen that she has a lead on Joel's brother
Dialogue: 2,2:53:45.78,2:53:49.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby also throws out the fact that Isaac approved the whole squad,
Dialogue: 2,2:53:49.82,2:53:52.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,leaving for weeks on end to chase Joel down.
Dialogue: 2,2:53:52.88,2:53:56.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,She exclaims that Isaac is more about justice than any one,
Dialogue: 2,2:53:56.69,2:53:59.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why he apparently approves of the plan
Dialogue: 2,2:53:59.16,2:54:03.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,for them to leave for weeks and weeks on end, potentially months
Dialogue: 2,2:54:03.21,2:54:07.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,trying to hunt down a guy that did something terrible years and years ago.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:07.79,2:54:11.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,To me, it seems like a stretch that he would be willing to let this many people go,
Dialogue: 2,2:54:11.90,2:54:16.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially young whippersnappers, who were involved in the active patrolling
Dialogue: 2,2:54:16.12,2:54:19.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,and maintenance of the WLF's defenses.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:19.22,2:54:21.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless, maybe that's just me.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:21.84,2:54:28.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,And may be it actually is within Isaac's character to let them go but it seems like a stretch to me.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:28.22,2:54:31.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,After a brief debate back and forth, they settle on it.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:31.40,2:54:34.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're going to Jackson, they're going to try to find Tommy,
Dialogue: 2,2:54:34.70,2:54:38.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then they're going to try and find Joel, once and for all, and finish it.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:38.93,2:54:41.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now we cut back to the forest.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:41.15,2:54:46.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is actually the trailer sequence that we saw back when we first met Abby years ago.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:46.64,2:54:49.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,I remember when I first saw this scene in the trailer,
Dialogue: 2,2:54:49.22,2:54:53.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,I thought that Abby was going to turn out to be Ellie's mom in this flashback,
Dialogue: 2,2:54:53.54,2:54:55.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,But… well…
Dialogue: 2,2:54:55.34,2:54:56.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,I was wrong.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:56.72,2:54:58.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Like… really wrong.
Dialogue: 2,2:54:58.76,2:55:01.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Scars start to string up Abby for execution
Dialogue: 2,2:55:01.30,2:55:04.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,when they're interrupted by a young girl that they've just captured.
Dialogue: 2,2:55:17.51,2:55:21.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now we don't know what this means, but for simplicity's sake,
Dialogue: 2,2:55:21.11,2:55:25.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,this girl Yara and the other apostate, whoever they may be,
Dialogue: 2,2:55:25.07,2:55:27.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,did something to piss off the Scars.
Dialogue: 2,2:55:27.41,2:55:34.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,After Yara spits in this elder Scars face, she is sentenced to having her wings clipped,
Dialogue: 2,2:55:34.61,2:55:35.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I have to say,
Dialogue: 2,2:55:35.78,2:55:40.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,this is probably the least clippy way they could have possibly clipped her wings.
Dialogue: 2,2:55:40.22,2:55:44.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,The other apostate shows up who will eventually find out his name Lev.
Dialogue: 2,2:55:44.45,2:55:47.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Lev starts shooting arrows at the Seraphites,
Dialogue: 2,2:55:47.00,2:55:48.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,killing a couple of them.
Dialogue: 2,2:55:48.38,2:55:52.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,And after a brief tussle with the elder, she's also killed.
Dialogue: 2,2:55:52.26,2:55:57.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,Following Yara's direction, Lev cuts Abby down, just in time for her to not die.
Dialogue: 2,2:55:57.38,2:55:59.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean seriously, she was really close.
Dialogue: 2,2:55:59.48,2:56:05.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,They just kind of left her hanging here after she killed the elder little… little ridiculous,
Dialogue: 2,2:56:05.51,2:56:10.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,but you know whatever she was just hang in there, and… and that's that.
Dialogue: 2,2:56:10.80,2:56:14.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,After Abby's cut down, they all prep to fight some zombies,
Dialogue: 2,2:56:14.18,2:56:17.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,just in case that you forgot that this game actually has zombies in it,
Dialogue: 2,2:56:17.42,2:56:20.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,because at this point it's been a hot minute since they were featured.
Dialogue: 2,2:56:20.48,2:56:22.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,And a fun little fact, and something to notice is that
Dialogue: 2,2:56:22.80,2:56:29.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,this rash and brews over Abby's neck will actually remain for the rest of the main story.
Dialogue: 2,2:56:29.36,2:56:31.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a great detail, and it really helps with immersion,
Dialogue: 2,2:56:31.49,2:56:34.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially as later scenes come and go,
Dialogue: 2,2:56:34.58,2:56:37.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,you'll see Abby rubbing her neck because it still hurts,
Dialogue: 2,2:56:37.97,2:56:40.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,because after all she was just hung from it.
Dialogue: 2,2:56:40.70,2:56:43.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's this attention to detail that Naughty Dog is really known for
Dialogue: 2,2:56:43.74,2:56:45.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that you have to compliment them on.
Dialogue: 2,2:56:45.68,2:56:48.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,These scenes are filmed months apart from each other
Dialogue: 2,2:56:48.87,2:56:52.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,in some cases, years apart after rewrites and reshoots,
Dialogue: 2,2:56:52.82,2:56:55.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then changing the game and level design around them,
Dialogue: 2,2:56:55.34,2:56:58.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,they have to reshoot it because the level design change.
Dialogue: 2,2:56:58.40,2:57:02.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,This amount of detail that's thrown in shows just how much they care.
Dialogue: 2,2:57:02.40,2:57:07.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,They made notes of absolutely everything that was going on with the character
Dialogue: 2,2:57:07.23,2:57:11.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that months after the fact, they would be able to reference back and say,
Dialogue: 2,2:57:11.03,2:57:14.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,"Oh, Abby's neck was sore here because she was hung from it,
Dialogue: 2,2:57:14.78,2:57:19.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,just a few hours of gameplay before this in the game's timeline,
Dialogue: 2,2:57:19.10,2:57:22.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,so make sure that that's reflected in your performance."
Dialogue: 2,2:57:22.43,2:57:25.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,That level of detail is something that's really rare
Dialogue: 2,2:57:25.16,2:57:30.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,you mostly only see it in Hollywood, and even then you don't see it on very many productions.
Dialogue: 2,2:57:30.56,2:57:35.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,But anyway, you escape the infected and come upon your old friend, Helga,
Dialogue: 2,2:57:35.09,2:57:37.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,attacking Lev who was leaving the pack.
Dialogue: 2,2:57:37.25,2:57:41.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,You have a quick fist fight where you eventually finish her with a hammer to…
Dialogue: 2,2:57:41.93,2:57:43.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,well, the face.
Dialogue: 2,2:57:43.56,2:57:45.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Abby gets her stuff back
Dialogue: 2,2:57:45.16,2:57:50.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,because Helga just happened to be wearing Abby's backpack after capturing her earlier.
Dialogue: 2,2:57:50.33,2:57:52.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,I actually thought this was kind of a fun touch,
Dialogue: 2,2:57:52.34,2:57:56.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,since the normal way that you would find all of your gear after being kidnapped like this in a video game
Dialogue: 2,2:57:56.67,2:58:00.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,would be to just find it in a chest or sitting on a desk somewhere.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:00.35,2:58:03.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now there's some dialogue here about the Seraphites and the WLF
Dialogue: 2,2:58:03.72,2:58:06.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's strange for them to trust each other.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:06.14,2:58:10.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,But at this point they've both saved each other's lives,
Dialogue: 2,2:58:10.19,2:58:12.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why it's a little more understandable.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:12.29,2:58:18.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby just saved Lev's life from Helga and Lev just saved Abby from hanging.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:18.65,2:58:23.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,There is a clear tit for tat here, which is why I think this blood pact is formed.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:23.21,2:58:26.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Abby eventually asks Lev the obvious question
Dialogue: 2,2:58:37.42,2:58:39.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Lev is being honest here,
Dialogue: 2,2:58:39.59,2:58:41.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it's far more complicated than it seems.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:41.96,2:58:44.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we're going to get to that later.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:44.24,2:58:50.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Your new little crew fights through waves of infected and slowly begin trusting each other more and more.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:50.87,2:58:55.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,The sequence actually climaxes with Abby carrying Yara while Lev keeps watch.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:55.82,2:58:59.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,You all push into a small office trailer and set up camp for the night.
Dialogue: 2,2:58:59.57,2:59:02.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Feeling bad for them, Abby helps Yara set her arm,
Dialogue: 2,2:59:02.57,2:59:05.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is clearly in some serious trouble.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:05.92,2:59:08.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,After helping them with this Abby leaves.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:08.45,2:59:12.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just as baffled as they are that she just helped a Seraphite.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:12.89,2:59:16.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,In yet another reflection between characters,
Dialogue: 2,2:59:16.07,2:59:20.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby has found herself in the same position that Owen found himself in.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:20.57,2:59:23.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,She seemingly helped a Scar,
Dialogue: 2,2:59:23.36,2:59:27.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is something that the WLF is never supposed to do.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:27.50,2:59:30.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is going to completely change the following scene,
Dialogue: 2,2:59:30.53,2:59:32.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,but we'll get to that in just a second.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:32.12,2:59:36.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,As Abby leaves Yara and Lev, her perplexion is palpable.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:36.17,2:59:40.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,She cares for these two kids, and she doesn't even really know why.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:40.25,2:59:44.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's the same emotion that the player is likely feeling towards Abby herself,
Dialogue: 2,2:59:44.45,2:59:47.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why it's so brilliant that it was done this way.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:47.96,2:59:52.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby is feeling the same confusion and inner conflict as the player.
Dialogue: 2,2:59:52.10,2:59:55.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in this case she's baffled that she's been made to feel sympathy
Dialogue: 2,2:59:55.60,2:59:58.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,for members of a group that she's supposed to hate,
Dialogue: 2,2:59:58.10,3:00:04.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,whereas we, the player likely feel that conflict because we want to hate Abby for killing Joel.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:04.56,3:00:06.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,And maybe a part of us still does,
Dialogue: 2,3:00:06.56,3:00:10.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,but at the very least we're beginning to sympathize with her and even care for her.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:10.94,3:00:12.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's masterfully done.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:12.56,3:00:16.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's this subtle character work that makes this game what it is.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:16.87,3:00:23.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,And why, in my opinion, you have to play it all the way through, even despite the pacing issues.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:23.61,3:00:27.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, eventually, Abby fights her way through a ton of infected in a shipping yard
Dialogue: 2,3:00:27.38,3:00:30.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,and finds her way to a series of boats and ships.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:30.71,3:00:35.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,You fight your way through another group of infected and stumble across a crossbow,
Dialogue: 2,3:00:35.69,3:00:38.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is actually my favorite weapon in the entire game.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:38.51,3:00:42.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,After you push through all of these infected you get to the aquarium where Owen is staying,
Dialogue: 2,3:00:42.68,3:00:45.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, you can't find Owen anywhere.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:45.59,3:00:50.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby starts to kind of freak out, worrying that he's dead or just abandoned and went AWOL.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:50.99,3:00:53.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,But eventually Abby stumbles on to him.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:53.18,3:00:56.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's sitting in the boat that he's been trying to fix up fridges.
Dialogue: 2,3:00:56.66,3:01:00.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it seems as though it's his one safe space left in the world.
Dialogue: 2,3:01:00.35,3:01:03.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Owen start talking, and…
Dialogue: 2,3:01:03.03,3:01:07.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,you know, I can't really explain this part in a good way,
Dialogue: 2,3:01:07.94,3:01:10.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,so I'm just going to let it play… so…
Dialogue: 2,3:05:17.78,3:05:21.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,So yeah, sexy times,
Dialogue: 2,3:05:21.56,3:05:23.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,I personally didn't see that coming at all,
Dialogue: 2,3:05:23.60,3:05:26.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I'll be honest I'm not entirely sure what to make of it.
Dialogue: 2,3:05:26.33,3:05:31.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,It kind of comes out of left field because they were fighting and then they start… start banging,
Dialogue: 2,3:05:31.43,3:05:34.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't… good for them, I mean, I guess it makes sense.
Dialogue: 2,3:05:34.31,3:05:37.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of tension and visceral emotion going on,
Dialogue: 2,3:05:37.67,3:05:41.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it seemed to come out of nowhere to me.
Dialogue: 2,3:05:41.50,3:05:45.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know, there's some deeper literary reason for this. I would love to hear it.
Dialogue: 2,3:05:45.86,3:05:50.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure I've thought about it, but I don't really know what to make of it.
Dialogue: 2,3:05:50.57,3:05:52.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,So… moving on.
Dialogue: 2,3:05:52.50,3:05:58.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seattle Day 1 wraps up with Abby having a bizarre nightmare about Yara and Lev being killed and strung up
Dialogue: 2,3:05:58.84,3:06:02.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,in the very same hospital room where her father died,
Dialogue: 2,3:06:02.93,3:06:08.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,which to me seems to imply that she feels some sort of familial attachment to them.
Dialogue: 2,3:06:08.33,3:06:13.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since in her dream they die in the same place that her father died.
Dialogue: 2,3:06:13.31,3:06:19.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,I really don't think you can understate the significance of her seeing them in this space.
Dialogue: 2,3:06:19.22,3:06:22.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,If she was stressing out purely about them being killed,
Dialogue: 2,3:06:22.31,3:06:26.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,why wouldn't she just have a nightmare where she imagines coming across their bodies
Dialogue: 2,3:06:26.33,3:06:28.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,as she was heading back to the WLF base.
Dialogue: 2,3:06:28.85,3:06:32.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fact that she has this dream and it set in the hospital is significant,
Dialogue: 2,3:06:32.90,3:06:38.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think it shows that she has a much deeper bond with these kids than even she realizes.
Dialogue: 2,3:06:38.63,3:06:44.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,So after this dream she decides that she needs to go and make sure that they're okay.
Dialogue: 2,3:06:44.12,3:06:47.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she's actually going to go and help Scars.
Dialogue: 2,3:06:47.95,3:06:52.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's just as baffled as any other WLF member would be,
Dialogue: 2,3:06:52.88,3:06:58.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it seems that she's coming to the realization that Owen also came to.
Dialogue: 2,3:06:58.49,3:07:00.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's done with all of it.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:00.83,3:07:02.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seattle Day 2.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:02.81,3:07:05.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,So after Abby wakes up she rushes back to the shipping yard
Dialogue: 2,3:07:05.84,3:07:07.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,to try and find Yara and Lev.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:07.76,3:07:11.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,She encounters a ton of Scars, including several Brutes,
Dialogue: 2,3:07:11.00,3:07:13.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,which leads to a fairly interesting combat encounter.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:13.91,3:07:16.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,After clearing them out, Abby heads back into the office trailer,
Dialogue: 2,3:07:16.82,3:07:20.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she finds Yara in really bad shape.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:20.15,3:07:22.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Her arm looks like a cherry laffey taffy,
Dialogue: 2,3:07:22.31,3:07:27.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's clear that it's going to need some… let's just say "severe treatment".
Dialogue: 2,3:07:27.11,3:07:32.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,So she picks Yara up and she brings her to the aquarium with Lev trailing close behind.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:32.78,3:07:38.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,Her plan is basically to have a Mel treat Yara's arm in whatever capacity that may take.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:38.33,3:07:41.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,Needless to say, this is a pretty big gamble.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:41.30,3:07:46.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because of Abby has found out and ratted out to Isaac and the other WLF members,
Dialogue: 2,3:07:46.97,3:07:52.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's likely going to end up either completely ostracized from the group,
Dialogue: 2,3:07:52.16,3:07:55.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,or downright executed for helping out their prime enemy.
Dialogue: 2,3:07:55.49,3:07:59.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sure, you could say that they are former members of the group now
Dialogue: 2,3:07:59.88,3:08:03.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that they should be helped because they are apostate from the group.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:03.53,3:08:05.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't really matter.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:05.24,3:08:10.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this type of situation, the enemy of the enemy is your friend.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:10.10,3:08:14.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this case, the enemy of the enemy is not actually your friend.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:14.60,3:08:17.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just somebody that you should ostracize and kill
Dialogue: 2,3:08:17.56,3:08:22.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,because complicated moral and ethical quandaries aren't worth the trouble
Dialogue: 2,3:08:22.25,3:08:24.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,in a post apocalyptic world.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:24.11,3:08:28.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless after taking a look and not initially freaking out,
Dialogue: 2,3:08:28.04,3:08:33.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Mel determines that the bone is completely shattered and that the arm has to come off
Dialogue: 2,3:08:33.32,3:08:35.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,if she has any chance of surviving.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:35.39,3:08:38.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,Mel then explains what she needs for this operation.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:38.39,3:08:42.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,She could just take a knife and hack at it and try to cauterize the wound with fire,
Dialogue: 2,3:08:42.74,3:08:44.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,as Owen points out.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:44.39,3:08:47.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,But this would likely lead to infection very quickly.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:47.63,3:08:50.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,If they're going to do this, they might as well do it right.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:50.30,3:08:53.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Mel requests to saw and some other surgical equipment.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:53.54,3:08:56.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby, says that she could get it from the hospital.
Dialogue: 2,3:08:56.18,3:09:00.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Problem being that the hospital, according to the WLF routes that are in place right now,
Dialogue: 2,3:09:00.77,3:09:07.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,is gonna take roughly a day to reach and then a day to return from, far too long for Yara.
Dialogue: 2,3:09:07.19,3:09:09.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's at this point that Lev offers help
Dialogue: 2,3:09:09.05,3:09:12.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,by giving access to the bridge system that the Scars used
Dialogue: 2,3:09:12.12,3:09:14.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,to navigate the city from the rooftops.
Dialogue: 2,3:09:14.36,3:09:18.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not clear exactly what this is going to be or what form it's going to take.
Dialogue: 2,3:09:19.01,3:09:23.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,It also, it's a little strange to me that the WLF member, such as Owen and Abby,
Dialogue: 2,3:09:23.36,3:09:27.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,don't seem to be aware of this bridge system whatsoever.
Dialogue: 2,3:09:27.50,3:09:31.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,They are aware that the Scars are able to navigate the city very quickly
Dialogue: 2,3:09:31.11,3:09:34.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,so quickly that it seems almost supernatural
Dialogue: 2,3:09:34.42,3:09:36.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,but apparently never occurred to them that
Dialogue: 2,3:09:36.33,3:09:41.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,they might be using bridge systems above the city by using the rooftops.
Dialogue: 2,3:09:41.69,3:09:46.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,The point is that Lev offers to give them access to this bridge system.
Dialogue: 2,3:09:46.52,3:09:48.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Lev knows these routes very well
Dialogue: 2,3:09:48.77,3:09:54.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,and says that they should be able to reach the hospital in around 2 hours if they were to follow the route.
Dialogue: 2,3:09:54.83,3:09:58.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so without much hesitation, Abby agrees and leaves.
Dialogue: 2,3:09:58.45,3:10:02.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,As they're leaving the aquarium, Owen stops Abby and tries to talk,
Dialogue: 2,3:10:02.12,3:10:07.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,but she is not interested in addressing what happened a night before with the sexy time.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:07.49,3:10:11.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it seems that she's found her new family and obsession.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:11.18,3:10:14.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is the first time that we've really seen her move past Owen
Dialogue: 2,3:10:14.48,3:10:18.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,and behave in a way that doesn't seem completely obsessive towards him.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:18.71,3:10:20.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's kind of refreshing to be honest.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:20.39,3:10:23.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Prior to this, it's very clear that Abby still has feelings for Owen.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:23.81,3:10:27.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,And even in the first chapter when we originally met Abby and Owen
Dialogue: 2,3:10:27.86,3:10:30.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,when their overlooking snow-crested Jackson,
Dialogue: 2,3:10:30.41,3:10:35.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,We saw that Abby and Owen shared a strange tension.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:35.18,3:10:39.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Owen can never really get on the same page after her father died.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:39.32,3:10:43.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,And quite obviously, since Joel's death, nothing has changed.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:43.85,3:10:48.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is lead Owen sticking with Mel, even though they're pretty clearly not compatible
Dialogue: 2,3:10:48.40,3:10:51.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,and even don't seem to particularly like each other.
Dialogue: 2,3:10:51.41,3:10:54.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm not entirely sure if this was intentional or not,
Dialogue: 2,3:10:54.02,3:11:00.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,but the fact that there's zero chemistry between Owen and Mel seems pretty obvious to me.
Dialogue: 2,3:11:00.32,3:11:05.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if the writers are even somewhat competent, as I believe they are over at Naughty Dog,
Dialogue: 2,3:11:05.00,3:11:06.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,surely somebody noticed this.
Dialogue: 2,3:11:06.65,3:11:11.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,So either it was masterful performance on the part of the actors and the writers to make sure that
Dialogue: 2,3:11:11.80,3:11:17.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,these characters didn't seem to have that much in common didn't seem to get along particularly well,
Dialogue: 2,3:11:17.90,3:11:21.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that they had an immense amount of tension brewing between them.
Dialogue: 2,3:11:21.89,3:11:25.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Either that was completely intentional or it was an accident,
Dialogue: 2,3:11:25.94,3:11:28.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it was the result of a misfire and the writing.
Dialogue: 2,3:11:28.22,3:11:30.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it's the former personally.
Dialogue: 2,3:11:30.11,3:11:34.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think that Mel and Owen are supposed to come off as a little strange.
Dialogue: 2,3:11:34.97,3:11:38.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everyone else in the group seems to be aware that their relationship is a little bizarre
Dialogue: 2,3:11:38.93,3:11:42.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that Owen and Abby seem to have feelings for each other
Dialogue: 2,3:11:42.56,3:11:44.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they're confused as to why they are not just together.
Dialogue: 2,3:11:44.90,3:11:49.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that tension will eventually be resolved, just… just wait.
Dialogue: 2,3:11:49.68,3:11:52.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,After leaving the aquarium, Abby and Lev head to the tower
Dialogue: 2,3:11:52.63,3:11:54.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they need to climb all the way to the top of
Dialogue: 2,3:11:54.71,3:11:57.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order to gain access to the aforementioned "bridge".
Dialogue: 2,3:11:57.68,3:12:02.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's pretty damn high up there, and it happens to be covered by clouds and fog.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:02.81,3:12:07.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is a nice and coincidentally thing because it adds to the tension of the situation.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:07.61,3:12:13.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't answer the question as to how the WLF weren't aware of this bridge system.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:13.11,3:12:17.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because chances are, it's not always cloudy and foggy
Dialogue: 2,3:12:17.09,3:12:20.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,to the point where you can't see to the top of these skyscrapers.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:20.36,3:12:24.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Surely somebody saw these bridges when the sky was clear.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:24.35,3:12:29.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems bizarre to me that the WLF didn't feel the need to explore these bridge systems
Dialogue: 2,3:12:29.71,3:12:35.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,that seemed to go perfectly between skyscrapers and buildings very high up,
Dialogue: 2,3:12:35.48,3:12:38.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially when they would have been visible from the ground.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:38.27,3:12:40.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I guess that's just me.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:40.25,3:12:43.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, as Abby and Lev are heading to the top of this tower,
Dialogue: 2,3:12:43.79,3:12:47.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,they climbed through multiple buildings, explore some different areas,
Dialogue: 2,3:12:47.51,3:12:50.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they share in a few interesting conversations.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:50.57,3:12:53.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now there's nothing really crazy here, it's mostly awkward small talk,
Dialogue: 2,3:12:53.87,3:12:57.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it mostly serves to show that they are growing more comfortable with each other.
Dialogue: 2,3:12:57.92,3:13:01.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,My personal favorite moment is when they come across somebody's apartment,
Dialogue: 2,3:13:01.13,3:13:03.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,who was clearly very into gaming.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:03.95,3:13:06.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, they even still have their D&D game set up
Dialogue: 2,3:13:06.60,3:13:09.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they have their Playstation gear scattered throughout the apartment.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:09.95,3:13:11.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's kind of cool.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:11.09,3:13:14.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,And personally, I would like to think that this whole apartment is modeled
Dialogue: 2,3:13:14.57,3:13:16.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,after one of the developers apartments.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:16.55,3:13:21.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've heard stories of developers from Bethesda and Rocksteady doing this type of thing
Dialogue: 2,3:13:21.76,3:13:25.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they take an environment model it after their own personal environment
Dialogue: 2,3:13:25.40,3:13:27.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,because after all, that's what they know.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:27.20,3:13:30.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a little piece of the real world in this imaginary world,
Dialogue: 2,3:13:30.83,3:13:33.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I just think that it's super cool.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:33.02,3:13:38.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I thought that this particular building was especially detailed.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:38.15,3:13:40.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,The two travel through a plethora of buildings,
Dialogue: 2,3:13:40.64,3:13:42.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,they push through some rapids,
Dialogue: 2,3:13:42.65,3:13:46.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they eventually land on a construction site that's next to the target building.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:46.70,3:13:48.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it just so happens that in this construction site
Dialogue: 2,3:13:48.87,3:13:52.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,is one of the most interesting combat arenas of the entire game.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:52.64,3:13:57.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's a ton of verticality here and there's a lot of Seraphites scattered throughout.
Dialogue: 2,3:13:57.40,3:14:00.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Some of them are Brutes, some of them have short range weapons,
Dialogue: 2,3:14:00.53,3:14:02.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,and some of them have long range weapons.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:02.87,3:14:06.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's really interesting how they laid all of this out and on harder difficulties.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:06.32,3:14:09.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let me just tell you it kicked my ass a few times.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:09.47,3:14:11.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's important to say that it felt fair.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:11.96,3:14:17.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,It wasn't as though I was getting my ass handed to me, and I felt like I was being slighted
Dialogue: 2,3:14:17.16,3:14:21.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,like a poorly designed boss that's able to clip through walls or something.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:21.29,3:14:23.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,This level feels completely fair.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:23.18,3:14:28.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,It just seems like a difficult situation where Lev and Abby have to work perfectly in tandem.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:28.22,3:14:30.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,And when that happens, things work out.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:30.47,3:14:32.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,But after clearing this area,
Dialogue: 2,3:14:32.45,3:14:37.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,the two get into an industrial elevator that they can take all the way to the top to reach the bridge.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:37.85,3:14:41.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, if you remember from earlier Abby's worst nightmare is heights.
Dialogue: 2,3:14:41.83,3:14:46.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Here, Lev actually shares a bit of sweet advice to try and take out his mind off of the terror
Dialogue: 2,3:14:46.86,3:14:50.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,that she feels due to the enormous and ever increasing heights.
Dialogue: 2,3:15:29.09,3:15:32.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, at the top of the skyscraper, they begin crossing the bridge,
Dialogue: 2,3:15:32.18,3:15:35.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is actually just a partially collapsed crane.
Dialogue: 2,3:15:35.60,3:15:41.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,This again reaffirms the point that the WLF probably should have seen this crane on a clear day
Dialogue: 2,3:15:41.67,3:15:44.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,and been intrigued enough to go and investigate it.
Dialogue: 2,3:15:44.15,3:15:46.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe even claiming it for themselves.
Dialogue: 2,3:15:46.10,3:15:50.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's a line or something that mentions why the WLF haven't used this bridge,
Dialogue: 2,3:15:50.69,3:15:55.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I just missed it or I couldn't think of it or remember it when writing the script.
Dialogue: 2,3:15:55.58,3:15:58.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,But either way, if there is something, let me know.
Dialogue: 2,3:15:58.19,3:16:03.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, understandably, Abby starts crossing the bridge and begins to completely freak out.
Dialogue: 2,3:16:03.44,3:16:07.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,To be honest, any normal person would probably be freaking out at this point,
Dialogue: 2,3:16:07.73,3:16:10.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's just people who are afraid of heights.
Dialogue: 2,3:16:10.10,3:16:14.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the fact that Abby is completely and utterly petrified by heights,
Dialogue: 2,3:16:14.15,3:16:17.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think just proves the point that this is not a good time for her.
Dialogue: 2,3:16:17.78,3:16:20.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's actually while crossing this makeshift bridge,
Dialogue: 2,3:16:20.63,3:16:24.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Lev throws out one of the funniest lines of the entire game,
Dialogue: 2,3:16:24.65,3:16:28.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least as far as I'm concerned, because it comes out of absolutely nowhere.
Dialogue: 2,3:16:36.99,3:16:38.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,Hah… I love it!
Dialogue: 2,3:16:38.41,3:16:40.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now after crossing the first bridge,
Dialogue: 2,3:16:40.00,3:16:43.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,it seems as though they've finished and gotten through the hardest part.
Dialogue: 2,3:16:43.12,3:16:44.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,But… NO.
Dialogue: 2,3:16:52.57,3:16:54.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now this is one of the few times I really remember
Dialogue: 2,3:16:54.68,3:16:58.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,being completely blown away by a set piece in this game.
Dialogue: 2,3:16:58.36,3:17:03.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,The bridge is beautiful and yet creepy at the same time.
Dialogue: 2,3:17:03.34,3:17:06.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the hospital in the distance is also all inspiring,
Dialogue: 2,3:17:06.40,3:17:11.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,and serves its purpose very well in informing the player of where they are within Seattle.
Dialogue: 2,3:17:11.29,3:17:13.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,I will say, though it was a little disappointing
Dialogue: 2,3:17:13.40,3:17:17.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,because there was some artifacting in Z-fighting on the textures when I first played,
Dialogue: 2,3:17:17.20,3:17:19.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I can get over it.
Dialogue: 2,3:17:19.09,3:17:22.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's pretty rare to see a graphical glitch like this in a Naughty Dog games
Dialogue: 2,3:17:22.54,3:17:23.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,so I'm letting it slide.
Dialogue: 2,3:17:23.89,3:17:26.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,But just like that, Abby crosses the bridge.
Dialogue: 2,3:17:26.96,3:17:29.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's conquered her fears with the Lev's help.
Dialogue: 2,3:17:29.76,3:17:33.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's achieved that which she thought was unachievable
Dialogue: 2,3:17:33.94,3:17:36.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,that she could cross this grand expanse…
Dialogue: 2,3:17:36.43,3:17:37.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,… Oh, my God! She fell!
Dialogue: 2,3:18:02.62,3:18:04.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, yeah, she… she falls.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:04.74,3:18:06.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,Good thing there is a penthouse pool right?
Dialogue: 2,3:18:06.42,3:18:08.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now the new dynamic duo decides
Dialogue: 2,3:18:08.48,3:18:11.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,to work their way to the bottom of the tower now that they've crossed
Dialogue: 2,3:18:11.52,3:18:15.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once at the base, they are going to be able to head straight for the hospital.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:15.78,3:18:20.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,Throughout the descent, there's a few hordes that you fight through of infected.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:20.59,3:18:26.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby also finds a flame thrower, which is probably the best hoard weapon in the entire game.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:26.20,3:18:27.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because it has such a widespread.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:27.97,3:18:31.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,It makes it really easy to handle crowds and large numbers of infected.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:31.90,3:18:34.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I will say that ammo is so limited.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:34.09,3:18:39.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,It makes it really hard to use it in any sort of consistent way.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:39.04,3:18:41.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'll also say that this tower actually excited me.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:41.92,3:18:44.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,I thought there would be some really cool opportunities for
Dialogue: 2,3:18:44.75,3:18:48.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,different combat sequences with a lot of verticality.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:48.10,3:18:53.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,And maybe some platforming with the rope mechanic… some thing,
Dialogue: 2,3:18:53.38,3:18:55.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,but really there's not much here.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:55.30,3:18:58.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,You just kind of make your way to the bottom of the tower, and that's it.
Dialogue: 2,3:18:58.30,3:19:03.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,After fighting through a few rooms of infected, seems like a missed opportunity.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:03.25,3:19:06.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless, they get to the bottom, and they come out right by the hospital.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:06.94,3:19:11.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this is actually the same exact area that Ellie entered the hospital earlier
Dialogue: 2,3:19:11.18,3:19:14.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,or in continuity I guess after this.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:14.44,3:19:20.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then this is probably a good time to bring up the fact that there are a lot of reused areas in the game.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:20.05,3:19:22.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,This has been something that a lot of people have criticized.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:22.42,3:19:27.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,That Naughty Dog seems to just be recycling the same maps and levels with different characters,
Dialogue: 2,3:19:27.46,3:19:30.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,or in this case just between Abby and Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:30.61,3:19:35.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I don't think it's actually fair to criticize them purely because they reuse levels.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:35.26,3:19:39.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,A level in a video game at least seems to be, in my estimation,
Dialogue: 2,3:19:39.97,3:19:43.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,a collection of different items, a lay out of a map,
Dialogue: 2,3:19:43.08,3:19:46.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,and in general, a pool of possibilities.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:46.33,3:19:51.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,Different things that the player can do to interact with that level to achieve a set goal.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:51.43,3:19:54.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,A really simple level would just be a room with a door.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:54.52,3:19:59.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,You walked to the door, open it and leave, you've completed the level.
Dialogue: 2,3:19:59.08,3:20:04.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, a complicated level would be one in which you have a complicated goal,
Dialogue: 2,3:20:04.06,3:20:07.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,such as making it out of this area alive.
Dialogue: 2,3:20:07.53,3:20:11.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then the developer complicates the achieving of that goal
Dialogue: 2,3:20:11.17,3:20:16.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,by introducing many different enemies that you could fight complicated traversal,
Dialogue: 2,3:20:16.33,3:20:20.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,or maybe even a puzzle that you have to solve in order to get through the door.
Dialogue: 2,3:20:20.29,3:20:23.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is how you take a level from something as simple as walking through a door
Dialogue: 2,3:20:23.94,3:20:26.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,into something more complicated and engaging for the player.
Dialogue: 2,3:20:26.83,3:20:27.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,For this reason,
Dialogue: 2,3:20:27.55,3:20:32.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's completely fair to say that Naughty Dog is purely reusing levels here.
Dialogue: 2,3:20:32.65,3:20:38.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because Abby and Ellie interact with these levels in completely different ways.
Dialogue: 2,3:20:38.71,3:20:42.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,When Abby's walking through the hospital here and eventually finds Nora,
Dialogue: 2,3:20:42.52,3:20:45.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's not actually fighting these people.
Dialogue: 2,3:20:45.64,3:20:47.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's not shooting them,
Dialogue: 2,3:20:47.08,3:20:50.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's not throwing bombs and molotovs on them.
Dialogue: 2,3:20:50.20,3:20:52.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's just walking and talking,
Dialogue: 2,3:20:52.42,3:20:56.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,not to mention that you also go to areas of the hospital that were unseen by Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,3:20:56.62,3:20:59.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,And when you compare this to Ellie traverse this level,
Dialogue: 2,3:20:59.35,3:21:01.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,well, it's pretty different.
Dialogue: 2,3:21:01.25,3:21:05.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now if your point is that they are clearly taking short cuts in terms of development
Dialogue: 2,3:21:05.95,3:21:10.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,by putting these characters in the same levels and structuring the story in that way,
Dialogue: 2,3:21:10.84,3:21:14.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think you can make that point, and perhaps that's fair.
Dialogue: 2,3:21:14.89,3:21:20.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't see the inherent problem with reusing a level if it makes sense in the story
Dialogue: 2,3:21:20.64,3:21:24.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,or if you write the story in a way where that makes sense
Dialogue: 2,3:21:24.54,3:21:29.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,because a quality game can be set in something as small as a couple of hallways.
Dialogue: 2,3:21:29.86,3:21:33.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Look at something like P.T., which was technically just a playable teaser,
Dialogue: 2,3:21:33.70,3:21:36.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,but even that was considered to be wildly successful,
Dialogue: 2,3:21:36.85,3:21:43.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it only really took place in two hallways, a back room and a bathroom I suppose.
Dialogue: 2,3:21:43.65,3:21:47.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's really all there was to it, and yet it was phenomenal.
Dialogue: 2,3:21:47.17,3:21:49.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,You can knit pick something as simple as
Dialogue: 2,3:21:49.41,3:21:53.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,how many times a particular mesh is used throughout a game,
Dialogue: 2,3:21:53.11,3:21:57.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,or you can argue your point based on how the game uses that asset.
Dialogue: 2,3:21:57.76,3:22:01.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think the latter is much more reasonable and much more defensible.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:01.78,3:22:03.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I digress.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:03.19,3:22:06.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby heads into the hospital alone, leaving Lev behind
Dialogue: 2,3:22:06.41,3:22:12.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,because quite obviously, if Lev were seen anywhere near the hospital, we wouldn't survive for very long.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:12.55,3:22:15.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby plays it cool with all of the WLF members.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:15.43,3:22:20.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's only a matter of time before everybody finds out that Abby's disobeyed Isaac's orders.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:20.29,3:22:23.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think Abby knows this, which is why she's moving through the level pretty quickly,
Dialogue: 2,3:22:23.74,3:22:26.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,trying to find the materials that she needs and leave.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:26.62,3:22:30.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean not to mention also that the girl that she's getting the materials for
Dialogue: 2,3:22:30.56,3:22:33.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,is on death's door that probably motivates her,
Dialogue: 2,3:22:33.64,3:22:37.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,her rushing a little bit, but by who am I to say.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:37.01,3:22:40.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,You walk through here, talking a few people and… oh look!
Dialogue: 2,3:22:40.63,3:22:45.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's the Vita girl that Ellie stabbed and crap out of earlier,
Dialogue: 2,3:22:45.03,3:22:50.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,or I guess later, because he or she is still alive, that's… that's funny.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:50.24,3:22:53.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Abby doesn't make it far into the hospital though.
Dialogue: 2,3:22:53.06,3:22:55.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's arrested once they check in with Isaac
Dialogue: 2,3:22:55.33,3:22:58.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,and find out that she has actually been AWOL since the day before,
Dialogue: 2,3:22:58.57,3:23:01.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,so she's locked up in the elevator.
Dialogue: 2,3:23:01.21,3:23:06.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's basically gonna held until they transport everything back to the front base with Isaac,
Dialogue: 2,3:23:06.85,3:23:08.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,where she'll be dealt with.
Dialogue: 2,3:23:08.09,3:23:10.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again this is something that was mentioned several times,
Dialogue: 2,3:23:10.53,3:23:14.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,not just to Abby, but also that Ellie overheard there is something going on with WLF
Dialogue: 2,3:23:14.86,3:23:17.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they need all of their supplies at the front base.
Dialogue: 2,3:23:17.86,3:23:22.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,And they're also collecting all of the WLF members to that same front base.
Dialogue: 2,3:23:22.51,3:23:26.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's something happening, Isaac's mobilizing everybody.
Dialogue: 2,3:23:26.58,3:23:28.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Something's about to go down.
Dialogue: 2,3:23:28.09,3:23:33.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Isaac mentioned earlier that he's planning on doing one final push into the Seraphites' island
Dialogue: 2,3:23:33.56,3:23:36.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they have to finish the war once and for all.
Dialogue: 2,3:23:36.34,3:23:39.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a pretty big deal because without a doubt,
Dialogue: 2,3:23:39.01,3:23:43.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,many hundreds or even thousands of people are about to die.
Dialogue: 2,3:23:43.27,3:23:46.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,I could have seen an alternative timeline or storyline
Dialogue: 2,3:23:46.39,3:23:51.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,where Abby instead of going after just materials to save Yara
Dialogue: 2,3:23:51.22,3:23:56.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,decides to go and try and stop this invasion to save all of the lives of the Seraphites
Dialogue: 2,3:23:56.35,3:24:00.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the lives of the WLF that will be wasted in this endeavor.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:00.34,3:24:04.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I understand that this is probably a little more relatable,
Dialogue: 2,3:24:04.27,3:24:08.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially because when you can emotionally attached the player to one character,
Dialogue: 2,3:24:08.86,3:24:12.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,in this case, Yara, and in another instance Lev.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:12.70,3:24:16.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,You can do a lot more compared to if you are trying to make the player
Dialogue: 2,3:24:16.13,3:24:19.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,feel emotionally engaged and attached to an organization
Dialogue: 2,3:24:19.80,3:24:23.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,such as the WLF, or a cult, such as the Seraphites.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:23.80,3:24:27.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, while Abby's locked up in the elevator, Nora I just happened to come by.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:27.78,3:24:30.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,And she comes in clutch, and let's Abby go.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:30.43,3:24:33.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is actually why she was in trouble with the WLF members
Dialogue: 2,3:24:33.04,3:24:36.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,back in Ellie section when she was climbing through the vent.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:36.10,3:24:40.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's because they think that Nora let Abby go, because well, she did.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:40.37,3:24:42.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again I think it's really cool to get a fresh understanding of
Dialogue: 2,3:24:42.89,3:24:45.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,everything that was going on with this new perspective.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:45.79,3:24:47.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you don't need to know everything
Dialogue: 2,3:24:47.58,3:24:52.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,that was going on to have an enjoyable game, play experience or narrative experience.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:52.75,3:24:57.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's plenty of examples of books that don't really explain much of anything of what's going on.
Dialogue: 2,3:24:57.64,3:25:02.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,They just cannot leave it there and leave it for your personal interpretation.
Dialogue: 2,3:25:02.08,3:25:05.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,In {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}, however, everything's been thought through,
Dialogue: 2,3:25:05.11,3:25:10.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least to a certain extent such that you're able to go back through with this new perspective,
Dialogue: 2,3:25:10.33,3:25:15.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,learn more and figure out why these characters were doing what they were doing.
Dialogue: 2,3:25:15.28,3:25:20.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,They weren't just moving materials from one location to the other to be convenient for the game story.
Dialogue: 2,3:25:20.80,3:25:24.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,But rather there is an overarching theme and idea behind it,
Dialogue: 2,3:25:24.22,3:25:28.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though that invasion has nothing to do with Ellie
Dialogue: 2,3:25:28.00,3:25:33.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,and really would never have been brought up if Ellie's story is where the game ended.
Dialogue: 2,3:25:33.43,3:25:38.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, Nora leads Abby to the basement to let her collect the stuff that she needs for Yara's arm.
Dialogue: 2,3:25:38.26,3:25:42.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know exactly who she's helping out or why she needs everything that she needs.
Dialogue: 2,3:25:42.46,3:25:45.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,But what she does know is that these surgical materials
Dialogue: 2,3:25:45.45,3:25:49.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,are probably going to be used for the betterment of somebody's life.
Dialogue: 2,3:25:49.93,3:25:54.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,And she knows also that all of the other materials in the rest of the hospital have been picked clean
Dialogue: 2,3:25:54.96,3:25:58.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,and are being brought to the forward base where Isaac wants them.
Dialogue: 2,3:25:58.33,3:26:02.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so the only place that's left for Abby to collect these items would be the basement.
Dialogue: 2,3:26:02.89,3:26:09.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,Problem being, when the outbreak initially happened in 2013, on outbreak day,
Dialogue: 2,3:26:09.79,3:26:12.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,everybody was brought to the hospital.
Dialogue: 2,3:26:12.08,3:26:17.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,With this obviously, there was a massive outbreak within the hospital itself
Dialogue: 2,3:26:17.22,3:26:20.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and eventually everything was quarantined off.
Dialogue: 2,3:26:20.02,3:26:25.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,The doors were locked and the stairs destroyed such that the infected couldn't reach the upper levels
Dialogue: 2,3:26:25.75,3:26:28.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,and would be trapped in the basement indefinitely.
Dialogue: 2,3:26:28.75,3:26:30.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, if you played the original {\i1}TLOU{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,3:26:30.37,3:26:34.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,you know that zombies don't tend to age like a fine wine.
Dialogue: 2,3:26:34.66,3:26:39.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,The more serious and severe zombies in the world of {\i1}TLOU{\i0} come with age.
Dialogue: 2,3:26:39.49,3:26:44.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means that all of the zombies and infected that you're going to see in the basement
Dialogue: 2,3:26:44.31,3:26:47.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,have likely been there for a quarter century.
Dialogue: 2,3:26:47.86,3:26:54.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,That makes them some of the most dangerous and severe infected in this entire city.
Dialogue: 2,3:26:54.25,3:26:58.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I don't know about you guys, but the second that I figured this out,
Dialogue: 2,3:26:58.09,3:27:00.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,I knew that we are probably going to end up finding
Dialogue: 2,3:27:00.46,3:27:04.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,a new type of infected or at the very least a new boss.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:04.21,3:27:06.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I was damn ready for that.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:06.16,3:27:09.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,The infected in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} seemed to be a bit of an afterthought.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:09.64,3:27:14.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's not a whole lot of focus on them, and I get it, there's a lot more going on.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:14.11,3:27:19.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I kind of miss how central the zombies were in the original game.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:19.21,3:27:24.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the idea of having a brand new type of infected introduce that we have to go up against
Dialogue: 2,3:27:24.22,3:27:27.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,was pretty interesting and I was damn ready for it.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:27.13,3:27:29.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so Nora leads Abby to the basement
Dialogue: 2,3:27:29.28,3:27:32.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,to let her collect everything that she's going to need for Yara's arm.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:32.18,3:27:34.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's at this point that she leaves Abby to it,
Dialogue: 2,3:27:34.84,3:27:39.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,and of course, as we know, she heads back upstairs to be confronted by Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:39.49,3:27:45.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it's at this point that Abby enters with Naughty Dog labeled this level as which is Ground Zero.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:45.28,3:27:47.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,She heads into the basement where all of these, in fact,
Dialogue: 2,3:27:47.71,3:27:50.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,that have just been sitting since the initial outbreak.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:50.23,3:27:54.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,And even Abby knows that there's probably going to be something pretty serious in here.
Dialogue: 2,3:27:54.22,3:27:56.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's only verified and reaffirmed
Dialogue: 2,3:27:56.72,3:28:00.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,by the fact that she starts seeing and hearing strange things almost immediately.
Dialogue: 2,3:28:00.70,3:28:04.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Abby pushes on and explores the area, trying to find the stuff that she needs,
Dialogue: 2,3:28:04.81,3:28:09.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and eventually she reconnects the power and pushes through some locked doors,
Dialogue: 2,3:28:09.10,3:28:10.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,only to find…
Dialogue: 2,3:28:17.59,3:28:20.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the door has been ripped open.
Dialogue: 2,3:28:20.26,3:28:22.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's something really big here, and Abby knows it.
Dialogue: 2,3:28:22.87,3:28:24.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, there is nowhere else to go.
Dialogue: 2,3:28:24.49,3:28:29.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Abby pushes through the tunnel and eventually finds the tools that she needs in an ambulance.
Dialogue: 2,3:28:29.68,3:28:34.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,But of course, because timing is perfect in every horror situation,
Dialogue: 2,3:28:34.51,3:28:35.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,this guy comes along.
Dialogue: 2,3:28:57.28,3:29:03.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this horrific monstrosity comes out and poses the next boss fight to the player.
Dialogue: 2,3:29:03.22,3:29:07.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a coagulation of multiple infected and Clickers,
Dialogue: 2,3:29:07.33,3:29:10.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's pretty disgusting looking,
Dialogue: 2,3:29:10.57,3:29:15.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I actually think that it's pretty impressive all things considered.
Dialogue: 2,3:29:15.04,3:29:17.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Something I did not see coming to be honest.
Dialogue: 2,3:29:17.53,3:29:21.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, I'm sorry to report that this disgusting creature
Dialogue: 2,3:29:21.08,3:29:24.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,is not actually that difficult all things considered.
Dialogue: 2,3:29:24.07,3:29:27.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,He moved so slowly that he can't be considered a major difficulty
Dialogue: 2,3:29:27.54,3:29:29.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,unless you're on, for instance, grounded.
Dialogue: 2,3:29:29.89,3:29:33.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,He moves so slowly that I wouldn't even really consider him much of a threat.
Dialogue: 2,3:29:33.82,3:29:36.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,He is a bullet sponge to be completely honest,
Dialogue: 2,3:29:36.67,3:29:39.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,but if you have enough ammo, you're just going to run around the building,
Dialogue: 2,3:29:39.79,3:29:41.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,eventually hurling things item,
Dialogue: 2,3:29:41.44,3:29:46.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially since they have dynamically generated crafting materials scattered throughout this floor.
Dialogue: 2,3:29:46.75,3:29:50.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means that you can always collect items, run to a corner, craft,
Dialogue: 2,3:29:50.26,3:29:52.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,run to another corner, equip it,
Dialogue: 2,3:29:52.12,3:29:55.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then throw pipe bombs and molotovs item if you need to.
Dialogue: 2,3:29:55.57,3:29:56.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think more broadly,
Dialogue: 2,3:29:56.68,3:30:01.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,difficulty in this game tends to come from the quantity of enemies.
Dialogue: 2,3:30:01.30,3:30:04.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,And ah…  Motherfu…
Dialogue: 2,3:30:10.00,3:30:12.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's real nasty.
Dialogue: 2,3:30:12.13,3:30:17.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you unload absolutely everything that you have into these two until they are eventually killed.
Dialogue: 2,3:30:17.77,3:30:22.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so Abby heads back up to the surface with all of the gear that she came for,
Dialogue: 2,3:30:22.33,3:30:25.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,she reconnects with Lev, and they head back to the aquarium.
Dialogue: 2,3:30:25.66,3:30:30.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's with these new-found tools that Mel is able to successfully amputate Yara's arm,
Dialogue: 2,3:30:30.73,3:30:32.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she does survive it.
Dialogue: 2,3:30:32.29,3:30:35.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems as though Abby's new family is going to be okay after all.
Dialogue: 2,3:30:35.77,3:30:39.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,Except totally not! That's not how anything in this game works.
Dialogue: 2,3:30:39.13,3:30:40.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,You should have known that by now.
Dialogue: 2,3:30:40.48,3:30:45.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,But of course, to finish out Seattle Day 2 there's another flashback slashed dream
Dialogue: 2,3:30:45.40,3:30:48.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,where Abby is in the hospital where her father died
Dialogue: 2,3:30:48.33,3:30:52.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,heads into the room where her father was found dead,
Dialogue: 2,3:30:52.15,3:30:57.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,except this time she sees him alive, and smiling,
Dialogue: 2,3:30:57.13,3:31:01.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,which to me actually represent something very significant.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:01.18,3:31:03.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Something that I do not think you can understate.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:03.60,3:31:10.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seriously I think this one little flashback slash, flash sideways, slashed dream.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:10.99,3:31:16.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think this is probably the most important moment of Abby's entire character.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:16.72,3:31:21.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you listen to anything in Abby sections, it's this, allow me to make my point.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:21.65,3:31:24.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,This moment to me seems to represent Abby,
Dialogue: 2,3:31:24.49,3:31:28.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,having finally made atonement for her sins and the death of Joel,
Dialogue: 2,3:31:28.87,3:31:33.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,while at the same time coming to complete peace with her father's death.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:33.13,3:31:37.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, at the very least, she doesn't seem to be struggling with sleep any more,
Dialogue: 2,3:31:37.09,3:31:39.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,because she's not having nightmares.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:39.16,3:31:43.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's actually having a good dream where she reconnects with her father.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:43.51,3:31:45.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's not a good dream, I don't know what is.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:45.49,3:31:50.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, the last time we saw Abby, rushing into the room, where her father was found dead,
Dialogue: 2,3:31:50.74,3:31:54.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,she witnessed Yara and Lev strung up and disemboweled.
Dialogue: 2,3:31:54.78,3:31:57.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,As we established back when that scene took place,
Dialogue: 2,3:31:57.58,3:31:59.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,it seemed as though that was implying that
Dialogue: 2,3:31:59.43,3:32:03.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yara and Lev were starting to have a significant impact on her psyche.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:03.52,3:32:05.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's the tone down version.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:05.14,3:32:10.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would argue that they seem to be starting to take a place in her mind and life
Dialogue: 2,3:32:10.53,3:32:13.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,that was previously occupied by her father.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:13.24,3:32:19.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a familial place that only is reserved for those that you truly care about.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:19.00,3:32:22.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,And whether it makes sense, whether it's justified or not,
Dialogue: 2,3:32:22.56,3:32:27.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby does feel that intense connection to Yara and Lev.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:27.10,3:32:31.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's just because they saved her life when they didn't need to.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:31.00,3:32:33.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or maybe it's because there is something more going on,
Dialogue: 2,3:32:33.25,3:32:36.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,an actual interest and appreciation of each other.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:36.94,3:32:39.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless it's there.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:39.20,3:32:45.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby, seeing her father in this setting, looking at her with a caring face,
Dialogue: 2,3:32:45.01,3:32:48.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,a face that says everything's going to be okay,
Dialogue: 2,3:32:48.52,3:32:51.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think is incredibly significant.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:51.79,3:32:53.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,She just saved Yara,
Dialogue: 2,3:32:53.88,3:32:57.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,and in turn, seems to have saved Lev at the same time,
Dialogue: 2,3:32:57.67,3:32:59.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,everything seems to have worked out.
Dialogue: 2,3:32:59.53,3:33:03.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,And as far as they know, the next day they're going to be able to load up in Owen's boat
Dialogue: 2,3:33:03.97,3:33:06.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and head off to Santa Barbara.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:06.10,3:33:09.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,It really does seem as though we're going to have a happy ending.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:09.04,3:33:12.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,And with that, Seattle Day 2, ends.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:12.25,3:33:16.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,Seattle Day 3, Abby wakes up to drama brewing.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:16.03,3:33:18.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,She slept well, but Mel is pissed.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:18.67,3:33:23.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,And basically she just wants Abby to leave her Owen and the new kids alone.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:23.29,3:33:27.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,She says that if Abby sticks along for any longer than she's going to screw everything up.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:27.66,3:33:33.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,So she might as well leave them to go to Santa Barbara by themselves and remain here with the WLF.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:33.37,3:33:38.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean the drama kind of makes sense, considering that Abby just slept with Mel's baby daddy.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:38.52,3:33:42.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I don't know if she knows this, or if she know and talked about it.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:42.22,3:33:47.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,But either way, it upsets Abby pretty significantly, and Abby actually starts to cry,
Dialogue: 2,3:33:47.38,3:33:51.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,one of the first times we see a crack in this facade that she puts forward,
Dialogue: 2,3:33:51.49,3:33:52.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think this hits hard for Abby,
Dialogue: 2,3:33:52.93,3:33:56.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,because she probably knows that it's true, at least to some extent.
Dialogue: 2,3:33:56.46,3:33:59.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean she is kind of toxic,
Dialogue: 2,3:33:59.04,3:34:03.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,she literally dragged a group of her closest friends halfway across the country,
Dialogue: 2,3:34:03.10,3:34:04.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,just to murder a dude.
Dialogue: 2,3:34:04.36,3:34:08.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Yara is dealing with Lev, who's come to the naive conclusion
Dialogue: 2,3:34:08.40,3:34:12.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,that he can convince their mother to join them in abandoning the cult.
Dialogue: 2,3:34:12.45,3:34:17.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yara, of course, realizes that this is a naive and stupid estimation
Dialogue: 2,3:34:17.30,3:34:18.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,of what they could do with their mother.
Dialogue: 2,3:34:18.70,3:34:22.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless Lev is convinced that there is a way.
Dialogue: 2,3:34:22.12,3:34:27.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Abby and Yara look for a gift that they can give to Lev, to make him feel better and stay.
Dialogue: 2,3:34:27.64,3:34:31.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it's during this chapter that the elephant in the room comes out,
Dialogue: 2,3:34:31.69,3:34:34.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's something that I'm sure many of us saw coming,
Dialogue: 2,3:34:34.12,3:34:38.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially if you've been listening to the passive dialogue for the last few hours of gameplay.
Dialogue: 2,3:34:38.86,3:34:41.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,You see, Lev is trans.
Dialogue: 2,3:34:41.16,3:34:44.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,In some of the previous combat sequences when you're moving with Lev through,
Dialogue: 2,3:34:44.38,3:34:48.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,for instance, the construction site in fighting a lot of Seraphites,
Dialogue: 2,3:34:48.10,3:34:53.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,there's times when the Seraphites will actually call out to Lev, referring to him as Lily.
Dialogue: 2,3:34:53.86,3:34:57.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now if you've been kind of mentally checked out for the majority of the game,
Dialogue: 2,3:34:57.04,3:35:00.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,this might come as a total shock, or it might just be confusing
Dialogue: 2,3:35:00.34,3:35:04.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,as to why they're referring to this character as Lily and not Lev.
Dialogue: 2,3:35:04.18,3:35:08.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's for that very reason that Yara and Lev left the group.
Dialogue: 2,3:35:08.74,3:35:11.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Lev was to be married off to one of the elders.
Dialogue: 2,3:35:11.17,3:35:15.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naturally, Lev did not agree with this or like the idea,
Dialogue: 2,3:35:15.16,3:35:18.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,and so started acting out eventually, cutting his hair,
Dialogue: 2,3:35:18.16,3:35:23.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,and fully transitioning, wanting to be referred to entreated as a male Seraphite,
Dialogue: 2,3:35:23.50,3:35:27.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,going out on patrols being trained and used as a soldier.
Dialogue: 2,3:35:27.49,3:35:30.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,And in what comes as absolutely no surprise to anybody,
Dialogue: 2,3:35:30.25,3:35:34.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,the Seraphites weren't exactly the most supportive of this transition.
Dialogue: 2,3:35:34.09,3:35:38.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,So they decided that they were going to severely punish Lev,
Dialogue: 2,3:35:38.32,3:35:43.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,or at the very least, we're not going to allow this alternative lifestyle, shall we say.
Dialogue: 2,3:35:43.93,3:35:50.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so Yara being a supportive and strong sister decided to come out with Lev and help them escape.
Dialogue: 2,3:35:50.95,3:35:55.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is, of course, why they're constantly referred to as apostate by the Seraphites,
Dialogue: 2,3:35:55.90,3:35:59.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,and why so many of the Seraphites in combat sequences
Dialogue: 2,3:35:59.11,3:36:03.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,will call out and ask Yara and Lev why they're doing what they're doing.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:03.37,3:36:07.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because as far as they knew up until very recently, they were just fine.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:07.51,3:36:10.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now there's been a lot of hubbub about this plot point.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:10.36,3:36:11.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,There has been a lot of debate,
Dialogue: 2,3:36:11.56,3:36:15.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,both left and right of center as to whether or not this was handled well.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:15.64,3:36:16.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,And to be honest,
Dialogue: 2,3:36:16.90,3:36:20.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm not really qualified to come to a determination on that point.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:20.47,3:36:23.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,But to me it seemed to be handled relatively well.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:23.65,3:36:26.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Though in this particular scene in the aquarium
Dialogue: 2,3:36:26.20,3:36:29.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Yara and Abby are talking about it,
Dialogue: 2,3:36:29.17,3:36:30.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,it does seem a little heavy handed.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:30.98,3:36:34.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,When I first figured it out for sure was a few hours before this,
Dialogue: 2,3:36:34.66,3:36:40.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Lev and Abby were exploring the tower together and Lev actually asks Abby,
Dialogue: 2,3:36:40.27,3:36:43.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,whether or not she heard what the other Seraphites were calling him.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:43.63,3:36:45.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,This, of course, was referencing the fact
Dialogue: 2,3:36:45.55,3:36:50.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,that the Seraphites constantly referred to Lev as Lily, or as the apostate.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:50.50,3:36:54.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby said she was aware of this, but that she didn't need to talk about it.
Dialogue: 2,3:36:54.22,3:36:57.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,That I thought was a pretty discreet way of handling something
Dialogue: 2,3:36:57.22,3:37:00.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Lev probably isn't too excited to talk about,
Dialogue: 2,3:37:00.22,3:37:04.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that frankly, isn't that important to what their end goal is.
Dialogue: 2,3:37:04.66,3:37:07.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this is one of the things that I've liked about Naughty Dog's work in the past
Dialogue: 2,3:37:07.95,3:37:12.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,when they have more diverse cast members or characters within their stories,
Dialogue: 2,3:37:12.91,3:37:16.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's usually not the defining point of that character.
Dialogue: 2,3:37:16.30,3:37:19.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,If there's a gay character in the original {\i1}TLOU{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,3:37:19.03,3:37:24.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's there for you to see and you can put it together if you're paying any attention whatsoever.
Dialogue: 2,3:37:24.01,3:37:27.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's not the defining point of that character.
Dialogue: 2,3:37:27.82,3:37:31.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,When somebody is purely defined by one trait of themselves,
Dialogue: 2,3:37:31.90,3:37:36.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,whether that something like sexual identity or their religion or their appearance,
Dialogue: 2,3:37:36.82,3:37:41.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's always a bad thing because people are far more complicated than that,
Dialogue: 2,3:37:41.77,3:37:45.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you shouldn't boil yourself down to just one trait.
Dialogue: 2,3:37:45.16,3:37:47.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,You're far more interesting than that.
Dialogue: 2,3:37:47.29,3:37:51.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is why generally, I feel that Naughty Dog's approach to these types of things is good
Dialogue: 2,3:37:51.49,3:37:54.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they don't make it the defining characteristic.
Dialogue: 2,3:37:54.40,3:38:01.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, in this most recent gained {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} and in their previous title, {\i1}Uncharted: The Lost Legacy{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,3:38:01.72,3:38:05.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,they fall prey much more to these heavy handed traits
Dialogue: 2,3:38:05.17,3:38:10.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they make a character define themselves purely by an external trait.
Dialogue: 2,3:38:10.63,3:38:15.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while I have no problem with whatever that trait may be by itself,
Dialogue: 2,3:38:15.70,3:38:18.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think that defining a character that you are crafting
Dialogue: 2,3:38:18.75,3:38:21.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,and putting it into a story by just that one trait
Dialogue: 2,3:38:21.40,3:38:23.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,is lazy writing.
Dialogue: 2,3:38:23.04,3:38:27.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think it does a disservice to the people who actually share that trait in reality.
Dialogue: 2,3:38:27.91,3:38:32.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, I think it's handled relatively well, if not a little heavy handed.
Dialogue: 2,3:38:32.29,3:38:35.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't seem to be that crucial of a reveal,
Dialogue: 2,3:38:35.95,3:38:39.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,and as far as I can tell, most people don't particularly care.
Dialogue: 2,3:38:39.70,3:38:41.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,I also can't help recognized
Dialogue: 2,3:38:41.48,3:38:46.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Naughty Dog saved this reveal quote-unquote for much later in the game.
Dialogue: 2,3:38:46.00,3:38:49.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Chances are, if you've made it this far, you're going to be much more understanding
Dialogue: 2,3:38:49.81,3:38:52.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,whereas if they put this reveal much earlier on in the game,
Dialogue: 2,3:38:52.87,3:38:55.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,it would be troll fodder without a doubt.
Dialogue: 2,3:38:55.68,3:38:57.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's smart, maybe it's cowardly,
Dialogue: 2,3:38:57.67,3:39:00.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,maybe it's just a coincidence that its revealed later in the game.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:00.79,3:39:04.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure, either way, I don't particularly care,
Dialogue: 2,3:39:04.45,3:39:05.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I don't think it matters.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:05.80,3:39:08.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, after they find a nice gift for Lev,
Dialogue: 2,3:39:08.83,3:39:14.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,they eventually push out to the edge of the aquarium and realized that Lev's taken a boat
Dialogue: 2,3:39:14.48,3:39:18.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,and is headed straight for the island that the Scars are based out of.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:18.00,3:39:20.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Lev's going to try to save his mom,
Dialogue: 2,3:39:20.02,3:39:23.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it really is…  it's just stupid to do this.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:23.77,3:39:26.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was one moment where I was a little confused,
Dialogue: 2,3:39:26.26,3:39:29.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,just because Lev doesn't seem like a naive or stupid person.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:29.89,3:39:34.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Lev's young, but that isn't necessarily directly correlative.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:34.44,3:39:37.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,You can be young and wise beyond your years.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:37.30,3:39:40.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Look at Ellie, for instance, in the first game she was young,
Dialogue: 2,3:39:40.60,3:39:42.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,but she was not naive whatsoever.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:42.70,3:39:46.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,I do not think that Ellie would have made this same rash decision.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:46.60,3:39:49.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the very least, you would have taken some time to plan out some way
Dialogue: 2,3:39:49.92,3:39:55.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,of dealing with this potential problem of leaving her mother forever potentially.
Dialogue: 2,3:39:55.84,3:40:00.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, because Naughty Dog needs a reason to show the player that Seraphites' island
Dialogue: 2,3:40:00.96,3:40:05.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this huge raid that the WLF are going to be carrying out on the island.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:05.05,3:40:09.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,They just put this together and say, "well, we'll have Lev race to the island".
Dialogue: 2,3:40:09.55,3:40:13.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then you follow Lev and you'll get to see all of this crazy stuff.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:13.45,3:40:17.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think that this one is again a little bit of a coincidence and
Dialogue: 2,3:40:17.68,3:40:23.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,seems to reek a little bit of the writer's trying to force characters into a situation
Dialogue: 2,3:40:23.21,3:40:28.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,that hasn't naturally percolated through the circumstances of what's going on.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:28.06,3:40:30.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's why this timing here is so important.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:30.46,3:40:34.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's because Abby's group is going to try to leave Seattle before the storm picks up.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:34.81,3:40:41.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,That storm is going to be used as cover for Isaac's final push on to the Seraphites' Island,
Dialogue: 2,3:40:41.02,3:40:45.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Isaac is not going to be delaying this push whatsoever at all.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:45.46,3:40:48.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's done with fighting as he told us earlier in the game.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:48.97,3:40:52.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's why all of this gear has been moved to the front base.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:52.09,3:40:55.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's because they're going to have one last, wipe-out fight
Dialogue: 2,3:40:55.09,3:40:58.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,to finish the Scars for good and be done with them.
Dialogue: 2,3:40:58.18,3:41:03.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,And at the same time, Abby can use this storm as cover to make her escape to Santa Barbara.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:03.97,3:41:06.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, this is much more of a lesser point.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:06.00,3:41:10.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because realistically, Abby and Owen, Mel, Yara and Lev
Dialogue: 2,3:41:10.53,3:41:13.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,don't really need that much cover to escape.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:13.21,3:41:15.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,If they have a boat, they can just leave.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:15.67,3:41:21.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,The WLF as far as I've seen in this game, don't actively patrolled the water.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:21.04,3:41:22.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,They do have boats that they use,
Dialogue: 2,3:41:22.57,3:41:27.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is after all, where Abby and Yara are going to grab a boat here in just a minute,
Dialogue: 2,3:41:27.85,3:41:30.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,but they don't seem to patrol it actively.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:30.31,3:41:32.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know, if they do patrol it actively,
Dialogue: 2,3:41:32.29,3:41:36.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that's why all of these people need the storm to cover their tracks.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:36.46,3:41:41.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,That would be interesting, but I'm not aware of any time when that's directly referenced.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:41.44,3:41:43.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you know, please let me know in the comments section below.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:43.84,3:41:48.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so Abby and Yara naturally decide that they need to go and get Lev,
Dialogue: 2,3:41:48.07,3:41:50.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,because if Lev steps foot on the island,
Dialogue: 2,3:41:50.53,3:41:54.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,chances are he will be killed within the first twenty seconds
Dialogue: 2,3:41:54.64,3:41:57.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,of being witnessed by any of the other Seraphites.
Dialogue: 2,3:41:57.40,3:42:00.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so Abby in Yara start to push for the marina.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:00.34,3:42:06.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,They eventually hear some sniper shots and Yara determines that she needs to stay behind.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:06.10,3:42:08.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,She, after all, only has one arm at this time,
Dialogue: 2,3:42:08.53,3:42:12.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,so it's a little harder for her to navigate these complex passageways
Dialogue: 2,3:42:12.80,3:42:16.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,of latter stairs and rafters that she has to jump across.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:16.03,3:42:19.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,You eventually cross into a wide open inner state
Dialogue: 2,3:42:19.37,3:42:24.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,and are instantly tackled right as you pop out by… who else but Manny.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:24.76,3:42:26.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is where the sniper is.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:26.26,3:42:30.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's got to pin down and has apparently killed all of Manny's guys.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:30.19,3:42:34.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so Abby and Manny worked together to push up and take out this sniper.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:34.39,3:42:37.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's actually pretty crazy sequence, it's very detailed too.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:37.45,3:42:42.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean just look at how the snipers shooting at Abby here as she advances through this ditch,
Dialogue: 2,3:42:42.10,3:42:46.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,even shoots the body that's laying right on it and part of the body's head blows off,
Dialogue: 2,3:42:46.81,3:42:49.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,which made all of this way more intense for me.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:49.72,3:42:52.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know if this happens every time for everybody,
Dialogue: 2,3:42:52.39,3:42:56.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,or if it was just a coincidental thing that the bullet happened to land right here.
Dialogue: 2,3:42:56.32,3:42:57.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,But either way,
Dialogue: 2,3:42:57.28,3:43:01.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,this spooked me and made me feel as though I was right in the thick of it.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:01.80,3:43:06.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now quick sidebar, remember why Jesse and Ellie separated just a few hours ago
Dialogue: 2,3:43:06.76,3:43:09.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,was because they heard that there was a sniper at the marina,
Dialogue: 2,3:43:09.37,3:43:11.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they assumed that this sniper had to be Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:11.65,3:43:14.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Jesse and Ellie separated.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:14.23,3:43:18.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Jesse could go and find Tommie and Ellie could leave and go to the aquarium.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:18.79,3:43:24.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Also remember the previous sniping section that we had with Ellie in the flashback.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:24.07,3:43:27.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Remember, I said that that wasn't just a one off sniping tutorial,
Dialogue: 2,3:43:27.49,3:43:31.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though it wasn't really going to be used at any other point in the game?
Dialogue: 2,3:43:31.03,3:43:33.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, it was for this very reason.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:33.20,3:43:37.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,They needed to establish that Tommy has sniping experience and is good at what he does.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:37.72,3:43:40.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,And sure enough, who do you think this sniper is?
Dialogue: 2,3:43:40.48,3:43:43.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,Whether or not the player realizes this in this particular moment,
Dialogue: 2,3:43:43.87,3:43:47.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think is too important because either way you the way you push up.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:47.05,3:43:49.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I think it's actually probably a cooler moment,
Dialogue: 2,3:43:49.33,3:43:52.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,if you don't realize it's Tommy handling the sniper rifle.
Dialogue: 2,3:43:52.93,3:43:56.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,When you're thinking of it purely as an NPC sniping at you,
Dialogue: 2,3:43:56.11,3:43:59.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,you have a much easier time just plowing through chasing him,
Dialogue: 2,3:43:59.38,3:44:01.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,shooting at him, trying to kill him.
Dialogue: 2,3:44:01.18,3:44:05.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,But once you realize it's a character that you also know and kind of love,
Dialogue: 2,3:44:05.08,3:44:10.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,but is actively threatening the life of another character that you're starting to enjoy and care about,
Dialogue: 2,3:44:10.72,3:44:17.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's that interesting conflict that makes {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} such a strange and bizarre story.
Dialogue: 2,3:44:17.29,3:44:20.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Manny push up and eventually get the sniper cornered.
Dialogue: 2,3:44:20.53,3:44:22.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, right as they reached the point,
Dialogue: 2,3:44:22.09,3:44:25.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,when they feel as though they've got him, this happens…
Dialogue: 2,3:44:55.96,3:44:58.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just like that, Manny is dead.
Dialogue: 2,3:44:58.36,3:45:00.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,And now Abby is mad.
Dialogue: 2,3:45:00.85,3:45:04.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is in my mind, just like the sudden death of Jesse.
Dialogue: 2,3:45:04.12,3:45:06.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,It comes out of nowhere and is a total shock.
Dialogue: 2,3:45:06.99,3:45:09.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, similes all over the place.
Dialogue: 2,3:45:09.46,3:45:13.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie lost a close friend out of nowhere very suddenly,
Dialogue: 2,3:45:13.78,3:45:17.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the player has to also deal with it suddenly and shockingly.
Dialogue: 2,3:45:17.98,3:45:23.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,And now Abby is losing a close friend of hers and is forced to deal with it in the same way.
Dialogue: 2,3:45:23.68,3:45:25.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you start around a little bit.
Dialogue: 2,3:45:25.27,3:45:26.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Abby pushes through the door.
Dialogue: 2,3:46:14.23,3:46:20.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you just look on her face, you know, Abby knows who this was.
Dialogue: 2,3:46:20.20,3:46:25.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,She knows that Tommy is here and that that is very bad.
Dialogue: 2,3:46:25.93,3:46:31.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is especially bad because Manny just said a few moments ago
Dialogue: 2,3:46:31.00,3:46:32.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,when you were in the interstate,
Dialogue: 2,3:46:32.68,3:46:38.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,that there's more than one trespassers in town, killing WLF members.
Dialogue: 2,3:46:47.41,3:46:52.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means that even if she killed Tommy just now, which is a stretch,
Dialogue: 2,3:46:52.96,3:46:58.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,there's a lot more people that are in town, killing WLF members.
Dialogue: 2,3:46:58.03,3:47:02.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if Tommy's here, chances are it's other people from Jackson
Dialogue: 2,3:47:02.64,3:47:06.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,coming to get revenge for what she did to Joel.
Dialogue: 2,3:47:06.27,3:47:09.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, Abby doesn't really have the time to freak out about this.
Dialogue: 2,3:47:09.58,3:47:14.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,She puts it out of her mind and heads to the island in a boat which they take from the pier,
Dialogue: 2,3:47:14.08,3:47:19.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,the same boat and peer that the WLF members use, apparently, occasionally.
Dialogue: 2,3:47:19.18,3:47:23.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,Her goal is simple, she needs to find Lev and get out.
Dialogue: 2,3:47:23.40,3:47:29.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,If she can do that quickly, shall avoid Ellie and her entire revenge crew completely.
Dialogue: 2,3:47:29.26,3:47:32.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Yara reach the Scars' island.
Dialogue: 2,3:47:32.20,3:47:36.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yara takes the lead, and brings Abby into the heart of one of their major camps.
Dialogue: 2,3:47:36.76,3:47:41.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the most interesting thing about this actually is that Yara and Lev still buy into the cult,
Dialogue: 2,3:47:41.80,3:47:43.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though they've rejected the leadership.
Dialogue: 2,3:47:58.84,3:48:00.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,And to be honest, I don't really know what to make of this.
Dialogue: 2,3:48:00.97,3:48:06.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've heard stories of people that were involved in cults that get out and still partially believe it,
Dialogue: 2,3:48:06.07,3:48:09.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though they feel as though it was corrupted somewhat.
Dialogue: 2,3:48:09.07,3:48:11.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,They feel as though they're still truth to it.
Dialogue: 2,3:48:11.77,3:48:14.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,I am not totally sure, but I thought it was interesting
Dialogue: 2,3:48:14.16,3:48:18.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,because after all, these kids were raised in this cult from the time that they were born.
Dialogue: 2,3:48:18.85,3:48:24.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it makes sense that just because they decided to leave under threat of death,
Dialogue: 2,3:48:24.22,3:48:30.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,they still have some adoration, or at least respect for the cult leaders.
Dialogue: 2,3:48:30.31,3:48:32.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, once in the belly of the island
Dialogue: 2,3:48:32.60,3:48:36.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Yara witnessed the Seraphites heading into their armories
Dialogue: 2,3:48:36.04,3:48:39.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,to prepare for the incoming WLF attack, which is beginning.
Dialogue: 2,3:48:39.34,3:48:45.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,They see WLF members heading into the island and are taken by complete surprise by this.
Dialogue: 2,3:48:45.00,3:48:50.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Honestly it's little surprising to me that the Seraphites didn't see this coming in at least a little bit.
Dialogue: 2,3:48:50.26,3:48:52.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,They have a huge infrastructure throughout the city,
Dialogue: 2,3:48:52.81,3:48:57.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,as we've seen with bridges that co from rooftop to rooftop and they're very sneaky,
Dialogue: 2,3:48:57.55,3:48:59.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it seems as though they should have been able to realize
Dialogue: 2,3:48:59.99,3:49:03.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,that the WLF was mobilizing for some sort of offensive.
Dialogue: 2,3:49:03.55,3:49:09.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, they were bringing all of their supplies in all of their soldiers into one central area.
Dialogue: 2,3:49:09.76,3:49:14.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,If that doesn't spook you as the leader of the Seraphites, I don't know what will.
Dialogue: 2,3:49:14.13,3:49:16.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless, they're preparing for the offensive.
Dialogue: 2,3:49:16.48,3:49:22.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,This gives you a little bit of space to explore the island and push through to Abby and Yara's house.
Dialogue: 2,3:49:22.18,3:49:27.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,While you're doing this, you find through multiple arenas of Seraphites, all fairly stealth oriented.
Dialogue: 2,3:49:27.58,3:49:29.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless it gives you something to do
Dialogue: 2,3:49:29.86,3:49:34.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,to shake up the monotony of just walking through sequences in watching small cut scenes.
Dialogue: 2,3:49:34.15,3:49:37.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,Eventually you come upon the house, and the following scene plays out.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:01.03,3:51:05.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this doesn't really surprise anyone, she was never going to understand.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:05.47,3:51:09.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's also important to note that this severs all ties for Lev,
Dialogue: 2,3:51:09.94,3:51:13.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,which signal to me that they were actually being set up to leave Seattle completely
Dialogue: 2,3:51:13.68,3:51:15.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,without leaving any baggage behind.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:15.93,3:51:22.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Whenever a game or a story starts to sever familial and friendly ties to a character
Dialogue: 2,3:51:22.76,3:51:26.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,usually it means that they are preparing to make some sort of big transition
Dialogue: 2,3:51:26.39,3:51:30.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that they aren't left with the baggage or having to explain that baggage way.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:30.10,3:51:33.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,I, however, don't think that this was particularly necessary.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:33.40,3:51:37.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think leaving Lev and Yara's mom behind really wouldn't have been that big of deal.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:37.93,3:51:41.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,After all, she's a member of a cult, a cult that wants to kill them.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:41.88,3:51:44.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, Abby, Yara and Lev pushed together to the docks
Dialogue: 2,3:51:44.86,3:51:48.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they want to find a boat and take that boat back to the aquarium.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:48.28,3:51:50.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,I was never super clear on why
Dialogue: 2,3:51:50.16,3:51:54.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,these characters couldn't just return to the boat that they had just taken to shore.
Dialogue: 2,3:51:54.55,3:51:57.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, they want you to push to the docks,
Dialogue: 2,3:51:57.31,3:52:01.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,grab a separate different boat and escape using that one.
Dialogue: 2,3:52:01.03,3:52:04.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if there was damage to the boat when you reached the island
Dialogue: 2,3:52:04.18,3:52:08.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,or why they can't use the boat they just took from the peer from the WLF.
Dialogue: 2,3:52:08.47,3:52:12.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless they can't for some reason.
Dialogue: 2,3:52:12.01,3:52:13.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,To me, it seems like more of an excuse
Dialogue: 2,3:52:13.61,3:52:17.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,just to get these characters to push into the main center of town
Dialogue: 2,3:52:17.28,3:52:22.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that they can see a new set piece as the WLF and Seraphites' clash.
Dialogue: 2,3:52:22.42,3:52:27.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,I get it, it makes sense, but it just doesn't seem to logically follow
Dialogue: 2,3:52:27.10,3:52:29.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,considering that they just took a boat to the island
Dialogue: 2,3:52:29.80,3:52:32.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's much closer than the boat they are trying to push to.
Dialogue: 2,3:52:32.56,3:52:33.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 2,3:52:33.05,3:52:36.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,If there's some really good excuse as to why they can't go back to that original boat,
Dialogue: 2,3:52:36.79,3:52:37.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,just let me know.
Dialogue: 2,3:52:37.50,3:52:41.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the three star pushing through an old town that's been completely abandoned,
Dialogue: 2,3:52:41.74,3:52:44.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it looks as though the Seraphites don't even actively patrol it
Dialogue: 2,3:52:44.92,3:52:47.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,since it's from the old world.
Dialogue: 2,3:52:47.08,3:52:49.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everything's quiet, until…
Dialogue: 2,3:55:04.09,3:55:07.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,So now we're paired with Lev against the WLF members
Dialogue: 2,3:55:07.03,3:55:09.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,we previously considered our friends.
Dialogue: 2,3:55:09.24,3:55:12.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,Be honest, it's a really emotionally confusing chunk of the game,
Dialogue: 2,3:55:12.37,3:55:17.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,since there are so many people constantly yelling at Abby asking why she is doing this.
Dialogue: 2,3:55:17.96,3:55:22.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now we may not know these characters, but Abby does.
Dialogue: 2,3:55:22.09,3:55:25.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's killing people that she worked with, that she knows,
Dialogue: 2,3:55:25.67,3:55:29.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,who haven't really done anything wrong themselves,
Dialogue: 2,3:55:29.47,3:55:33.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,all for the sake of Lev, somebody that she's not even related to,
Dialogue: 2,3:55:33.96,3:55:37.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and for whom she has really no reason to care.
Dialogue: 2,3:55:37.63,3:55:41.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's pretty crazy, I mean, who would do that?
Dialogue: 2,3:55:41.65,3:55:44.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Who would kill people that they've previously worked with
Dialogue: 2,3:55:44.24,3:55:45.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,for somebody that are not related to
Dialogue: 2,3:55:45.92,3:55:49.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,and just care because they've built a connection to them?
Dialogue: 2,3:55:49.06,3:55:49.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 2,3:55:57.07,3:56:00.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Abby and Lev come upon a view of what Isaac's group has done.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:00.28,3:56:04.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're torturing the whole place, they're literally going scorched earth.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:04.24,3:56:08.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so as we push to the marina to get the boat that we need to escape,
Dialogue: 2,3:56:08.17,3:56:13.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,we fight multiple waves of Scars and WLF members at the same time,
Dialogue: 2,3:56:13.69,3:56:18.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,sometimes coming across them, fighting each other when we interrupt just trying to pass through.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:18.64,3:56:20.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,Really, it's kind of cool,
Dialogue: 2,3:56:20.42,3:56:25.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,to see all of these enemies interacting with each other and just wiping each other out.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:25.54,3:56:27.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's kind of crazy.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:27.13,3:56:31.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now the sequence has actually got a fair amount of crap because there's no infected here,
Dialogue: 2,3:56:31.06,3:56:35.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,but that to me doesn't make any sense as an accusation or criticism.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:35.77,3:56:41.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is an island, and it's an island that the Seraphites have lived on for a long time.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:41.29,3:56:47.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,They likely cleared out the infected on the island very early on and have kept it contained.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:47.15,3:56:51.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Sure, it's a little weird to play what many people thought was just going to be a zombie game
Dialogue: 2,3:56:51.48,3:56:55.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,and to not see zombies for hours and hours on end.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:55.12,3:56:58.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I think it makes sense, at least in the world that they've built.
Dialogue: 2,3:56:58.63,3:57:03.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,{\i1}TLOU{\i0} is far more complicated than just a story about zombies.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:03.04,3:57:08.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's really upsetting to hear boiled down to that basic and estimation.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:08.92,3:57:11.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, eventually, Abby and Lev find a horse,
Dialogue: 2,3:57:11.71,3:57:15.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,hop on it and ride into the heart of the Seraphites' capital.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:15.82,3:57:20.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,This really is a visually stunning sequence and I really can't complemented enough.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:20.59,3:57:23.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,The lighting is ridiculously good.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:23.08,3:57:29.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's probably the most impressed I was visually across the entire game, just this one sequence.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:29.29,3:57:32.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Abby rides the horse all the way through to the edge of the docks.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:32.95,3:57:36.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,After killing more and more WLF members, more Seraphites,
Dialogue: 2,3:57:36.43,3:57:37.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,climbing through a burning house.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:37.66,3:57:42.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,You eventually find one last many boss in this chapter.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:42.04,3:57:44.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's a Brute in the same style as Helga.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:44.35,3:57:48.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,And there's actually some pretty impressive mesh deformation systems at play here.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:48.49,3:57:52.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,As he gets cut on his body, it actually becomes more and more mutilated.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:52.21,3:57:53.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,The skin flays open.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:53.71,3:57:55.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's pretty impressive.
Dialogue: 2,3:57:55.15,3:57:59.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's unfortunate that this type of feature couldn't be applied to absolutely every character
Dialogue: 2,3:57:59.29,3:58:03.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,at this fidelity level as you attack them throughout the course of the game.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:03.19,3:58:08.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,I will grant you the mesh deformation system and the gore system in {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} was pretty incredible.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:08.65,3:58:12.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if it was on this level it would be another world.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:12.28,3:58:16.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Hopefully we get to see this level of quality in the next generation of consoles.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:16.78,3:58:20.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,I have a feeling as though we're going to get it, and it's going to be pretty bad ass.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:20.59,3:58:26.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Probably the best example of this system working is when you use a scythe to gash his mouth open.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:26.64,3:58:31.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it seems to me that this can't be just a coincidence that the gash occurs at this place,
Dialogue: 2,3:58:31.69,3:58:35.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,considering that the Scars got their name "the Scars"
Dialogue: 2,3:58:35.30,3:58:41.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they actively and willingly mutilate their mouths with this type of scar intentionally.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:41.08,3:58:45.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I took this as a way for Abby and Lev to in essence repay the Seraphites
Dialogue: 2,3:58:45.56,3:58:49.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,for all of the physical and mental damage that they've applied upon Lev and Yara.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:49.66,3:58:53.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,In other words, taking what the Scars, considered a sacred right,
Dialogue: 2,3:58:53.65,3:58:56.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,and turning it into a way to strike back.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:56.14,3:58:59.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or maybe I'm just reading way too much into this.
Dialogue: 2,3:58:59.44,3:59:02.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, after defeating this Brute, Abby and Lev grab a rowboat
Dialogue: 2,3:59:02.92,3:59:06.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they head back to the aquarium with the island burning in the background.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:06.52,3:59:11.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,We don't really find out what happened after this or how this battle resolved itself,
Dialogue: 2,3:59:11.44,3:59:14.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I don't really think it's important.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:14.23,3:59:16.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,But we do know is that Isaac is dead.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:16.30,3:59:20.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so the WLF began crumbling upon realizing that their leader was gone.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:20.98,3:59:25.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would therefore assume that they lost the fight and the Seraphites held their ground.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:25.00,3:59:26.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I don't think it matters.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:26.95,3:59:32.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Back at the aquarium, Abby comes across the bodies of Owen, Mel and Alice, the dog.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:32.98,3:59:39.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's absolutely devastated, and it seems as though the writer's job has worked.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:39.03,3:59:43.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,These characters that we didn't really care about just a few hours of gameplay ago,
Dialogue: 2,3:59:43.72,3:59:46.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Ellie came in and killed them,
Dialogue: 2,3:59:46.12,3:59:49.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,now actually have a place in our hearts.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:49.63,3:59:51.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,We know these characters.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:51.28,3:59:55.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,You don't care that much about Mel, you don't really care that much about Owen,
Dialogue: 2,3:59:55.45,3:59:59.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,but you have started to care about Abby and Lev.
Dialogue: 2,3:59:59.50,4:00:04.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby is devastated by this, and I couldn't help but feel bad.
Dialogue: 2,4:00:04.12,4:00:06.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the crazy thing is that at this point,
Dialogue: 2,4:00:06.16,4:00:11.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,She doesn't even really know that a lot of the other crew members are also dead.
Dialogue: 2,4:00:11.56,4:00:17.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know, as far as I am aware, that Nora was brutally bashed by Ellie;
Dialogue: 2,4:00:17.20,4:00:22.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know about all of the others that Ellie came across and killed on her way to find Abby.
Dialogue: 2,4:00:22.72,4:00:23.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,And to be honest,
Dialogue: 2,4:00:23.44,4:00:27.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if Abby ever found out about those characters deaths
Dialogue: 2,4:00:27.81,4:00:31.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,because as far as I can tell, after the following sequence, she left.
Dialogue: 2,4:00:31.90,4:00:35.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,They went to Santa Barbara and started a new life.
Dialogue: 2,4:00:35.44,4:00:40.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,The point is, Abby is devastated, and she starts to go into a rage driven mode.
Dialogue: 2,4:00:40.87,4:00:43.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Remember that map that Ellie dropped and left behind
Dialogue: 2,4:00:43.72,4:00:46.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Tommy and Jesse took her out of the aquarium?
Dialogue: 2,4:00:46.51,4:00:48.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, Abby finds it.
Dialogue: 2,4:00:48.28,4:00:54.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,She picks it up and conveniently Ellie has marked in a huge circle exactly where they're staying.
Dialogue: 2,4:00:54.94,4:01:00.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so, Abby and Lev go to the Jackson-Knights' hideout, expecting to find Tommy alone.
Dialogue: 2,4:01:00.44,4:01:05.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, as far as they know, it's just Tommy here and some other helpers he has.
Dialogue: 2,4:01:05.53,4:01:08.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,They do know for a fact, though, that Tommy's here.
Dialogue: 2,4:01:08.05,4:01:12.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,So my assumption would be that Abby really only expects to find Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,4:01:12.35,4:01:14.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,After breaking in, they find everyone.
Dialogue: 2,4:01:14.76,4:01:20.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,First Tommy at the counter in the lobby, then Jesse, and Ellie as they come through the door.
Dialogue: 2,4:03:12.01,4:03:14.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is when the game reaches its climax.
Dialogue: 2,4:03:14.17,4:03:20.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,You play as Abby as you chase Ellie deep into the depths of the theaters, props and storage room.
Dialogue: 2,4:03:20.14,4:03:26.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's here that we have to play as the character we initially hated and tried to defeat,
Dialogue: 2,4:03:26.56,4:03:28.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then flip that on its head,
Dialogue: 2,4:03:28.84,4:03:35.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,trying to hunt down and kill someone that we fell in love with almost a decade ago,
Dialogue: 2,4:03:35.02,4:03:37.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,that character being Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,4:03:37.18,4:03:42.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Though based on the pole and the responses that you guys wrote to that survey,
Dialogue: 2,4:03:42.04,4:03:47.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,there is actually a fair number of people that reached this point in the game and refused to continue.
Dialogue: 2,4:03:47.59,4:03:51.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,They'd played 20, 25, 30 hours of this game,
Dialogue: 2,4:03:51.73,4:03:57.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,got to this point and realized that they were being asked to kill Ellie, and they refused to do it.
Dialogue: 2,4:03:57.16,4:03:59.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now at one point, I think that that's a testament
Dialogue: 2,4:03:59.49,4:04:04.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,to just how phenomenally well connected these characters are, to us, the players.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:04.13,4:04:07.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,We care about them, and we don't want to see them mistreated.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:07.24,4:04:10.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it's really too bad that there wasn't some alternative state
Dialogue: 2,4:04:10.15,4:04:16.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,where you could actually choose not to continue this fight, forgive Ellie, and move on.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:16.14,4:04:19.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thing that could have been a cool moment in terms of player agency
Dialogue: 2,4:04:19.17,4:04:21.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,to resolve this dispute peacefully.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:21.76,4:04:25.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,But with a linear narrative game such as this, that doesn't really work too well.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:25.90,4:04:29.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so, you're forced to engage in this boss fight,
Dialogue: 2,4:04:29.30,4:04:32.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,where Abby, the protagonist in this instance,
Dialogue: 2,4:04:32.02,4:04:34.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,is chasing after the antagonist, which is Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:34.74,4:04:36.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not to say one is right or wrong,
Dialogue: 2,4:04:36.91,4:04:42.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,because protagonist and antagonist are purely based on the perspective of the author.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:42.22,4:04:47.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now as to whether or not this point in the game works, I think there's an active question here.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:47.35,4:04:49.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's probably going to be a little different for everybody.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:49.45,4:04:52.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Some people probably are going to connect to Abby and Lev
Dialogue: 2,4:04:52.15,4:04:56.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,far more than they connected to Ellie over the course of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}.
Dialogue: 2,4:04:56.17,4:04:57.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now of course, if you played the original game,
Dialogue: 2,4:04:57.91,4:05:01.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're probably still going to have a lot of that baggage built up from the original game,
Dialogue: 2,4:05:01.79,4:05:03.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,when Ellie was far more likable.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:03.73,4:05:08.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,The sad truth is that Ellie isn't very likable in this game
Dialogue: 2,4:05:08.02,4:05:10.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,as I've said multiple times throughout this critique.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:10.75,4:05:14.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,But for me I found myself just sitting and staring at my screen for a moment
Dialogue: 2,4:05:14.70,4:05:17.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,when I realized what I was being asked to do here.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:17.65,4:05:21.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think it was because the game didn't completely succeed in what it was trying to do
Dialogue: 2,4:05:21.79,4:05:23.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,the first time I played the game.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:23.29,4:05:27.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Namely, Naughty Dog, wanted to make the player feel as though killing Ellie was justified
Dialogue: 2,4:05:27.81,4:05:32.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,at the very least, just as justifiable as Ellie killing Abby.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:32.50,4:05:35.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the reason I don't think this has worked too well
Dialogue: 2,4:05:35.44,4:05:38.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,is because the people that Ellie has taken from Abby
Dialogue: 2,4:05:38.71,4:05:41.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,were all effectively B-Class characters.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:41.35,4:05:47.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,Owen? Yeah, he's great, but he's supporting and he's not particularly charismatic.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:47.05,4:05:49.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Definitely not a leading character.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:49.36,4:05:55.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, on the other hand, if Ellie shot and killed Lev right as they enter the theater,
Dialogue: 2,4:05:55.06,4:05:57.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,I can't help but feel as though this would have worked much better.
Dialogue: 2,4:05:57.85,4:06:00.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Likely the player playing as Abby in this case
Dialogue: 2,4:06:00.44,4:06:05.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,would feel much more justified in chasing down Ellie if this had happened.
Dialogue: 2,4:06:05.68,4:06:08.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, Abby hunts Ellie down in a boss fight
Dialogue: 2,4:06:08.94,4:06:13.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's basically identical to the one that ended the winter chapter in the first game
Dialogue: 2,4:06:13.43,4:06:16.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,against everybody's favorite cannibal king.
Dialogue: 2,4:06:16.39,4:06:19.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it's just lazy, repetitive game design,
Dialogue: 2,4:06:19.03,4:06:24.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,or if this is meant to be an actual reversal and similarly in and of itself.
Dialogue: 2,4:06:24.13,4:06:25.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 2,4:06:25.12,4:06:28.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it does seem shockingly similar in terms of how it's laid out
Dialogue: 2,4:06:28.97,4:06:31.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the structure of this boss fight.
Dialogue: 2,4:06:31.27,4:06:35.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a coincidence, maybe it's something very intentional, I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 2,4:06:35.68,4:06:39.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,But at the very least, I thought that it was a direct parallel.
Dialogue: 2,4:06:39.31,4:06:43.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,The whole thing wraps up with one of the hardest to watch cut scenes
Dialogue: 2,4:06:43.21,4:06:45.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,in all of gaming as far as I'm concerned.
Dialogue: 2,4:07:54.67,4:07:58.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,She stopped short… after Lev calls out to her,
Dialogue: 2,4:07:58.12,4:08:01.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,She realizes that this isn't going to help anything.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:01.53,4:08:05.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just like killing Joel didn't help her get over her father's death,
Dialogue: 2,4:08:05.77,4:08:09.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,the moment she moved on from her father's death, or at the very least accepted,
Dialogue: 2,4:08:09.70,4:08:13.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,was that first night after she met Lev and Yara
Dialogue: 2,4:08:13.08,4:08:16.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,when she realized that she could have a family again.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:16.36,4:08:21.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,United not in hate and vengeance, but in love and unity.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:21.49,4:08:22.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,So she lets them go.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:22.90,4:08:28.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby and Lev leave, and Ellie and Dina are left, bleeding out on the floor.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:28.33,4:08:32.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,We cut to black and the game moves into the final chapter.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:32.59,4:08:37.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now I don't think I can stress enough just how weird the player likely feels at this point.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:37.99,4:08:43.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a mixture of a let-down with being blue balled all at the same time,
Dialogue: 2,4:08:43.72,4:08:46.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and if I'm being honest, I really didn't know what to make of it.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:46.63,4:08:48.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of other people also pointed out
Dialogue: 2,4:08:48.52,4:08:52.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,that this was somewhat similar to how {\i1}Red Dead Redemption 2{\i0} started to wrap up its story,
Dialogue: 2,4:08:52.57,4:08:56.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,with Arthur's death coming seemingly wrapping up the main story.
Dialogue: 2,4:08:56.65,4:09:02.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then the player entering into an epilogue that seemed important, but not crucial.
Dialogue: 2,4:09:02.32,4:09:04.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, I asked several friends of mine,
Dialogue: 2,4:09:04.63,4:09:07.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,whether or not they actually played the epilogue or not,
Dialogue: 2,4:09:07.24,4:09:09.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,after they got through the main story of {\i1}Red Dead redemption 2{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,4:09:09.85,4:09:14.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you'd be surprised how many of them said that they stopped playing after Arthur died.
Dialogue: 2,4:09:14.83,4:09:15.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,On the one hand, I get it.
Dialogue: 2,4:09:15.94,4:09:18.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,You've been following one character for the entire length of the game,
Dialogue: 2,4:09:18.82,4:09:22.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that character's story has seemingly come to an end.
Dialogue: 2,4:09:22.12,4:09:24.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,So why do you need to continue playing through
Dialogue: 2,4:09:24.41,4:09:30.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,what is objectively a much more boring sequence for multiple hours at a time
Dialogue: 2,4:09:30.28,4:09:32.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,if you don't feel as though it's necessary?
Dialogue: 2,4:09:32.35,4:09:33.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,And when that game came out,
Dialogue: 2,4:09:33.52,4:09:38.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,I couldn't help but feel as though it was either a very conscious decision on the part of Rockstar
Dialogue: 2,4:09:38.77,4:09:42.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,to have this epilogue so clearly separate from the main story,
Dialogue: 2,4:09:42.70,4:09:45.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,or it was a complete and total oversight.
Dialogue: 2,4:09:45.76,4:09:47.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the case of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,4:09:47.35,4:09:50.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's direct comparison, but I do think there are similarities.
Dialogue: 2,4:09:50.92,4:09:51.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,In my estimation,
Dialogue: 2,4:09:51.79,4:09:54.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,most players have been going through {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}
Dialogue: 2,4:09:54.16,4:09:59.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,with the hope that it will end in a climactic scene between Ellie and Abby,
Dialogue: 2,4:09:59.32,4:10:03.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,where everything gets resolved, preferably where one kills the other,
Dialogue: 2,4:10:03.28,4:10:05.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,or at the very least, there are some sort of reckoning.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:05.56,4:10:10.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I wouldn't say that this scratches that itch or satisfies that demand.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:10.51,4:10:15.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's controversial to say that Abby, pretty clearly won this exchange.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:15.61,4:10:20.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if she wanted to, could have killed Ellie and Dina easily.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:20.50,4:10:26.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,But out of some sense of dignity or grace and forgiveness, pride,
Dialogue: 2,4:10:26.86,4:10:29.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,whatever it may be, she decided to spare them.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:29.95,4:10:33.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,So while this may be a resolution of the conflict from Abby's perspective,
Dialogue: 2,4:10:33.97,4:10:36.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's moving on and wants to forget about all of this.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:36.85,4:10:41.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not a resolution for Ellie, for Tommy, or for Dina,
Dialogue: 2,4:10:41.02,4:10:42.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,as we'll see in the following scenes.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:42.97,4:10:45.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think the really frustrating thing for the player
Dialogue: 2,4:10:45.24,4:10:50.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,is that the entire story has been building to this moment, this exchange, this fight,
Dialogue: 2,4:10:50.43,4:10:53.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,throughout the entirety of the game play time.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:53.50,4:10:57.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,And now that we've reached it, it doesn't resolve itself at all.
Dialogue: 2,4:10:57.04,4:11:01.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,And instead, Ellie, Dina and Tommy are left bleeding out on the floor,
Dialogue: 2,4:11:01.51,4:11:04.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,and in the case of Jesse, he's dead.
Dialogue: 2,4:11:04.18,4:11:08.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,And especially considering how emotionally exhausting the scheme is to play,
Dialogue: 2,4:11:08.62,4:11:12.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's really difficult to ask the player to buckle down for another
Dialogue: 2,4:11:12.73,4:11:17.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,however many hours it's going to take to get through what is effectively the epilogue.
Dialogue: 2,4:11:17.32,4:11:22.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I know it's not technically an epilogue because the story hasn't resolved itself.
Dialogue: 2,4:11:22.09,4:11:26.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's still part of the main story as we move into this next chapter.
Dialogue: 2,4:11:26.11,4:11:29.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,But still it feels as though it separate from the main game.
Dialogue: 2,4:11:29.80,4:11:34.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,And after a lot of contemplation, I am not sure if Naughty Dog wanted this to be the case,
Dialogue: 2,4:11:34.63,4:11:40.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,or if they even meant for this to feel so different from the core body of the game in Seattle.
Dialogue: 2,4:11:40.57,4:11:46.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems to be pretty clear that shifting pace very sharply after all of the events of the core game,
Dialogue: 2,4:11:46.09,4:11:51.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,is going to hit the player in a fairly significant way such that they're going to feel very differently.
Dialogue: 2,4:11:51.52,4:11:53.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's something a good number of developers have spoken of
Dialogue: 2,4:11:53.89,4:11:57.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,in GDC conference, speeches, and things like that,
Dialogue: 2,4:11:57.76,4:12:02.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they express this frustration with working on a project for years and years and years
Dialogue: 2,4:12:02.66,4:12:04.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,and losing perspective on it,
Dialogue: 2,4:12:04.36,4:12:08.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,such that they forget how it would actually feel to play it for the first time.
Dialogue: 2,4:12:08.74,4:12:11.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,In other words, when you're working really hard on something,
Dialogue: 2,4:12:11.32,4:12:16.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,you develop a sort of tunnel vision and you lose perspective on what it looks like from the outside.
Dialogue: 2,4:12:16.96,4:12:18.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,It may seem great to you,
Dialogue: 2,4:12:18.61,4:12:21.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,but just because you're so focused on the little details,
Dialogue: 2,4:12:21.55,4:12:23.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,you might have lost sight of the overall picture.
Dialogue: 2,4:12:23.92,4:12:29.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or vice versa, you are focused on the broader picture, so you lose sight of the minutiae.
Dialogue: 2,4:12:29.09,4:12:33.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Regardless, this final fight leaves the player feeling kind of strange,
Dialogue: 2,4:12:33.09,4:12:34.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least it did for me;
Dialogue: 2,4:12:34.48,4:12:37.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,and based on a lot of your responses to the survey,
Dialogue: 2,4:12:37.12,4:12:40.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,it left a lot of you feeling very strange as well.
Dialogue: 2,4:12:40.15,4:12:41.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I don't know about you,
Dialogue: 2,4:12:41.41,4:12:45.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,but often strangers into feeling I would associate with quality.
Dialogue: 2,4:12:45.97,4:12:50.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,But with all that said after this initial chunk of the game is over,
Dialogue: 2,4:12:50.21,4:12:53.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,the player's left with a lot of questions unresolved.
Dialogue: 2,4:12:53.02,4:12:55.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,For instance, is Dina okay?
Dialogue: 2,4:12:55.45,4:13:00.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is she going to survive having her face bashed into cement multiple times?
Dialogue: 2,4:13:00.32,4:13:03.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,While it's technically it wasn't cement, they put down a particle board
Dialogue: 2,4:13:03.99,4:13:07.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that they could have an excuse as to why she survived, its good detail.
Dialogue: 2,4:13:07.54,4:13:08.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that they put this in there
Dialogue: 2,4:13:08.87,4:13:12.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that it's not totally unbelievable that she survived a cracked skull.
Dialogue: 2,4:13:12.91,4:13:18.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,But still this is a pretty rough thing to go through, especially when you're pregnant.
Dialogue: 2,4:13:18.49,4:13:21.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the player's left wondering whether or not she's going to be okay.
Dialogue: 2,4:13:21.52,4:13:24.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,You also have to ask yourself what's going to happen to this couple
Dialogue: 2,4:13:24.64,4:13:27.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,when the incoming baby comes along now that Jesse's gone.
Dialogue: 2,4:13:27.79,4:13:29.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,How is Jackson going to handle
Dialogue: 2,4:13:29.80,4:13:34.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,having so many of their best and brightest, decimated by an out of state group?
Dialogue: 2,4:13:34.69,4:13:38.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Can, or will they ever be able to adjust?
Dialogue: 2,4:13:38.35,4:13:40.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, we don't ever really get to know.
Dialogue: 2,4:13:40.28,4:13:43.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because in the following sequences, we never return back to Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,4:13:43.72,4:13:47.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,And perhaps the most important question is what does Ellie do now?
Dialogue: 2,4:13:47.68,4:13:49.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is she capable of moving on?
Dialogue: 2,4:13:49.54,4:13:51.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is that something that Ellie would even want?
Dialogue: 2,4:13:51.58,4:13:54.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is that something that would even satisfy the player?
Dialogue: 2,4:13:54.46,4:13:59.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or are we setting ourselves up for one last hurrah to try and resolve everything
Dialogue: 2,4:13:59.77,4:14:04.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,in a desperate attempt to justify the events of the core game itself?
Dialogue: 2,4:14:04.90,4:14:09.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just like {\i1}Red Dead Redemption 2{\i0}, it's gonna end up being the latter.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:09.46,4:14:14.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Answers to these questions will mostly come, but for now we're left in the dark.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:14.60,4:14:18.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,After cut to black, after this fight, we open up on a farm.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:18.76,4:14:24.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's an expansive wheat field with a farm house off in the distance and a barn behind it.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:24.19,4:14:25.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's very calm and picturesque.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:25.96,4:14:27.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,Inside we see Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,4:14:27.79,4:14:31.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,she seems, healed up and relatively healthy,
Dialogue: 2,4:14:31.36,4:14:36.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she's holding Joel's old broken watch that he got from Sarah in the first game.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:36.07,4:14:41.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is a not so subtle way of reminding the player that Ellie is still thinking about Joel,
Dialogue: 2,4:14:41.74,4:14:43.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that she hasn't moved on.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:43.42,4:14:45.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Also, there's a baby now.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:45.91,4:14:52.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,This reaffirms that it's been a good long while since the events of the previous scene.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:52.03,4:14:54.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, we see Dina in the kitchen,
Dialogue: 2,4:14:54.04,4:14:56.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it seems as though she's recovered just fine,
Dialogue: 2,4:14:56.74,4:14:59.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she also has her mom jeans coming in clutch.
Dialogue: 2,4:14:59.98,4:15:03.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean maybe, it's stupid, I'm honestly not sure what it is.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:03.01,4:15:07.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when I saw Dina in this scene, I thought that she just she looked like a mom.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:07.48,4:15:11.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it is, maybe they bushed up her eyebrows, and that did it.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:11.20,4:15:15.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's the strange outfit she has on or the fact that she's doing dishes.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:15.10,4:15:16.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it is.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:16.93,4:15:21.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,But they seemingly did a good job of making her appear as a mother,
Dialogue: 2,4:15:21.40,4:15:23.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,I guess props to Naughty Dog.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:23.05,4:15:26.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,And to be honest, everything seems calm and relatively happy,
Dialogue: 2,4:15:26.80,4:15:30.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,but nothing ever ends happily in this world.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:30.34,4:15:32.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,So of course this won't last for long.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:32.83,4:15:37.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie does some routine chores, you dance with Dina a little bit, and you explore the house.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:37.48,4:15:41.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Fun little note here is that Ellie actually has a good amount of art in the house
Dialogue: 2,4:15:41.77,4:15:43.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,that was taken from Joel's house.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:43.81,4:15:44.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a nice touch,
Dialogue: 2,4:15:44.74,4:15:47.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it makes sense since she would likely want to hold on to parts of him,
Dialogue: 2,4:15:47.89,4:15:50.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,as we just saw earlier when she had his watch.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:50.32,4:15:52.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just a really sweet little detail,
Dialogue: 2,4:15:52.27,4:15:56.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially considering the fact that the player will likely not notice this,
Dialogue: 2,4:15:56.38,4:15:58.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,at least on their first run through the game.
Dialogue: 2,4:15:58.36,4:16:03.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,I only noticed it once I spent a lot of time recording footage for this video
Dialogue: 2,4:16:03.22,4:16:05.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,going back through environments very carefully.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:05.80,4:16:10.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,I noticed that in Joel's house there are a lot of really nice looking paintings that I liked.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:10.48,4:16:13.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, I even reference those earlier in this very video.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:13.99,4:16:18.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,But then when I went back through this section, I noticed that those paintings looked similar.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:18.59,4:16:23.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I initially thought that they were just reusing assets which is pretty common in game development.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:23.11,4:16:26.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,But upon further inspection and deliberation,
Dialogue: 2,4:16:26.14,4:16:28.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,I realized that this was actually an artistic choice,
Dialogue: 2,4:16:28.87,4:16:34.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,because Ellie is trying to keep and bring parts of Joel into her life even still.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:34.00,4:16:36.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, after exploring the house and chilling with Dina for a little bit,
Dialogue: 2,4:16:36.97,4:16:41.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina asks Ellie to bring in the sheep from outside and put them into the barn.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:41.08,4:16:43.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Ellie goes, and does this with the baby.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:43.66,4:16:46.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,And after doing it, Ellie spots one little straggler.
Dialogue: 2,4:16:46.60,4:16:50.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,And there's probably leads to the fastest mood shift of the whole game.
Dialogue: 2,4:17:46.48,4:17:50.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,I really think that this moment is meant to hit the player just as hard as it hits Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,4:17:50.41,4:17:52.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everything seems fine, calm and relaxed.
Dialogue: 2,4:17:52.54,4:17:56.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems as though they've moved on from a lot of the struggles of the core game
Dialogue: 2,4:17:56.73,4:17:59.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that their living a happy, satisfied life together.
Dialogue: 2,4:17:59.86,4:18:02.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,But now everything is falling apart.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:02.68,4:18:05.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie's mind won't let her forget what happened to Joel,
Dialogue: 2,4:18:05.98,4:18:09.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she's clearly been unable to move on.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:09.10,4:18:14.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina knows this and is understanding because she knows that Ellie can't help this.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:14.17,4:18:16.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's something beyond her control,
Dialogue: 2,4:18:16.18,4:18:20.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,just like anybody else who suffers from panic attacks can't really control it.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:20.32,4:18:22.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,It just happens when it happens.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:22.36,4:18:24.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the game keeps carrying along, relatively quickly.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:24.94,4:18:28.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,We jump to the next day and there is a guest in the house.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:28.42,4:18:29.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's Tommy.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:29.26,4:18:32.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's survived the shot to the head.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:32.41,4:18:37.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,He's currently got a lot of damage that he's dealing with and he even struggles walking.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:37.15,4:18:41.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, he took a bullet to the head, so… it's understandable.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:41.41,4:18:42.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Clearly he's not in good shape,
Dialogue: 2,4:18:42.94,4:18:46.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,but he does not want to let Abby get away with what she's done.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:46.75,4:18:49.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,He says that he's tracked her to a location in Santa Barbara.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:49.93,4:18:51.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, even though he doesn't state it outright,
Dialogue: 2,4:18:51.85,4:18:54.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's pretty clear that he's unable to go and chase her himself.
Dialogue: 2,4:18:54.97,4:18:58.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,He can barely walk after all, and he's missing an eye now,
Dialogue: 2,4:18:58.09,4:19:01.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,so he wouldn't exactly be much help if he were to go.
Dialogue: 2,4:19:01.51,4:19:06.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so he's come to Ellie to proposition her for this revenge plot.
Dialogue: 2,4:19:06.16,4:19:08.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now initially, this might seem relatively far fetched
Dialogue: 2,4:19:08.69,4:19:14.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Tommy was able to track her down to a city that is very far away from where they are at.
Dialogue: 2,4:19:14.65,4:19:18.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Apparently they're just outside of Jackson in the surrounding area,
Dialogue: 2,4:19:18.67,4:19:22.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,so they're local, but they have moved out away from the core group.
Dialogue: 2,4:19:22.99,4:19:26.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, I don't think this is as far as stretch as it might initially seem.
Dialogue: 2,4:19:26.56,4:19:29.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy has a ton of connections to the Fireflies.
Dialogue: 2,4:19:29.29,4:19:30.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you remember from earlier,
Dialogue: 2,4:19:30.58,4:19:36.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Owen said that he wanted to go to Santa Barbara on the boat with Mel, Abby, Yara and Lev,
Dialogue: 2,4:19:36.85,4:19:40.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,because he thought that there were going to be a lot of Fireflies there
Dialogue: 2,4:19:40.36,4:19:42.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they could connect and join up with.
Dialogue: 2,4:19:42.57,4:19:46.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Using the same contacts, it seems Tommy was able to track
Dialogue: 2,4:19:46.28,4:19:54.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,a very buff woman with a small young Asian individual by her side to this area.
Dialogue: 2,4:19:54.67,4:19:59.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it seems relatively plausible that they would be able to track her to this point,
Dialogue: 2,4:19:59.14,4:20:05.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially if Tommy were to put out an APB on this individual trying to find her,
Dialogue: 2,4:20:05.05,4:20:06.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,which he's clearly done.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:06.25,4:20:11.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, after hearing his proposition, Ellie and Dina strongly reject the idea.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:11.95,4:20:13.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,They are done with that.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:13.03,4:20:16.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or at the very least, Dina is, and Ellie going along with it.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:16.36,4:20:18.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now they have too much to lose.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:18.73,4:20:22.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,They have a house of family and of course each other.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:22.49,4:20:24.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,They've been there, done that.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:24.03,4:20:27.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the last time they tried to chase Abby down, it didn't end well.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:27.67,4:20:30.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tommy leaves furious that they're not going to do anything.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:30.91,4:20:33.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,He feels betrayed, and even calls Ellie out,
Dialogue: 2,4:20:33.75,4:20:37.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,since she told him that she was going to do whatever it took to get revenge.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:37.99,4:20:43.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's an understandable reaction, considering that Tommy is still furious about his brother's death,
Dialogue: 2,4:20:43.03,4:20:46.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that she has now permanently scarred him.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:46.48,4:20:52.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it is a little startling to see Tommy react in such a sharp way towards Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,4:20:52.15,4:20:55.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, I can't think of a time when we've ever seen Tommy
Dialogue: 2,4:20:55.55,4:21:01.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,react or talk to somebody in this way throughout the entirety of this franchise.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:01.12,4:21:06.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,The closest example would be in the first game when Joel and Tommy got frustrated with each other
Dialogue: 2,4:21:06.76,4:21:08.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,when they initially visited the power plant.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:08.80,4:21:12.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,But even that wasn't this sharp or direct.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:12.16,4:21:17.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina asks that Tommy leaves and then yells at him for a brief moment outside
Dialogue: 2,4:21:17.11,4:21:19.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,where it can still be overheard by Ellie.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:19.81,4:21:22.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Ellie is still caught up in all of this.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:22.72,4:21:27.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,She knows that Dina is not OK with her going and trying to end this once and for all,
Dialogue: 2,4:21:27.61,4:21:30.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,but she's still pondering everything.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:30.31,4:21:31.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, in the next scene,
Dialogue: 2,4:21:31.75,4:21:34.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,we see her walking aimlessly through the house in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 2,4:21:34.93,4:21:37.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,unable to sleep and unsure of what to do.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:37.72,4:21:41.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,She wants revenge but knows that it may cost her everything.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:41.53,4:21:45.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,She plays a little ditty and Joel's old guitar to take her mind off of everything.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:45.70,4:21:47.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't seem to do anything.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:47.74,4:21:50.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, it seems to make everything worse.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:50.32,4:21:53.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,We then jumped to the scene of the Jackson Winter Ball
Dialogue: 2,4:21:53.16,4:21:56.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,that we have only heard discussed up to this point.
Dialogue: 2,4:21:56.32,4:21:59.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,It plays out just like we saw in the trailer before launch,
Dialogue: 2,4:21:59.62,4:22:04.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,except that now we see the events described in the first hours of the game.
Dialogue: 2,4:22:04.33,4:22:09.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,After the happenings of the trailer, culminating in the kiss between Ellie and Dina,
Dialogue: 2,4:22:09.16,4:22:13.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,an old man makes a disparaging comments about Dina and Ellie kissing.
Dialogue: 2,4:22:13.08,4:22:17.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel steps in and pushes them which upsets Ellie for some reason.
Dialogue: 2,4:22:17.62,4:22:23.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,Likely because she feels as though Joel is once again keeping her from fighting her own fights.
Dialogue: 2,4:22:23.23,4:22:25.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we'll talk about this more in just a little bit.
Dialogue: 2,4:22:25.66,4:22:30.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, back in the present, Ellie has decided that she has to take Abby on,
Dialogue: 2,4:22:30.44,4:22:32.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,to finish this once, and for all,
Dialogue: 2,4:22:32.62,4:22:36.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Perhaps reminded of this confrontation with the old, bigoted man,
Dialogue: 2,4:22:36.34,4:22:40.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,she realizes that she needs to fight her own fights and finish this,
Dialogue: 2,4:22:40.27,4:22:42.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,otherwise she won't be able to live with herself.
Dialogue: 2,4:22:42.34,4:22:45.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, this time she's not just leaving Jackson behind,
Dialogue: 2,4:22:45.82,4:22:50.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's abandoning her entire family, this whole thing that she's built up.
Dialogue: 2,4:22:50.14,4:22:53.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once again it's hard to feel sorry for Ellie here,
Dialogue: 2,4:22:53.62,4:22:55.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially since most people I think
Dialogue: 2,4:22:55.98,4:23:00.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,would say that she should have left well enough alone and not chased Abby again.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:00.07,4:23:04.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,Literally every single person I've talked to about this final decision by Ellie
Dialogue: 2,4:23:04.42,4:23:07.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,to leave everything, and Chase Abby down again
Dialogue: 2,4:23:07.56,4:23:12.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,has said that this was the wrong decision, and that they didn't want her to do it.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:12.31,4:23:15.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,They wanted her to forgive Abby to move on.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:15.55,4:23:20.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's yet another example of how emotionally exhausting the scheme can be to play,
Dialogue: 2,4:23:20.26,4:23:23.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,because when you don't agree with what the characters are doing,
Dialogue: 2,4:23:23.80,4:23:25.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,you start to lose sympathy with them.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:25.90,4:23:29.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that makes it harder to empathize with everything that they're going through.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:29.98,4:23:32.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie starts packing up her things when Dina finds her.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:32.89,4:23:35.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina clearly knows that Ellie's been considering this
Dialogue: 2,4:23:35.61,4:23:38.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,but is terrified to see her actually going through with it.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:38.89,4:23:40.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina begs her to come back to bed,
Dialogue: 2,4:23:40.51,4:23:45.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,to move on, to forget about everything, to stay with the family and not do this.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:45.52,4:23:48.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Ellie says she has no choice and has to.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:48.61,4:23:52.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina makes it very clear that she's not going to do this whole thing again.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:52.81,4:23:54.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's not going to go and help her.
Dialogue: 2,4:23:54.49,4:23:58.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if Ellie decides that this is what's most important to her,
Dialogue: 2,4:23:58.06,4:24:04.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,she shouldn't expect to find her and the baby there when or if she gets back alive.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:04.63,4:24:07.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,She is effectively giving Ellie an ultimatum.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:07.39,4:24:09.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Choose Abby, or choose Dina,
Dialogue: 2,4:24:09.94,4:24:13.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the family, and everything that she's built up with her.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:13.78,4:24:15.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie chooses Abby.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:15.38,4:24:20.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, giving the player very little reason to feel bad or sorry for her,
Dialogue: 2,4:24:20.84,4:24:25.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Losing Dina, and for all of the pain that she's likely to encounter
Dialogue: 2,4:24:25.18,4:24:27.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,in the next few hours as the game wraps up.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:27.49,4:24:30.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,So Ellie leaves, Dina's left devastated.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:30.97,4:24:33.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Naughty Dog pulls a fake out.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:33.18,4:24:34.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,We jumped to California.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:34.54,4:24:38.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a market set difference, everything's very dry and dead.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:38.50,4:24:42.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,The chapter opens up with the camera focused on a pair of Converse.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:42.10,4:24:45.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Anyone who's played the first game knows that this is Ellie signature shoe.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:45.97,4:24:47.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the camera pans up,
Dialogue: 2,4:24:47.62,4:24:52.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we see that it's Lev wearing the shoes and Abby's walking alongside him.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:52.27,4:24:54.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now this is a bit obvious for me,
Dialogue: 2,4:24:54.13,4:24:59.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it's clearly setting up the parallel between Abby and Joel and Ellie and Lev.
Dialogue: 2,4:24:59.74,4:25:04.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Whether you think those are fair to draw as comparisons or similes is up to you,
Dialogue: 2,4:25:04.24,4:25:06.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,but that's clearly what the writers are doing.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:06.43,4:25:08.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie is known for her Converse,
Dialogue: 2,4:25:08.20,4:25:12.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,and in fact it's one of the staples of her outfit in the first game,
Dialogue: 2,4:25:12.31,4:25:14.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,and even throughout most of the second game.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:14.35,4:25:20.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,To so clearly show these shoes to me is hitting the player over the head with this simile.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:20.92,4:25:23.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now Abby and Lev are looking for the Fireflies
Dialogue: 2,4:25:23.16,4:25:25.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,hoping to find a new home to which they can belong.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:25.56,4:25:29.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again, remembering that Owen suggested Santa Barbara way back when.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:29.80,4:25:33.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now they had a tip that 2425 Constance in Santa Barbara
Dialogue: 2,4:25:33.93,4:25:36.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,was a hideout for the underground Firefly network.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:36.97,4:25:40.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so after Abby and Lev fight through a few infected,
Dialogue: 2,4:25:40.87,4:25:42.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,they worked their way to the basement of the house,
Dialogue: 2,4:25:42.88,4:25:44.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the pair discovers a radio.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:44.92,4:25:47.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,And after a few attempts they connect with somebody.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:47.59,4:25:52.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it seems as though Abby and Lev have found their new home and will be safe after all.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:52.69,4:25:55.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,But again, no, everything is sad and terrible.
Dialogue: 2,4:25:55.78,4:26:01.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,Nothing's gonna end happily, so just get ready, everything is going to go terribly wrong.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:01.45,4:26:05.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the two set up a meet up point where they're gonna head to meet up with the Fireflies.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:05.47,4:26:06.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,As the pair leaves the house,
Dialogue: 2,4:26:06.70,4:26:10.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,they are intercepted by a small gang as they exit out the front of the house.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:10.78,4:26:13.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems that these people are involved in the slave trade,
Dialogue: 2,4:26:13.57,4:26:17.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,which, to be honest, I'm stunned took this long to be featured in the game.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:17.50,4:26:20.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're beaten, tied up and taken away,
Dialogue: 2,4:26:20.17,4:26:25.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,presumably to be entered into the slave trade and used for manual labor.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:25.39,4:26:27.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,We then cut to Ellie, who was closing in quickly.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:27.88,4:26:30.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's found their boat and begins pushing into their location
Dialogue: 2,4:26:30.72,4:26:34.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,after finding a map that has 2425 Constance marked on it.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:34.15,4:26:36.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,As you push through multiple houses and streets,
Dialogue: 2,4:26:36.94,4:26:40.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,this is the last zombie hurrah combat in the entire game.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:40.24,4:26:41.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,So be sure to enjoy it.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:41.36,4:26:45.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because after this Naughty Dog is going to be sticking with human enemies exclusively.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:45.46,4:26:49.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Except for one small exception, which I'll point out in a moment.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:49.09,4:26:52.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,But still, it's going to be pretty much all humans after this.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:52.03,4:26:55.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie pushes her way through an initial neighborhood and starts climbing down a hill.
Dialogue: 2,4:26:55.84,4:26:56.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,When this happens.
Dialogue: 2,4:28:59.56,4:29:02.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now these guys are obviously super dome.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:02.17,4:29:07.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,But you have to ask yourself as the player, what's keeping you going?
Dialogue: 2,4:29:07.16,4:29:12.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Other than just going through the motions of continuing to do what the game asks you to do.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:12.22,4:29:15.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,One of the best things about the early hours of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}
Dialogue: 2,4:29:15.02,4:29:21.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,is that the player is completely on board with Ellie's drive and mission to take out Abby.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:21.34,4:29:22.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,And as the game goes on,
Dialogue: 2,4:29:22.54,4:29:28.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,you also start to lose that motivation once you start to sympathize with Abby and her crew.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:28.06,4:29:31.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you end up very conflicted in that final boss fight
Dialogue: 2,4:29:31.15,4:29:34.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,where you don't want to do anything or hurt either one of these characters.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:34.66,4:29:37.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,But now the players still feels like that.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:37.48,4:29:41.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,And yet the game designers are asking Ellie to chase down Abby,
Dialogue: 2,4:29:41.44,4:29:44.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though it's caused her to lose everything at this point
Dialogue: 2,4:29:44.68,4:29:48.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,and will likely not result in the conclusion
Dialogue: 2,4:29:48.46,4:29:51.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,that either the player or Ellie he would be satisfied with.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:51.64,4:29:53.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,Some people have said that this is a pacing issue,
Dialogue: 2,4:29:53.83,4:29:56.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I don't think that that's the right way to phrase it.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:56.44,4:29:59.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,If anything, I think that this is a motivational issue.
Dialogue: 2,4:29:59.17,4:30:03.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think the player doesn't feel motivated to continue on this mission
Dialogue: 2,4:30:03.24,4:30:05.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they're being asked to embark on.
Dialogue: 2,4:30:05.59,4:30:07.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now of course, you could have a game
Dialogue: 2,4:30:07.07,4:30:11.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,that motivates the player to continue playing purely by way of its game play,
Dialogue: 2,4:30:11.14,4:30:14.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,and there is no narrative reason to continue at all.
Dialogue: 2,4:30:14.32,4:30:17.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, that's not how Naughty Dog games work.
Dialogue: 2,4:30:17.29,4:30:23.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Naughty Dog games are entirely about motivating the player by way of this narrative drive.
Dialogue: 2,4:30:23.77,4:30:27.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I'll be honest, it's really too bad that this falls so flat
Dialogue: 2,4:30:27.32,4:30:29.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,because this should be the climax of the game.
Dialogue: 2,4:30:29.62,4:30:32.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,But instead it feels as though it's a total chore,
Dialogue: 2,4:30:32.95,4:30:37.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,because the player doesn't feel as though Ellie is justified in what she's doing.
Dialogue: 2,4:30:37.09,4:30:40.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,And certainly Ellie is even frustrated with her own decision.
Dialogue: 2,4:30:40.81,4:30:45.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,The only reason Ellie is continuing on it is because she feels an obligation to Joel,
Dialogue: 2,4:30:45.49,4:30:48.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,an obligation that's going to be resolved very shortly.
Dialogue: 2,4:30:48.73,4:30:54.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,But even so, the player pushes on into the slave trader camped known as "the Resort".
Dialogue: 2,4:30:54.46,4:30:56.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's not a sassy or funny name,
Dialogue: 2,4:30:56.44,4:31:01.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's just that it's an old resort, so they call it "the Resort", it's pretty simple.
Dialogue: 2,4:31:01.85,4:31:05.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now this section does feature my favorite gun of the entire game,
Dialogue: 2,4:31:05.44,4:31:10.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it's so damn powerful that it removes any need for any finesse whatsoever.
Dialogue: 2,4:31:10.99,4:31:12.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,So with this new found super weapon,
Dialogue: 2,4:31:12.97,4:31:17.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,you fight your way through the Resorts main building where all of the slaves are housed.
Dialogue: 2,4:31:17.62,4:31:20.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,And to be honest, the section is actually pretty bad,
Dialogue: 2,4:31:20.23,4:31:24.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially when considering that it is the final section of the game.
Dialogue: 2,4:31:24.55,4:31:30.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is the final game play section of the game other than the final boss quote-unquote, "fight",
Dialogue: 2,4:31:30.76,4:31:33.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and its painfully uninteresting.
Dialogue: 2,4:31:33.10,4:31:35.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,The only thing that shakes it up a little bit
Dialogue: 2,4:31:35.32,4:31:40.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,is having zombies chained up that you can release on the human NPCs.
Dialogue: 2,4:31:40.36,4:31:43.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,But other than that, there's really nothing that's interesting about this level.
Dialogue: 2,4:31:43.57,4:31:47.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,And even though zombies, you shoot off their chains or disconnect them,
Dialogue: 2,4:31:47.17,4:31:50.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they started attacking the other people, the other NPCs
Dialogue: 2,4:31:50.48,4:31:53.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then you just end up having to kill zombies before they come to you
Dialogue: 2,4:31:53.56,4:31:56.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,if they are not already killed by those human NPCs.
Dialogue: 2,4:31:56.77,4:32:00.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it even by itself doesn't do anything new or different.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:00.61,4:32:02.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just bland.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:02.61,4:32:06.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's unfortunate because it really should be the climax,
Dialogue: 2,4:32:06.31,4:32:09.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,but instead it just lands super flat.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:09.28,4:32:10.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,I was really surprised to see this
Dialogue: 2,4:32:10.82,4:32:14.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,because usually Naughty Dog is pretty good about sticking the landing.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:14.05,4:32:18.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,They go crazy, big and elaborate in the final sections of the game,
Dialogue: 2,4:32:18.31,4:32:21.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,whether you're looking at {\i1}Uncharted{\i0} or even the original {\i1}TLOU{\i0} game
Dialogue: 2,4:32:21.88,4:32:25.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they really push the boundary of difficulty.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:25.27,4:32:27.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,But here it just doesn't work.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:27.64,4:32:32.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,But even so, after killing countless slavers, Ellie finds her way to the beach.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:32.17,4:32:34.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's told by several other prisoners
Dialogue: 2,4:32:34.04,4:32:38.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,that this is where Abby and Lev have been moved after they tried to escape.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:38.26,4:32:41.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,And usually the slaves are left here hung up until they die.
Dialogue: 2,4:32:41.74,4:32:44.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I gotta say it's pretty surreal once you reach this beach
Dialogue: 2,4:32:44.96,4:32:47.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,and what Ellie finds there is pretty upsetting.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:08.20,4:33:12.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now there's actually a fake out with the girl in the center that has the braid.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:12.55,4:33:16.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,It looks like Abby, especially Abby the last time that we saw her.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:16.42,4:33:18.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's not Abby.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:18.60,4:33:21.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby in fact, you just walked past.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:21.81,4:33:24.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,And she's in much worse shape.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:39.17,4:33:42.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Truely, she doesn't even look like the same person.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:42.46,4:33:46.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now it took a moment that Abby recognizes Ellie here,
Dialogue: 2,4:33:46.06,4:33:48.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,but she's not interested in fighting.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:48.37,4:33:52.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,Instead, the moment that Ellie cuts her down, she goes to help Lev.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:52.66,4:33:56.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby then carries Lev into the distance despite her weakness.
Dialogue: 2,4:33:56.68,4:33:58.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,And they come up on the same boat
Dialogue: 2,4:33:58.55,4:34:02.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,that we've seen in the title screen every time we booted up the game to this point.
Dialogue: 2,4:34:02.95,4:34:07.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even now, Abby is purely concerned with taking care of Lev,
Dialogue: 2,4:34:07.06,4:34:09.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,making sure that they are able to get out safely.
Dialogue: 2,4:34:09.94,4:34:13.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,She even leads Ellie to the boats to help her escape.
Dialogue: 2,4:34:13.33,4:34:16.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm aware that Ellie has come to kill her
Dialogue: 2,4:34:16.84,4:34:20.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,and enact the revenge that she sought out initially.
Dialogue: 2,4:34:20.32,4:34:25.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,As far as we know, Abby may think that Ellie was being housed as a slave herself,
Dialogue: 2,4:34:25.39,4:34:27.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,and has escaped to this point.
Dialogue: 2,4:34:27.34,4:34:29.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,But whatever it may be,
Dialogue: 2,4:34:29.08,4:34:31.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby gets down to the boat area
Dialogue: 2,4:34:31.52,4:34:36.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Ellie still wounded from the tree branch that she was impaled with,
Dialogue: 2,4:34:36.04,4:34:40.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,and Abby, wounded from the weeks or months of torture,
Dialogue: 2,4:34:40.41,4:34:46.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,at their very end, have to face off in one final painful battle.
Dialogue: 2,4:34:46.27,4:34:50.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie demands to fight with Abby to finish this once and for all.
Dialogue: 2,4:34:50.31,4:34:55.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,She even takes out her switch blade and threatens to kill Lev if Abby doesn't engage with her.
Dialogue: 2,4:34:55.48,4:34:57.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so left with no choice,
Dialogue: 2,4:34:57.79,4:35:03.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Abby decides that she'll fight Ellie, not for her, not for Ellie, but for Lev.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:03.67,4:35:07.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you show to player this fight scene at the very start of the game,
Dialogue: 2,4:35:07.90,4:35:10.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,it would probably give them a lot of pleasure.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:10.45,4:35:16.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,It would feel good for the player to literally hack and slash the person that killed Joel to pieces.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:16.66,4:35:20.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,But instead, it's absolutely horrible, it's pathetic.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:20.95,4:35:25.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,And no part of this feels like a comeuppance or like justice.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:25.06,4:35:29.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think if anything, this means that the game's arc worked.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:29.50,4:35:33.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,It actually went from me wanting to kill Joel's killer
Dialogue: 2,4:35:33.67,4:35:36.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,to wanting to forgive her and move on.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:36.43,4:35:38.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's simple, but it's powerful.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:38.74,4:35:44.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,And as this fight continued on, all I could ask for was that they would just stop.
Dialogue: 2,4:35:44.83,4:35:46.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the fight continues,
Dialogue: 2,4:35:46.78,4:35:51.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,each growing weaker and weaker until the fight comes to its inevitable conclusion.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:10.57,4:38:12.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're now back at the farm house.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:12.52,4:38:17.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,It seems to have been quite a while, since everything is so dilapidated.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:17.02,4:38:21.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,The house's empty, the paint chipping, the woods warped,
Dialogue: 2,4:38:21.50,4:38:24.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think all of this is meant to show that Dina moved out with the baby
Dialogue: 2,4:38:24.72,4:38:26.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that Ellie is now alone.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:26.50,4:38:30.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,But regardless, it's been quite a while since anyone's been here.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:30.10,4:38:33.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so while it may be meant to show that Ellie is alone
Dialogue: 2,4:38:33.87,4:38:36.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that the ramifications for her actions
Dialogue: 2,4:38:36.86,4:38:40.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,have taken much more of a toll than just the loss of a couple fingers.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:40.96,4:38:42.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it might not be that simple,
Dialogue: 2,4:38:42.76,4:38:46.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this might actually be a happier ending than it might initially seem to be.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:46.78,4:38:48.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,But we'll get to that in just a few minutes.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:48.82,4:38:50.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie walks through the empty house,
Dialogue: 2,4:38:50.65,4:38:55.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,eventually coming into one room that has what seems to be most of Ellie's old things,
Dialogue: 2,4:38:55.30,4:38:58.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,and a lot of Joel's items that were collected throughout the house.
Dialogue: 2,4:38:58.66,4:39:00.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,She takes up Joel's guitar
Dialogue: 2,4:39:00.52,4:39:06.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,and plays a strained version of the song that he played for her in the beginning.
Dialogue: 2,4:39:06.04,4:39:12.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Her missing fingers, now a permanent example of the distance between Joel and Ellie
Dialogue: 2,4:39:12.16,4:39:14.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,and their inability to truly connect,
Dialogue: 2,4:39:14.84,4:39:18.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,she can't even play the song properly or fully now.
Dialogue: 2,4:39:18.52,4:39:21.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,We then cut to the most important scene of the whole game.
Dialogue: 2,4:39:21.61,4:39:23.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,A scene that I couldn't do justice
Dialogue: 2,4:39:23.65,4:39:26.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,even if I were to spend weeks riding it outward for word.
Dialogue: 2,4:39:26.62,4:39:28.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,So instead, I'm just going to let it play.
Dialogue: 2,4:45:32.17,4:45:34.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,And just like that, the game is over.
Dialogue: 2,4:45:34.87,4:45:38.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,Closing in on the same shot that the game opened up with,
Dialogue: 2,4:45:38.37,4:45:41.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,a focus on Joel's guitar as he was cleaning it at the very start,
Dialogue: 2,4:45:41.98,4:45:46.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,describing what happened the hospital at the end of the first game.
Dialogue: 2,4:45:46.09,4:45:50.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,The last scene demonstrating how Ellie was going to try and forgive Joel
Dialogue: 2,4:45:50.85,4:45:54.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,and move on the very night before his passing.
Dialogue: 2,4:45:54.04,4:45:57.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,The story reaches a surprising conclusion.
Dialogue: 2,4:45:57.73,4:45:59.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is why, back at the beginning of the video,
Dialogue: 2,4:45:59.86,4:46:05.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,I told you that Ellie wanting to have a movie night with Joel was so very important.
Dialogue: 2,4:46:05.92,4:46:09.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was going to be their first step towards healing.
Dialogue: 2,4:46:09.04,4:46:11.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,They were going to try and bury the hatchet,
Dialogue: 2,4:46:11.38,4:46:15.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why Ellie was so unbelievably distraught
Dialogue: 2,4:46:15.10,4:46:18.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,when she lost Joel before this healing could take place.
Dialogue: 2,4:46:18.37,4:46:19.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it seems as though,
Dialogue: 2,4:46:19.45,4:46:22.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,after all of this contemplation, all of this nervousness,
Dialogue: 2,4:46:22.72,4:46:27.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,all of this stress, all of this hatred that had built up over months,
Dialogue: 2,4:46:27.94,4:46:31.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,and at this point, years of struggling with Joel's demise
Dialogue: 2,4:46:31.84,4:46:35.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,that she's realized the best way to deal with that grief
Dialogue: 2,4:46:35.75,4:46:40.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,is to accept that he's gone and to move on, living her life happily,
Dialogue: 2,4:46:40.60,4:46:42.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,not seeking revenge,
Dialogue: 2,4:46:42.40,4:46:47.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,but living it with people like Joel, who loved her, for her,
Dialogue: 2,4:46:47.74,4:46:54.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,and where she could enact and practice that very same love and affection that she received.
Dialogue: 2,4:46:54.79,4:46:57.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,And as she walks off into the distance,
Dialogue: 2,4:46:57.13,4:47:02.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's leaving everything behind, all of Joel's old items, everything that he left her.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:02.95,4:47:04.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,She has moved on.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:04.87,4:47:08.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it seems as though, after a very long journey,
Dialogue: 2,4:47:08.77,4:47:13.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Joel and Ellie story has finally come to an end.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:13.48,4:47:16.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,And just like that the game is over.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:16.69,4:47:19.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, I really don't know
Dialogue: 2,4:47:19.41,4:47:23.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,how to break down where my mind was when I first saw these credits roll.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:24.84,4:47:30.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I feel as though the best way to kind of wrap all of this up is by talking with you guys,
Dialogue: 2,4:47:30.01,4:47:34.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,one on one in an unscripted way, or I can just wrap up all of my thoughts.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:34.39,4:47:37.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because I think that this game is truly exceptional,
Dialogue: 2,4:47:37.85,4:47:41.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,again in the purest sense of the word, where it's an exception to the rule.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:41.83,4:47:43.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Most games, you can give a thumbs up or thumbs down,
Dialogue: 2,4:47:43.93,4:47:45.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,you can say it's really good or it's really bad.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:45.70,4:47:49.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,And {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} is a game I think is very, very good.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:49.45,4:47:52.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's an enjoyable game play experience, I think.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:52.45,4:47:56.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,For the most part, it works really well, except for some pacing issues.
Dialogue: 2,4:47:56.53,4:48:02.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,But a lot of those pacing issues are problematic, primarily because of the narrative
Dialogue: 2,4:48:02.61,4:48:07.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,because you want to focus on one character and you're having to keep swap between the two.
Dialogue: 2,4:48:07.12,4:48:09.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,But even so, there're some gameplay pacing issues,
Dialogue: 2,4:48:09.46,4:48:14.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,such as having problems with climax building
Dialogue: 2,4:48:14.39,4:48:19.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,and making sure that the final boss fights are really intriguing and interesting, and things like that.
Dialogue: 2,4:48:19.87,4:48:25.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,But all told, as far as the game is concerned, it's very well done as a game,
Dialogue: 2,4:48:25.37,4:48:28.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and most people who have a problem with {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}
Dialogue: 2,4:48:28.63,4:48:31.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,don't deny that they accepted and agree with it.
Dialogue: 2,4:48:31.24,4:48:35.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that doesn't seem to be where the criticisms tend to come out.
Dialogue: 2,4:48:35.98,4:48:39.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think we're most criticisms find themselves presented…
Dialogue: 2,4:48:40.51,4:48:44.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,our with regards to the direction Naughty Dog chose to go in.
Dialogue: 2,4:48:45.19,4:48:47.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because the writers, of course, had the option,
Dialogue: 2,4:48:47.80,4:48:50.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,they didn't have to go the direction that they did.
Dialogue: 2,4:48:50.35,4:48:52.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,They didn't have to kill Joel off for one,
Dialogue: 2,4:48:52.36,4:48:55.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,they didn't have to make you empathize with Abby,
Dialogue: 2,4:48:55.93,4:49:00.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,they didn't have to make you play as Abby for the second half of the game,
Dialogue: 2,4:49:00.70,4:49:02.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,they didn't have to do any of that.
Dialogue: 2,4:49:02.17,4:49:04.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that's the direction they chose to go in.
Dialogue: 2,4:49:04.03,4:49:06.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think as far as I can tell,
Dialogue: 2,4:49:06.25,4:49:13.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,most people were hoping and expecting that the game would be about Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,4:49:13.15,4:49:14.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that's it.
Dialogue: 2,4:49:14.56,4:49:19.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,They weren't interested in playing and getting to know this new character.
Dialogue: 2,4:49:20.20,4:49:23.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think that that's just the frustrating thing about it
Dialogue: 2,4:49:23.76,4:49:26.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,is that a lot of people were hoping and expecting to
Dialogue: 2,4:49:26.96,4:49:29.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,have exposure and experience with Ellie
Dialogue: 2,4:49:29.44,4:49:34.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,that was not just dreadful through and through.
Dialogue: 2,4:49:34.03,4:49:37.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,But instead they were forced to go through this very frustrating and
Dialogue: 2,4:49:37.97,4:49:41.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,very emotionally taxing journey with her,
Dialogue: 2,4:49:41.35,4:49:43.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,which I think is probably where I land.
Dialogue: 2,4:49:43.75,4:49:48.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because I really cherish Ellie as a character, I care about her,
Dialogue: 2,4:49:48.97,4:49:50.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I connected with her on a level,
Dialogue: 2,4:49:50.64,4:49:53.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize I could connect with the character in the first game.
Dialogue: 2,4:49:53.74,4:49:58.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,And her actions in the second game make her very difficult to sympathize with.
Dialogue: 2,4:49:58.66,4:50:02.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because she's doing things that are objectively pretty dumb and stupid
Dialogue: 2,4:50:02.04,4:50:05.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,that aren't for the betterment of her and the people around her.
Dialogue: 2,4:50:05.95,4:50:08.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's being fairly selfish in what she's doing,
Dialogue: 2,4:50:08.47,4:50:14.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she does feel a… an obligation of sorts to Joel to continue on in her revenge journey.
Dialogue: 2,4:50:14.98,4:50:20.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,But still, it's not the same as the actions of Joel in the first game
Dialogue: 2,4:50:20.59,4:50:22.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,where he goes after Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,4:50:22.07,4:50:27.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though he's killing a lot of people to get to her and to save her from the Fireflies
Dialogue: 2,4:50:27.12,4:50:29.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,and everything they are about to do to her.
Dialogue: 2,4:50:29.28,4:50:32.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,At least there you can understand why he's doing it and you might even agreed
Dialogue: 2,4:50:32.70,4:50:34.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,because you care about Ellie too.
Dialogue: 2,4:50:34.27,4:50:36.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you might say I care about her so much,
Dialogue: 2,4:50:36.49,4:50:39.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would probably do the same thing if I was in his shoes.
Dialogue: 2,4:50:39.39,4:50:43.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,With Ellie in this game, many times, I found myself saying
Dialogue: 2,4:50:43.67,4:50:47.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would not have done that. That was the wrong choice, I don't agree with that.
Dialogue: 2,4:50:47.44,4:50:50.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,I care about you Ellie, and that's why I disagree with what you're doing.
Dialogue: 2,4:50:50.53,4:50:55.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,She's on a self destructive, borderline suicide mission throughout the entire game,
Dialogue: 2,4:50:55.93,4:50:59.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that just makes it so hard to sympathize with her, if not impossible.
Dialogue: 2,4:51:00.40,4:51:02.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,And when you don't sympathize with somebody,
Dialogue: 2,4:51:02.95,4:51:05.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,you shouldn't be surprised when people don't connect with them,
Dialogue: 2,4:51:05.53,4:51:07.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why, for a lot of people,
Dialogue: 2,4:51:07.33,4:51:12.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,they found themselves feeling as though that this wasn't a {\i1}TLOU{\i0} game, even by itself.
Dialogue: 2,4:51:12.76,4:51:16.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a sequel, it was a completely separate story.
Dialogue: 2,4:51:16.63,4:51:18.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie had grown up and become a different person,
Dialogue: 2,4:51:18.85,4:51:23.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she was almost unrecognisable from the character she was in the first game,
Dialogue: 2,4:51:23.50,4:51:27.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why Naughty Dog keep springing up all these flashbacks
Dialogue: 2,4:51:27.04,4:51:30.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,to kind of remind you of what Ellie used to be like.
Dialogue: 2,4:51:31.30,4:51:34.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that isn't enough, because you're playing in the current timeline.
Dialogue: 2,4:51:34.66,4:51:39.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if that Ellie is not enjoyable, isn't sympathetic, and you don't care about her,
Dialogue: 2,4:51:39.55,4:51:41.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,you don't care about her.
Dialogue: 2,4:51:41.08,4:51:43.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,So when we bring up the question,
Dialogue: 2,4:51:43.51,4:51:47.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,whether or not Ellie is is a well written character in this story.
Dialogue: 2,4:51:47.86,4:51:50.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think for the story they were trying to tell she was well written,
Dialogue: 2,4:51:50.95,4:51:53.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it accomplish the purpose which for Naughty Dog
Dialogue: 2,4:51:53.94,4:52:00.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,was to make you sympathize with somebody that killed a character you loved and cared about,
Dialogue: 2,4:52:00.00,4:52:03.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,to make you see the other side of the story,
Dialogue: 2,4:52:03.58,4:52:05.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,to understand all the perspectives,
Dialogue: 2,4:52:05.76,4:52:08.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,and to get that sometimes violence isn't the answer.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:08.92,4:52:14.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,And sometimes, terrible things happen and are somewhat justified.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:14.38,4:52:18.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or that you could even find yourself in the shoes of that character doing that thing
Dialogue: 2,4:52:19.16,4:52:23.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,if you were put into some sort of like different circumstances, you know.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:23.17,4:52:27.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think that that's a really interesting story to tell.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:27.76,4:52:29.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think that's a fair story to tell.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:29.29,4:52:31.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's… when I think of the game that way,
Dialogue: 2,4:52:31.84,4:52:36.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,I find myself much more impressed with it and thinking that it's absolutely a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:37.42,4:52:40.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I think my frustration is that it was a {\i1}TLOU{\i0} game.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:41.48,4:52:49.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that they sacrifice not just Joel but also Ellie at the altar of that story.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:49.09,4:52:53.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because I don't think that creating new characters
Dialogue: 2,4:52:53.29,4:52:58.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,and telling the story from start to finish with new characters would have been as successful.
Dialogue: 2,4:52:58.24,4:53:05.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,”I think part of what makes that story arc of "Forgiving the Unforgivable", the title of this video.
Dialogue: 2,4:53:06.13,4:53:10.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think that's part… of what of what makes it so impressive is that
Dialogue: 2,4:53:10.93,4:53:16.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,you are dealing with characters you've known effectively for a decade at this point.
Dialogue: 2,4:53:16.35,4:53:18.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,You've known for seven plus years,
Dialogue: 2,4:53:18.58,4:53:21.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,by the time you're watching this magnum for… for longer than that.
Dialogue: 2,4:53:22.45,4:53:26.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think that that's just what's really frustrating,
Dialogue: 2,4:53:26.52,4:53:31.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,but understandable is that they sacrifice these two characters that you love
Dialogue: 2,4:53:31.28,4:53:33.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,for the sake of telling this story,
Dialogue: 2,4:53:33.34,4:53:36.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,when they reassured us prior to launch
Dialogue: 2,4:53:36.16,4:53:40.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,that they were doing what was best for the characters that they weren't going to do them dirty,
Dialogue: 2,4:53:40.84,4:53:44.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,that this was what was best for Joel and Ellie,
Dialogue: 2,4:53:44.08,4:53:48.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they wouldn't be making the game if they didn't feel as though it was the right story to tell.
Dialogue: 2,4:53:49.72,4:53:53.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I can understand the frustration on that end.
Dialogue: 2,4:53:53.80,4:53:57.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,A lot of people also are frustrated that the game doesn't seem to have a happy ending
Dialogue: 2,4:53:57.46,4:54:00.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,that Ellie lost everything then moves on.
Dialogue: 2,4:54:01.24,4:54:03.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Forgets Joel and forgets Dina,
Dialogue: 2,4:54:03.94,4:54:06.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,and leaves everything behind and
Dialogue: 2,4:54:06.20,4:54:10.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,seemingly has lost everything hasn't gained, anything other than
Dialogue: 2,4:54:10.08,4:54:14.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,maybe coming to grips and peace with what happened with Joel moving on,
Dialogue: 2,4:54:14.17,4:54:17.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,leaving all of his stuff behind in the farmhouse.
Dialogue: 2,4:54:17.14,4:54:21.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I actually think that there's remnants of a happy ending here,
Dialogue: 2,4:54:21.13,4:54:23.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's something that's a small detail,
Dialogue: 2,4:54:23.02,4:54:29.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's something I didn't really consider until a good number of people had tweeted it at me
Dialogue: 2,4:54:29.90,4:54:35.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and… had… mentioned it on Discord.
Dialogue: 2,4:54:35.02,4:54:38.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's something that once I started to investigate it, I was kind of blown away,
Dialogue: 2,4:54:38.11,4:54:40.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I thought that it's actually really interesting theory.
Dialogue: 2,4:54:40.68,4:54:46.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because you see at the end of the core story of {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} after Ellie and Abby have their fight out,
Dialogue: 2,4:54:47.05,4:54:53.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ellie is not wearing any sort of adornment, she is bare arrested.
Dialogue: 2,4:54:53.26,4:54:58.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when you see her back at the farmhouse, in the final scene of the game,
Dialogue: 2,4:54:58.36,4:55:01.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,she's actually wearing this very bracelet,
Dialogue: 2,4:55:01.75,4:55:05.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is why it's interesting that they included it as part of the Collector's Edition.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:05.62,4:55:10.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is actually Dina's bracelet that she has.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:10.40,4:55:16.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the one that they include here, I mean, it's just it's a crappy little Collector's Edition.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:16.99,4:55:21.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,You know, trinket, but it's still it's still fun.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:21.10,4:55:23.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,But Ellie is wearing that.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:23.46,4:55:29.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Ellie wearing it even though seemingly she's split up with Dina,
Dialogue: 2,4:55:29.53,4:55:34.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Dina moved away and has completely cut ties.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:34.48,4:55:36.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the theory basically goes that
Dialogue: 2,4:55:36.76,4:55:41.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,they've returned to the house after a good amount of time, at least Ellie has.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:41.68,4:55:45.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,The house is cleared out, and they've decided to completely move on from Jackson.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:45.85,4:55:49.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're moving out, which is why the house is much more dilapidated.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:50.04,4:55:54.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Ellie has decided to leave all of Joel's things behind because she needs to move on,
Dialogue: 2,4:55:54.82,4:55:57.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,and she needs to stop bringing this with her.
Dialogue: 2,4:55:57.49,4:56:02.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so her wearing of the bracelet isn't just meant
Dialogue: 2,4:56:02.96,4:56:08.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,to symbolise that she still feels a connection with Dina,
Dialogue: 2,4:56:08.17,4:56:12.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,or that she misses Dina or wishes she had made a different decision.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:12.04,4:56:18.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that it's actually a direct message that she and Dina are back together.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:19.38,4:56:21.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that they've decided to move on together.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:21.76,4:56:26.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,Dina has forgiven Ellie, and that they are effectively living happily ever after.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:27.79,4:56:30.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now is that a stretch, perhaps… perhaps.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:30.32,4:56:35.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,Not many things in {\i1}TLOU{\i0}, at the world of {\i1}TLOU{\i0}, have happy endings.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:35.29,4:56:38.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I think the tone of the end of the game is very uplifting,
Dialogue: 2,4:56:38.50,4:56:40.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,very bright and sunny.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:40.63,4:56:46.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the title screen at the end of the game goes back to a sunny beach right outside the Resort,
Dialogue: 2,4:56:46.15,4:56:48.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,where the game reaches its climax,
Dialogue: 2,4:56:48.64,4:56:50.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,which I think symbolizes the same thing.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:50.92,4:56:54.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a bright, happy ending, morning has come.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:54.94,4:56:59.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,The light is always after the darkness, the sun has risen after night.
Dialogue: 2,4:56:59.92,4:57:03.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Use any analogy or simply you want.
Dialogue: 2,4:57:03.24,4:57:04.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 2,4:57:04.96,4:57:08.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'd like to think that the story actually has a happy ending,
Dialogue: 2,4:57:08.02,4:57:12.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that Ellie and Dina and the baby all got back together.
Dialogue: 2,4:57:12.61,4:57:15.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,And they're off living in some cabin in the middle of nowhere.
Dialogue: 2,4:57:15.70,4:57:18.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,They've left Jackson and they've moved on
Dialogue: 2,4:57:18.44,4:57:21.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they're just not going to be burdened by any of this anymore.
Dialogue: 2,4:57:22.48,4:57:24.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's at least what I choose to believe,
Dialogue: 2,4:57:24.40,4:57:29.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,because I think Ellie deserves that ending after all of this,
Dialogue: 2,4:57:29.65,4:57:32.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,and so that's what I'm going to go with until I learn differently.
Dialogue: 2,4:57:32.92,4:57:40.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think the fact that the designers included the bracelet on Ellie's wrist at that ending farm scene
Dialogue: 2,4:57:40.62,4:57:45.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,is directly indicative of that being what happened.
Dialogue: 2,4:57:45.67,4:57:50.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it's a little nod, maybe a little hint-hint that things actually ended happily,
Dialogue: 2,4:57:50.92,4:57:53.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,but who knows? I'd like to think that things ended happily.
Dialogue: 2,4:57:55.66,4:57:58.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,But all told, the game is very…
Dialogue: 2,4:57:59.26,4:58:02.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,difficult to come to terms with.
Dialogue: 2,4:58:02.31,4:58:08.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because it wasn't what I was expecting and perhaps even hoping for.
Dialogue: 2,4:58:08.68,4:58:13.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,But even so, I think it succeeded in what it was trying to do as I said earlier in the video.
Dialogue: 2,4:58:13.54,4:58:17.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think the mission was to get you to sympathize with Abby
Dialogue: 2,4:58:17.62,4:58:24.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,and to flip the script so that you went from hating Abby to caring about her.
Dialogue: 2,4:58:24.55,4:58:28.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so when you reach this conclusion that you initially had hoped for,
Dialogue: 2,4:58:28.95,4:58:35.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,for Ellie to take on Abby and kill her, it feels empty and hollow and unsatisfying.
Dialogue: 2,4:58:35.47,4:58:40.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because you realize that this isn't as simple as just revenge.
Dialogue: 2,4:58:40.06,4:58:47.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think that that in and of itself as a narrative decision is truly remarkable.
Dialogue: 2,4:58:47.95,4:58:52.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,It really is, whether you love it or hate it, you've got to give Naughty Dog credit
Dialogue: 2,4:58:52.80,4:58:58.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,for having the balls to do something so unbelievably risky
Dialogue: 2,4:58:58.62,4:59:04.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,that has obviously polarized the fan base, pissed off a lot of people.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:04.06,4:59:08.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,I can only imagine the hate mail that they've received since this went live,
Dialogue: 2,4:59:08.59,4:59:11.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,but they knew that it would, they knew that it would.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:12.10,4:59:17.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,And… they chose to do it anyways, when they didn't need to.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:17.44,4:59:22.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,They could have done just an obligatory, you know, sequel
Dialogue: 2,4:59:22.19,4:59:25.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,where Joel and Ellie embark on some new journey
Dialogue: 2,4:59:25.02,4:59:29.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,maybe Tommy gets murdered by Abby, and then they chase him down.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:29.44,4:59:33.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,And maybe right before the final scene, Abby kills Joel,
Dialogue: 2,4:59:33.52,4:59:37.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then Ellie gets revenge on Abby, wipes her out.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:37.03,4:59:41.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it's kind of the {\i1}Uncharted{\i0} style ending where everything wraps up,
Dialogue: 2,4:59:41.26,4:59:42.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,but a character died in it.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:42.76,4:59:45.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,It makes you feel more appreciative of what you have,
Dialogue: 2,4:59:45.43,4:59:47.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they could have done that.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:47.38,4:59:49.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,That would have been the easy way to go, though.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:49.39,4:59:52.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while I think it would have been received well, the gameplay would have been really solid.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:52.93,4:59:57.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think it would have challenged so many of us to think about
Dialogue: 2,4:59:57.62,4:59:59.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,video game narratives in a different way.
Dialogue: 2,4:59:59.93,5:00:03.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because as I've said for many many years at this point
Dialogue: 2,5:00:03.57,5:00:06.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,and by many many years and be like two or three,
Dialogue: 2,5:00:07.45,5:00:11.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think video games are the evolution of narrative storytelling.
Dialogue: 2,5:00:11.44,5:00:17.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think gaming is a remarkable tool, for storytelling.
Dialogue: 2,5:00:18.79,5:00:21.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I can't help but feel as though {\i1}TLOU2{\i0}
Dialogue: 2,5:00:21.94,5:00:28.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,takes a huge leap forward in the types of stories that can and will be told on the platform,
Dialogue: 2,5:00:28.78,5:00:31.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially moving into the next generation.
Dialogue: 2,5:00:31.42,5:00:33.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now some people think that that's terrible,
Dialogue: 2,5:00:33.01,5:00:37.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,some people hear that, and they think why can't stories just end happily ever after nowadays?
Dialogue: 2,5:00:37.24,5:00:40.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everything's going to be so dark, everything so dreary, everything so sad.
Dialogue: 2,5:00:40.81,5:00:44.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while that's true for some stories,
Dialogue: 2,5:00:44.05,5:00:45.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think more than anything,
Dialogue: 2,5:00:45.16,5:00:51.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's just trying to push narratives to the point where they can be… thought provoking
Dialogue: 2,5:00:51.05,5:00:55.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,in a way that very few happy go lucky stories are.
Dialogue: 2,5:00:55.21,5:00:56.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,I enjoy {\i1}Uncharted{\i0}.
Dialogue: 2,5:00:56.59,5:01:00.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm making a whole series of {\i1}Uncharted{\i0} critiques,
Dialogue: 2,5:01:00.94,5:01:04.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that's what I was doing before {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} launched.
Dialogue: 2,5:01:04.21,5:01:07.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this whole video experience began.
Dialogue: 2,5:01:09.49,5:01:12.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,But those stories don't really make you ponder, they don't make you think.
Dialogue: 2,5:01:12.85,5:01:16.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've never played an {\i1}Uncharted{\i0} game and then sat back and just…
Dialogue: 2,5:01:18.43,5:01:21.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Wow, what does this mean? What do I think of this?
Dialogue: 2,5:01:21.64,5:01:26.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't even know, I'm so conflicted, I have so many thoughts and emotions going on.
Dialogue: 2,5:01:26.09,5:01:32.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,Usually {\i1}Uncharted{\i0}'s emotional repertoire consists of action and excitement,
Dialogue: 2,5:01:32.83,5:01:36.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then maybe some light heartwarming moments
Dialogue: 2,5:01:36.32,5:01:40.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,with some witty banter back and forth between two characters you like,
Dialogue: 2,5:01:40.18,5:01:41.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that's kind of it.
Dialogue: 2,5:01:43.30,5:01:49.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think Naughty Dog is trying to push the boundary, and tell a story that does a lot more than that.
Dialogue: 2,5:01:49.60,5:01:51.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think they're successful,
Dialogue: 2,5:01:51.46,5:01:56.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think it's pretty remarkable what they've managed to accomplish.
Dialogue: 2,5:01:56.02,5:02:00.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,So while I am frustrated with {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} for pacing issues,
Dialogue: 2,5:02:00.35,5:02:06.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,for flip flopping back and forth between character so frequently that you start to lose focus,
Dialogue: 2,5:02:06.01,5:02:09.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,I do think that it's truly a remarkable game,
Dialogue: 2,5:02:09.94,5:02:13.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think it does far more good than it does bad.
Dialogue: 2,5:02:13.60,5:02:16.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while a couple of things are handled kinda clinically
Dialogue: 2,5:02:16.42,5:02:19.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think some characters aren't as relatable as they were hoping,
Dialogue: 2,5:02:19.87,5:02:22.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,for instance, Owen and Mel.
Dialogue: 2,5:02:22.69,5:02:26.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,When they get killed, you're supposed to feel really bad as far as I can tell,
Dialogue: 2,5:02:26.08,5:02:31.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I just even after playing through Abby sections, it just didn't really hit me hard.
Dialogue: 2,5:02:31.45,5:02:34.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,What hit me hard with seeing Abby so upset about it,
Dialogue: 2,5:02:34.33,5:02:38.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,it wasn't saying Owen and Mel killed that upset me.
Dialogue: 2,5:02:38.47,5:02:42.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think that that's more a failure of Naughty Dogs writing than a success.
Dialogue: 2,5:02:42.91,5:02:44.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think that was intentional
Dialogue: 2,5:02:45.88,5:02:47.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,as I said earlier in the video.
Dialogue: 2,5:02:47.50,5:02:49.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,But… all told,
Dialogue: 2,5:02:49.60,5:02:51.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think the game is pretty amazing.
Dialogue: 2,5:02:51.91,5:02:57.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's taken me months of playing through it multiple times to come to that conclusion,
Dialogue: 2,5:02:57.25,5:03:01.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I'll tell you right now when I finished the game the first time I was not…
Dialogue: 2,5:03:03.46,5:03:06.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,I was not in the same place I am now.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:06.10,5:03:10.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would not have said that I thought it was a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:10.03,5:03:14.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would not have said that I thought it was amazing and remarkable.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:14.05,5:03:18.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,I was pretty frustrated and emotionally torn apart,
Dialogue: 2,5:03:18.79,5:03:24.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,but after playing through the game a couple more times it really is kind of like an acquired taste.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:24.58,5:03:27.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's like a fine wine or caviar or something.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:27.79,5:03:30.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's… it's something where the more that you engage with it,
Dialogue: 2,5:03:30.67,5:03:34.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,the more you realize and appreciate all of the little details,
Dialogue: 2,5:03:34.66,5:03:39.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,all of the interweaving plot lines and character arcs.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:39.46,5:03:44.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,And for that reason I think the game is truly remarkable.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:44.02,5:03:46.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Will it take my game of the year? I… I don't know.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:46.80,5:03:51.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm really hoping that {\i1}Cyberpunk 2077{\i0} comes out and just blows us all away.
Dialogue: 2,5:03:51.37,5:03:53.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,I love CD Projekt Red,
Dialogue: 2,5:03:53.41,5:03:57.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,and from what I saw behind closed doors at E3 last year of {\i1}Cyberpunk{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,5:03:57.82,5:04:01.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think it has the possibility of being really impressive,
Dialogue: 2,5:04:01.93,5:04:05.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I'm also worried that hype is getting out of control,
Dialogue: 2,5:04:05.35,5:04:07.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is very possible with that game.
Dialogue: 2,5:04:07.69,5:04:09.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,But we'll see, who knows,
Dialogue: 2,5:04:09.01,5:04:13.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,by the time you're watching this video, you've probably played through {\i1}Cyberpunk{\i0},
Dialogue: 2,5:04:13.60,5:04:17.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,or you might have played through {\i1}Cyberpunk{\i0}, and you'll be laughing at what I'm saying,
Dialogue: 2,5:04:17.02,5:04:19.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,or maybe they'll be like… Yeah, no, it is terrible, It's awful.
Dialogue: 2,5:04:19.87,5:04:21.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,I have no idea, I have no idea.
Dialogue: 2,5:04:21.37,5:04:27.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,But what I can say is that I think {\i1}TLOU{\i0} does a lot to move the industry forward.
Dialogue: 2,5:04:27.94,5:04:33.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,I think that the risks that they took are truly…
Dialogue: 2,5:04:36.07,5:04:38.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,"applautable", if that's even a word.
Dialogue: 2,5:04:38.59,5:04:42.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,I appreciate that they took those risks that they didn't play it safe.
Dialogue: 2,5:04:42.34,5:04:47.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while I think a lot of us probably wish, they had gone a different direction,
Dialogue: 2,5:04:47.20,5:04:51.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,I respect the hell out of them for what they did, and I think it worked.
Dialogue: 2,5:04:52.39,5:04:56.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while I wouldn't have thought to go this direction,
Dialogue: 2,5:04:56.47,5:04:59.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm… in the end, I think glad that they did.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:00.97,5:05:04.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,But even now, I am… I'm very conflicted.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:04.28,5:05:08.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think the point of art is to make you think to make you ponder.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:08.84,5:05:15.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everything that went on in the story that was being told to ponder your place in this world
Dialogue: 2,5:05:15.24,5:05:17.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,and everything that's going on.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:17.26,5:05:23.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I think {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} does that, in a way that literally no game has ever done for me.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:23.17,5:05:26.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,And for that I just have to say thank you to Naughty Dog.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:26.80,5:05:31.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,They've done something truly incredible, truly.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:31.27,5:05:33.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that's all from me.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:33.43,5:05:36.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thank you for watching this monstrosity of a video.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:36.44,5:05:41.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,At me and everybody that I've worked with on this video we truly appreciate it.
Dialogue: 2,5:05:41.35,5:05:47.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,A big thank to Jacob, my editor for all of the hard work he's done on this video,
Dialogue: 2,5:05:47.65,5:05:54.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,he's edited a lot of sections that you've seen and been watching for the last few hours, so…
Dialogue: 2,5:05:54.70,5:05:59.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,Big thanks to him, and thanked all of the patrons, and all of the viewers who have been so patient
Dialogue: 2,5:05:59.59,5:06:04.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,because this has been the video that's eaten up all my time for the last few months
Dialogue: 2,5:06:04.18,5:06:08.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,as I was getting ready for a wedding, as I was starting a new job.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:08.05,5:06:10.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is consumed all of my time.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:10.27,5:06:15.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,And while I think {\i1}TLOU2{\i0} was incredible in a lot of ways,
Dialogue: 2,5:06:15.28,5:06:20.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm… I am ready to move on and to tackle the next big thing, so…
Dialogue: 2,5:06:21.28,5:06:24.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's bizarre to be done with everything, it's bizarre to be at the end of this video.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:24.82,5:06:26.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,I hope that you enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:26.05,5:06:29.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you did, please at the very least hit the like button.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:29.23,5:06:32.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you really enjoyed it, hit the subscribe button.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:32.59,5:06:35.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't mean to sound entitled,
Dialogue: 2,5:06:35.08,5:06:38.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,but after all of this, if you really did enjoy this video and got to this point,
Dialogue: 2,5:06:38.74,5:06:41.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,I would like to think that you would, at the very least, subscribe
Dialogue: 2,5:06:41.66,5:06:46.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and maybe even ring the bells so to get notified of the next video.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:46.63,5:06:47.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,But truly, thank you.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:47.86,5:06:49.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thank you for watching.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:49.15,5:06:50.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thank you for sharing the video.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:50.92,5:06:54.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thank you for donating thanks for doing everything that you guys do.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:54.25,5:06:58.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,You're truly amazing and I love you all more than you could possibly know.
Dialogue: 2,5:06:58.36,5:07:03.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'll see you in the next video, which will probably be a fair amount, shorter.
Dialogue: 2,5:07:04.75,5:07:06.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Truly, thank you,
Dialogue: 2,5:07:06.55,5:07:07.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,I love you guys,
Dialogue: 2,5:07:07.93,5:07:09.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I'll see you in the next video.
